<book id="PSA"><id id="PSA">Psalms
</id><h>((Psalms))
<!--currentProgress-->
</h><toc level="1">The Book of Psalms
</toc><toc level="2">Psalms
</toc><toc level="3">Psa
</toc><p sfm="mt">The Book of Psalms
</p><c id="1" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.1.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man that walketh not in the counsel of the ungodly, nor standeth in the way of sinners, nor sitteth in the seat of the scornful.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.1.2" /> \begin{signline}But his delight\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the law of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and in his law doth he meditate day and night.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.1.3" /> \begin{signline}And he shall be like a tree planted by the rivers of water, that bringeth forth his fruit in his season; his leaf also shall not wither; and whatsoever he doeth shall prosper.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.1.4" /> \begin{signline}The ungodly\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not so: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the chaff which the wind driveth away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.1.5" /> \begin{signline}Therefore the ungodly shall not stand in the judgment, nor sinners in the congregation of the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.1.6" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}knoweth the way of the righteous: but the way of the ungodly shall perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="2" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.2.1" /> \begin{signline}Why do the heathen rage, and the people imagine a vain thing?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.2.2" /> \begin{signline}The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers take counsel together, against the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and against his anointed,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}saying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline},\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.2.3" /> \begin{signline}Let us break their bands asunder, and cast away their cords from us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.2.4" /> \begin{signline}He that sitteth in the heavens shall laugh: the Lord shall have them in derision.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.2.5" /> \begin{signline}Then shall he speak unto them in his wrath, and vex them in his sore displeasure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.2.6" /> \begin{signline}Yet have I set my king upon my holy hill of Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.2.7" /> \begin{signline}I will declare the decree: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath said unto me, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my Son; this day have I begotten thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.2.8" /> \begin{signline}Ask of me, and I shall give\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thee\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the heathen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine inheritance, and the uttermost parts of the earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy possession.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.2.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt break them with a rod of iron; thou shalt dash them in pieces like a potter’s vessel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.2.10" /> \begin{signline}Be wise now therefore, O ye kings: be instructed, ye judges of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.2.11" /> \begin{signline}Serve the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with fear, and rejoice with trembling.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.2.12" /> \begin{signline}Kiss the Son, lest he be angry, and ye perish\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the way, when his wrath is kindled but a little. Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all they that put their trust in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="3" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he fled\end{signline}
\begin{signline}from\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Absalom\end{signline}
\begin{signline}his son.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.3.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how are they increased that trouble me! many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that rise up against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.3.2" /> \begin{signline}Many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}which say of my soul,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no help for him in God. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.3.3" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a shield for me; my glory, and the lifter up of mine head.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.3.4" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with my voice, and he heard me out of his holy hill. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.3.5" /> \begin{signline}I laid me down and slept; I awaked; for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}sustained me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.3.6" /> \begin{signline}I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people, that have set\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}themselves\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me round about.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.3.7" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; save me, O my God: for thou hast smitten all mine enemies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the cheek bone; thou hast broken the teeth of the ungodly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.3.8" /> \begin{signline}Salvation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belongeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: thy blessing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon thy people. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="4" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.4.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear me when I call, O God of my righteousness: thou hast enlarged me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when I was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in distress; have mercy upon me, and hear my prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.4.2" /> \begin{signline}O ye sons of men, how long\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}will ye turn\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my glory into shame?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}how long\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will ye love vanity,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seek after leasing? Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.4.3" /> \begin{signline}But know that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath set apart him that is godly for himself: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will hear when I call unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.4.4" /> \begin{signline}Stand in awe, and sin not: commune with your own heart upon your bed, and be still. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.4.5" /> \begin{signline}Offer the sacrifices of righteousness, and put your trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.4.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}many that say, Who will shew us\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good? \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, lift thou up the light of thy countenance upon us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.4.7" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast put gladness in my heart, more than in the time\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their corn and their wine increased.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.4.8" /> \begin{signline}I will both lay me down in peace, and sleep: for thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, only makest me dwell in safety.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="5" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Nehiloth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.5.1" /> \begin{signline}Give ear to my words, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, consider my meditation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.5.2" /> \begin{signline}Hearken unto the voice of my cry, my King, and my God: for unto thee will I pray.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.5.3" /> \begin{signline}My voice shalt thou hear in the morning, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; in the morning will I direct\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my prayer\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto thee, and will look up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.5.4" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not a God that hath pleasure in wickedness: neither shall evil dwell with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.5.5" /> \begin{signline}The foolish shall not stand in thy sight: thou hatest all workers of iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.5.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt destroy them that speak leasing: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will abhor the bloody and deceitful man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.5.7" /> \begin{signline}But as for me, I will come\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}into\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy house in the multitude of thy mercy:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thy fear will I worship toward thy holy temple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.5.8" /> \begin{signline}Lead me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in thy righteousness because of mine enemies; make thy way straight before my face.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.5.9" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no faithfulness in their mouth; their inward part\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}very wickedness; their throat\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an open sepulchre; they flatter with their tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.5.10" /> \begin{signline}Destroy thou them, O God; let them fall by their own counsels; cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions; for they have rebelled against thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.5.11" /> \begin{signline}But let all those that put their trust in thee rejoice: let them ever shout for joy, because thou defendest them: let them also that love thy name be joyful in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.5.12" /> \begin{signline}For thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, wilt bless the righteous; with favour wilt thou compass him as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="6" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Sheminith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.6.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, rebuke me not in thine anger, neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.6.2" /> \begin{signline}Have mercy upon me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}weak: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, heal me; for my bones are vexed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.6.3" /> \begin{signline}My soul is also sore vexed: but thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how long?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.6.4" /> \begin{signline}Return, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, deliver my soul: oh save me for thy mercies’ sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.6.5" /> \begin{signline}For in death\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no remembrance of thee: in the grave who shall give thee thanks?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.6.6" /> \begin{signline}I am weary with my groaning; all the night make I my bed to swim; I water my couch with my tears.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.6.7" /> \begin{signline}Mine eye is consumed because of grief; it waxeth old because of all mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.6.8" /> \begin{signline}Depart from me, all ye workers of iniquity; for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath heard the voice of my weeping.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.6.9" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath heard my supplication; the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will receive my prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.6.10" /> \begin{signline}Let all mine enemies be ashamed and sore vexed: let them return\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}be ashamed suddenly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="7" />
<d>\begin{signline}Shiggaion\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}which he sang\end{signline}
\begin{signline}unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline}
\begin{signline}concerning the words\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Cush\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the Benjamite.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.7.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, in thee do I put my trust: save me from all them that persecute me, and deliver me:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.7.2" /> \begin{signline}Lest he tear my soul like a lion, rending\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in pieces, while\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to deliver.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.7.3" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, if I have done this; if there be iniquity in my hands;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.7.4" /> \begin{signline}If I have rewarded evil unto him that was at peace with me; (yea, I have delivered him that without cause is mine enemy:)\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.7.5" /> \begin{signline}Let the enemy persecute my soul, and take\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}yea, let him tread down my life upon the earth, and lay mine honour in the dust. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.7.6" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in thine anger, lift up thyself because of the rage of mine enemies: and awake for me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast commanded.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.7.7" /> \begin{signline}So shall the congregation of the people compass thee about: for their sakes therefore return thou on high.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.7.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall judge the people: judge me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, according to my righteousness, and according to mine integrity\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.7.9" /> \begin{signline}Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end; but establish the just: for the righteous God trieth the hearts and reins.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.7.10" /> \begin{signline}My defence\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of God, which saveth the upright in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.7.11" /> \begin{signline}God judgeth the righteous, and God is angry\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with the wicked\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}every day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.7.12" /> \begin{signline}If he turn not, he will whet his sword; he hath bent his bow, and made it ready.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.7.13" /> \begin{signline}He hath also prepared for him the instruments of death; he ordaineth his arrows against the persecutors.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.7.14" /> \begin{signline}Behold, he travaileth with iniquity, and hath conceived mischief, and brought forth falsehood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.7.15" /> \begin{signline}He made a pit, and digged it, and is fallen into the ditch\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he made.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.7.16" /> \begin{signline}His mischief shall return upon his own head, and his violent dealing shall come down upon his own pate.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.7.17" /> \begin{signline}I will praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}according to his righteousness: and will sing praise to the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}most high.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="8" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Gittith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.8.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our Lord, how excellent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy name in all the earth! who hast set thy glory above the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.8.2" /> \begin{signline}Out of the mouth of babes and sucklings hast thou ordained strength because of thine enemies, that thou mightest still the enemy and the avenger.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.8.3" /> \begin{signline}When I consider thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, the moon and the stars, which thou hast ordained;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.8.4" /> \begin{signline}What is man, that thou art mindful of him? and the son of man, that thou visitest him?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.8.5" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast made him a little lower than the angels, and hast crowned him with glory and honour.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.8.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou madest him to have dominion over the works of thy hands; thou hast put all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}under his feet:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.8.7" /> \begin{signline}All sheep and oxen, yea, and the beasts of the field;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.8.8" /> \begin{signline}The fowl of the air, and the fish of the sea,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and whatsoever\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}passeth through the paths of the seas.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.8.9" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our Lord, how excellent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy name in all the earth!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="9" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Muthlabben,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.9.1" /> \begin{signline}I will praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, with my whole heart; I will shew forth all thy marvellous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.9.2" /> \begin{signline}I will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most High.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.9.3" /> \begin{signline}When mine enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at thy presence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.9.4" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast maintained my right and my cause; thou satest in the throne judging  right.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.9.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast rebuked the heathen, thou hast destroyed the wicked, thou hast put out their name for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.9.6" /> \begin{signline}O thou enemy, destructions are come to a perpetual end: and thou hast destroyed cities; their memorial is perished with them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.9.7" /> \begin{signline}But the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall endure for ever: he hath prepared his throne for judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.9.8" /> \begin{signline}And he shall judge the world in righteousness, he shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.9.9" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.9.10" /> \begin{signline}And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee: for thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.9.11" /> \begin{signline}Sing praises to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, which dwelleth in Zion: declare among the people his doings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.9.12" /> \begin{signline}When he maketh inquisition for blood, he remembereth them: he forgetteth not the cry of the humble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.9.13" /> \begin{signline}Have mercy upon me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; consider my trouble\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which I suffer\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of them that hate me, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.9.14" /> \begin{signline}That I may shew forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in thy salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.9.15" /> \begin{signline}The heathen are sunk down in the pit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they made: in the net which they hid is their own foot taken.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.9.16" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}is known\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}by\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he executeth: the wicked is snared in the work of his own hands. Higgaion. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.9.17" /> \begin{signline}The wicked shall be turned into hell,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all the nations that forget God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.9.18" /> \begin{signline}For the needy shall not alway be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perish for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.9.19" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; let not man prevail: let the heathen be judged in thy sight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.9.20" /> \begin{signline}Put them in fear, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the nations may know themselves\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to be but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}men. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="10" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.10.1" /> \begin{signline}Why standest thou afar off, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}why\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hidest thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thyself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in times of trouble?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.10.2" /> \begin{signline}The wicked in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pride doth persecute the poor: let them be taken in the devices that they have imagined.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.10.3" /> \begin{signline}For the wicked boasteth of his heart’s desire, and blesseth the covetous,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}abhorreth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.10.4" /> \begin{signline}The wicked, through the pride of his countenance, will not seek\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}after God:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not in all his thoughts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.10.5" /> \begin{signline}His ways are always grievous; thy judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far above out of his sight:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all his enemies, he puffeth at them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.10.6" /> \begin{signline}He hath said in his heart, I shall not be moved: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}I shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}never\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in adversity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.10.7" /> \begin{signline}His mouth is full of cursing and deceit and fraud: under his tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mischief and vanity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.10.8" /> \begin{signline}He sitteth in the lurking places of the villages: in the secret places doth he murder the innocent: his eyes are privily set against the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.10.9" /> \begin{signline}He lieth in wait secretly as a lion in his den: he lieth in wait to catch the poor: he doth catch the poor, when he draweth him into his net.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.10.10" /> \begin{signline}He croucheth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}humbleth himself, that the poor may fall by his strong ones.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.10.11" /> \begin{signline}He hath said in his heart, God hath forgotten: he hideth his face; he will never see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.10.12" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; O God, lift up thine hand: forget not the humble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.10.13" /> \begin{signline}Wherefore doth the wicked contemn God? he hath said in his heart, Thou wilt not require\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.10.14" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast seen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for thou beholdest mischief and spite, to requite\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with thy hand: the poor committeth himself unto thee; thou art the helper of the fatherless.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.10.15" /> \begin{signline}Break thou the arm of the wicked and the evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seek out his wickedness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}till\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou find none.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.10.16" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}King for ever and ever: the heathen are perished out of his land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.10.17" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou hast heard the desire of the humble: thou wilt prepare their heart, thou wilt cause thine ear to hear:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.10.18" /> \begin{signline}To judge the fatherless and the oppressed, that the man of the earth may no more oppress.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="11" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.11.1" /> \begin{signline}In the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}put I my trust: how say ye to my soul, Flee\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a bird to your mountain?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.11.2" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, the wicked bend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bow, they make ready their arrow upon the string, that they may privily shoot at the upright in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.11.3" /> \begin{signline}If the foundations be destroyed, what can the righteous do?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.11.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his holy temple, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}throne\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in heaven: his eyes behold, his eyelids try, the children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.11.5" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}trieth the righteous: but the wicked and him that loveth violence his soul hateth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.11.6" /> \begin{signline}Upon the wicked he shall rain snares, fire and brimstone, and an horrible tempest:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the portion of their cup.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.11.7" /> \begin{signline}For the righteous \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}loveth righteousness; his countenance doth behold the upright.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="12" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Sheminith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.12.1" /> \begin{signline}Help, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for the godly man ceaseth; for the faithful fail from among the children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.12.2" /> \begin{signline}They speak vanity every one with his neighbour:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flattering lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with a double heart do they speak.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.12.3" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall cut off all flattering lips,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the tongue that speaketh proud things:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.12.4" /> \begin{signline}Who have said, With our tongue will we prevail; our lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our own: who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lord over us?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.12.5" /> \begin{signline}For the oppression of the poor, for the sighing of the needy, now will I arise, saith the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; I will set\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in safety\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from him that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}puffeth at him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.12.6" /> \begin{signline}The words of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pure words:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}silver tried in a furnace of earth, purified seven times.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.12.7" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt keep them, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou shalt preserve them from this generation for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.12.8" /> \begin{signline}The wicked walk on every side, when the vilest men are exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="13" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.13.1" /> \begin{signline}How long wilt thou forget me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? for ever? how long wilt thou hide thy face from me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.13.2" /> \begin{signline}How long shall I take counsel in my soul,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}having\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sorrow in my heart daily? how long shall mine enemy be exalted over me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.13.3" /> \begin{signline}Consider\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hear me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God: lighten mine eyes, lest I sleep the\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}sleep of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}death;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.13.4" /> \begin{signline}Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against him;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}those that trouble me rejoice when I am moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.13.5" /> \begin{signline}But I have trusted in thy mercy; my heart shall rejoice in thy salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.13.6" /> \begin{signline}I will sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="14" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.14.1" /> \begin{signline}The fool hath said in his heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no God. They are corrupt, they have done abominable works,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none that doeth good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.14.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were any that did understand,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seek God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.14.3" /> \begin{signline}They are all gone aside, they are\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}all\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}together become filthy:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none that doeth good, no, not one.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.14.4" /> \begin{signline}Have all the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they eat bread, and call not upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.14.5" /> \begin{signline}There were they in great fear: for God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the generation of the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.14.6" /> \begin{signline}Ye have shamed the counsel of the poor, because the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his refuge.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.14.7" /> \begin{signline}Oh that the salvation of Israel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were come\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}out of Zion! when the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Israel shall be glad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="15" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.15.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, who shall abide in thy tabernacle? who shall dwell in thy holy hill?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.15.2" /> \begin{signline}He that walketh uprightly, and worketh righteousness, and speaketh the truth in his heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.15.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}backbiteth not with his tongue, nor doeth evil to his neighbour, nor taketh up a reproach against his neighbour.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.15.4" /> \begin{signline}In whose eyes a vile person is contemned; but he honoureth them that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}He that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sweareth to\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his own\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hurt, and changeth not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.15.5" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}putteth not out his money to usury, nor taketh reward against the innocent. He that doeth these\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall never be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="16" />
<d>\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.16.1" /> \begin{signline}Preserve me, O God: for in thee do I put my trust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.16.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}O my soul\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, thou hast said unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my Lord: my goodness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}extendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not to thee;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.16.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}But\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the saints that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the earth, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the excellent, in whom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all my delight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.16.4" /> \begin{signline}Their sorrows shall be multiplied\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hasten\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}after\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}another\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}god:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names into my lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.16.5" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the portion of mine inheritance and of my cup: thou maintainest my lot.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.16.6" /> \begin{signline}The lines are fallen unto me in pleasant\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}places;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}yea, I have a goodly heritage.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.16.7" /> \begin{signline}I will bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, who hath given me counsel: my reins also instruct me in the night seasons.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.16.8" /> \begin{signline}I have set the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}always before me: because\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}at my right hand, I shall not be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.16.9" /> \begin{signline}Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoiceth: my flesh also shall rest in hope.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.16.10" /> \begin{signline}For thou wilt not leave my soul in hell; neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.16.11" /> \begin{signline}Thou wilt shew me the path of life: in thy presence\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fulness of joy; at thy right hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pleasures for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="17" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Prayer\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.17.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear the right, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, attend unto my cry, give ear unto my prayer,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that goeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not out of feigned lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.17.2" /> \begin{signline}Let my sentence come forth from thy presence; let thine eyes behold the things that are equal.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.17.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast proved mine heart; thou hast visited\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the night; thou hast tried me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shalt find nothing; I am purposed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my mouth shall not transgress.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.17.4" /> \begin{signline}Concerning the works of men, by the word of thy lips I have kept\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the paths of the destroyer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.17.5" /> \begin{signline}Hold up my goings in thy paths,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my footsteps slip not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.17.6" /> \begin{signline}I have called upon thee, for thou wilt hear me, O God: incline thine ear unto me,\end{signline} <add> \begin{signline}and hear\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my speech.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.17.7" /> \begin{signline}Shew thy marvellous lovingkindness, O thou that savest by thy right hand them which put their trust\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in thee\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from those that rise up\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}against them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.17.8" /> \begin{signline}Keep me as the apple of the eye, hide me under the shadow of thy wings,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.17.9" /> \begin{signline}From the wicked that oppress me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my deadly enemies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}compass me about.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.17.10" /> \begin{signline}They are inclosed in their own fat: with their mouth they speak proudly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.17.11" /> \begin{signline}They have now compassed us in our steps: they have set their eyes bowing down to the earth;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.17.12" /> \begin{signline}Like as a lion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is greedy of his prey, and as it were a young lion lurking in secret places.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.17.13" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, disappoint him, cast him down: deliver my soul from the wicked,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy sword:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.17.14" /> \begin{signline}From men\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy hand, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, from men of the world,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which have\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their portion in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life, and whose belly thou fillest with thy hid\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}treasure:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they are full of children, and leave the rest of their\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}substance\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to their babes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.17.15" /> \begin{signline}As for me, I will behold thy face in righteousness: I shall be satisfied, when I awake, with thy likeness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="18" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the servant\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline}
\begin{signline}who spake\end{signline}
\begin{signline}unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>
\begin{signline}the words\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of this song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}in the day\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>
\begin{signline}delivered\end{signline}
\begin{signline}him from the hand\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of all his enemies,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and from the hand\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Saul:\end{signline}
\begin{signline}And he said,\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.18.1" /> \begin{signline}I will love thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, my strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.18.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my buckler, and the horn of my salvation,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my high tower.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.18.3" /> \begin{signline}I will call upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who is worthy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to be praised: so shall I be saved from mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.18.4" /> \begin{signline}The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.18.5" /> \begin{signline}The sorrows of hell compassed me about: the snares of death prevented me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.18.6" /> \begin{signline}In my distress I called upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and cried unto my God: he heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}into his ears.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.18.7" /> \begin{signline}Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken, because he was wroth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.18.8" /> \begin{signline}There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.18.9" /> \begin{signline}He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}under his feet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.18.10" /> \begin{signline}And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly: yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.18.11" /> \begin{signline}He made darkness his secret place; his pavilion round about him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dark waters\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thick clouds of the skies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.18.12" /> \begin{signline}At the brightness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before him his thick clouds passed, hail\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}stones\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and coals of fire.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.18.13" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}stones\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and coals of fire.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.18.14" /> \begin{signline}Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings, and discomfited them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.18.15" /> \begin{signline}Then the channels of waters were seen, and the foundations of the world were discovered at thy rebuke, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.18.16" /> \begin{signline}He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.18.17" /> \begin{signline}He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.18.18" /> \begin{signline}They prevented me in the day of my calamity: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}was my stay.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.18.19" /> \begin{signline}He brought me forth also into a large place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.18.20" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.18.21" /> \begin{signline}For I have kept the ways of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and have not wickedly departed from my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.18.22" /> \begin{signline}For all his judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.18.23" /> \begin{signline}I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.18.24" /> \begin{signline}Therefore hath the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.18.25" /> \begin{signline}With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful; with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.18.26" /> \begin{signline}With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself froward.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.18.27" /> \begin{signline}For thou wilt save the afflicted people; but wilt bring down high looks.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.18.28" /> \begin{signline}For thou wilt light my candle: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God will enlighten my darkness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.18.29" /> \begin{signline}For by thee I have run through a troop; and by my God have I leaped over a wall.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.18.30" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God, his way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perfect: the word of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}is tried: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a buckler to all those that trust in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.18.31" />\begin{signline}For who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God save the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? or who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a rock save our God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.18.32" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.18.33" /> \begin{signline}He maketh my feet like hinds’\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}feet\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and setteth me upon my high places.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.18.34" /> \begin{signline}He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.18.35" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation: and thy right hand hath holden me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.18.36" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.18.37" /> \begin{signline}I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.18.38" /> \begin{signline}I have wounded them that they were not able to rise: they are fallen under my feet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.18.39" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.18.40" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.18.41" /> \begin{signline}They cried, but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to save\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them: even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, but he answered them not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.18.42" /> \begin{signline}Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.18.43" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast made me the head of the heathen: a people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I have not known shall serve me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.18.44" /> \begin{signline}As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.18.45" /> \begin{signline}The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="46" bcv="PSA.18.46" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}liveth; and blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="47" bcv="PSA.18.47" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="48" bcv="PSA.18.48" /> \begin{signline}He delivereth me from mine enemies: yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="49" bcv="PSA.18.49" /> \begin{signline}Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, among the heathen, and sing praises unto thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="50" bcv="PSA.18.50" /> \begin{signline}Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="19" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.19.1" /> \begin{signline}The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handywork.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.19.2" /> \begin{signline}Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.19.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no speech nor language,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}where\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their voice is not heard.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.19.4" /> \begin{signline}Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.19.5" />\begin{signline}Which\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.19.6" /> \begin{signline}His going forth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.19.7" /> \begin{signline}The law of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sure, making wise the simple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.19.8" /> \begin{signline}The statutes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pure, enlightening the eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.19.9" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}true\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteous altogether.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.19.10" /> \begin{signline}More to be desired\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are they\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}than gold, yea, than much fine gold: sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.19.11" /> \begin{signline}Moreover by them is thy servant warned:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in keeping of them\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great reward.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.19.12" /> \begin{signline}Who can understand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}errors? cleanse thou me from secret\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}faults\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.19.13" /> \begin{signline}Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}sins;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.19.14" /> \begin{signline}Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, my strength, and my redeemer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="20" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.20.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hear thee in the day of trouble; the name of the God of Jacob defend thee;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.20.2" /> \begin{signline}Send thee help from the sanctuary, and strengthen thee out of Zion;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.20.3" /> \begin{signline}Remember all thy offerings, and accept thy burnt sacrifice; Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.20.4" /> \begin{signline}Grant thee according to thine own heart, and fulfil all thy counsel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.20.5" /> \begin{signline}We will rejoice in thy salvation, and in the name of our God we will set up\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}our\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}banners: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}fulfil all thy petitions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.20.6" /> \begin{signline}Now know I that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}saveth his anointed; he will hear him from his holy heaven with the saving strength of his right hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.20.7" />\begin{signline}Some\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}trust\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in chariots, and some in horses: but we will remember the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.20.8" /> \begin{signline}They are brought down and fallen: but we are risen, and stand upright.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.20.9" /> \begin{signline}Save, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: let the king hear us when we call.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="21" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.21.1" /> \begin{signline}The king shall joy in thy strength, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and in thy salvation how greatly shall he rejoice!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.21.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast given him his heart’s desire, and hast not withholden the request of his lips. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.21.3" /> \begin{signline}For thou preventest him with the blessings of goodness: thou settest a crown of pure gold on his head.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.21.4" /> \begin{signline}He asked life of thee,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou gavest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}length of days for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.21.5" /> \begin{signline}His glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great in thy salvation: honour and majesty hast thou laid upon him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.21.6" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast made him most blessed for ever: thou hast made him exceeding glad with thy countenance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.21.7" /> \begin{signline}For the king trusteth in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and through the mercy of the most High he shall not be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.21.8" /> \begin{signline}Thine hand shall find out all thine enemies: thy right hand shall find out those that hate thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.21.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt make them as a fiery oven in the time of thine anger: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall swallow them up in his wrath, and the fire shall devour them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.21.10" /> \begin{signline}Their fruit shalt thou destroy from the earth, and their seed from among the children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.21.11" /> \begin{signline}For they intended evil against thee: they imagined a mischievous device,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they are not able\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to perform\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.21.12" /> \begin{signline}Therefore shalt thou make them turn their back,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou shalt make ready\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thine arrows\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon thy strings against the face of them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.21.13" /> \begin{signline}Be thou exalted, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in thine own strength:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will we sing and praise thy power.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="22" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Aijeleth\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Shahar,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.22.1" /> \begin{signline}My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}why art thou so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far from helping me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the words of my roaring?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.22.2" /> \begin{signline}O my God, I cry in the daytime, but thou hearest not; and in the night season, and am not silent.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.22.3" />\begin{signline}But thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}O thou\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that inhabitest the praises of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.22.4" /> \begin{signline}Our fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.22.5" /> \begin{signline}They cried unto thee, and were delivered: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.22.6" />\begin{signline}But I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.22.7" /> \begin{signline}All they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}saying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline},\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.22.8" /> \begin{signline}He trusted on the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he would deliver him: let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.22.9" />\begin{signline}But thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that took me out of the womb: thou didst make me hope\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when I was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon my mother’s breasts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.22.10" /> \begin{signline}I was cast upon thee from the womb: thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God from my mother’s belly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.22.11" /> \begin{signline}Be not far from me; for trouble\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}near; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.22.12" /> \begin{signline}Many bulls have compassed me: strong\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}bulls\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of Bashan have beset me round.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.22.13" /> \begin{signline}They gaped upon me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their mouths,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a ravening and a roaring lion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.22.14" /> \begin{signline}I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint: my heart is like wax; it is melted in the midst of my bowels.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.22.15" /> \begin{signline}My strength is dried up like a potsherd; and my tongue cleaveth to my jaws; and thou hast brought me into the dust of death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.22.16" /> \begin{signline}For dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have inclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.22.17" /> \begin{signline}I may tell all my bones: they look\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}stare upon me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.22.18" /> \begin{signline}They part my garments among them, and cast lots upon my vesture.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.22.19" /> \begin{signline}But be not thou far from me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: O my strength, haste thee to help me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.22.20" /> \begin{signline}Deliver my soul from the sword; my darling from the power of the dog.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.22.21" /> \begin{signline}Save me from the lion’s mouth: for thou hast heard me from the horns of the unicorns.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.22.22" /> \begin{signline}I will declare thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.22.23" /> \begin{signline}Ye that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, praise him; all ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him; and fear him, all ye the seed of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.22.24" /> \begin{signline}For he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; neither hath he hid his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.22.25" /> \begin{signline}My praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of thee in the great congregation: I will pay my vows before them that fear him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.22.26" /> \begin{signline}The meek shall eat and be satisfied: they shall praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}that seek him: your heart shall live for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.22.27" /> \begin{signline}All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.22.28" /> \begin{signline}For the kingdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: and he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the governor among the nations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.22.29" />\begin{signline}All\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they that be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fat upon earth shall eat and worship: all they that go down to the dust shall bow before him: and none can keep alive his own soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.22.30" /> \begin{signline}A seed shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.22.31" /> \begin{signline}They shall come, and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born, that he hath done\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="23" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.23.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my shepherd; I shall not want.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.23.2" /> \begin{signline}He maketh me to lie down in green pastures: he leadeth me beside the still waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.23.3" /> \begin{signline}He restoreth my soul: he leadeth me in the paths of righteousness for his name’s sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.23.4" /> \begin{signline}Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with me; thy rod and thy staff they comfort me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.23.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou preparest a table before me in the presence of mine enemies: thou anointest my head with oil; my cup runneth over.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.23.6" /> \begin{signline}Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="24" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.24.1" /> \begin{signline}The earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.24.2" /> \begin{signline}For he hath founded it upon the seas, and established it upon the floods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.24.3" /> \begin{signline}Who shall ascend into the hill of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? or who shall stand in his holy place?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.24.4" /> \begin{signline}He that hath clean hands, and a pure heart; who hath not lifted up his soul unto vanity, nor sworn deceitfully.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.24.5" /> \begin{signline}He shall receive the blessing from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and righteousness from the God of his salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.24.6" />\begin{signline}This\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the generation of them that seek him, that seek thy face, O Jacob. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.24.7" /> \begin{signline}Lift up your heads, O ye gates; and be ye lift up, ye everlasting doors; and the King of glory shall come in.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.24.8" />\begin{signline}Who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}this King of glory? The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}strong and mighty, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}mighty in battle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.24.9" /> \begin{signline}Lift up your heads, O ye gates; even lift\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}up, ye everlasting doors; and the King of glory shall come in.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.24.10" /> \begin{signline}Who is this King of glory? The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts, he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the King of glory. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="25" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.25.1" /> \begin{signline}Unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, do I lift up my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.25.2" /> \begin{signline}O my God, I trust in thee: let me not be ashamed, let not mine enemies triumph over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.25.3" /> \begin{signline}Yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed: let them be ashamed which transgress without cause.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.25.4" /> \begin{signline}Shew me thy ways, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; teach me thy paths.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.25.5" /> \begin{signline}Lead me in thy truth, and teach me: for thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of my salvation; on thee do I wait all the day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.25.6" /> \begin{signline}Remember, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thy tender mercies and thy lovingkindnesses; for they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}have been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ever of old.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.25.7" /> \begin{signline}Remember not the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions: according to thy mercy remember thou me for thy goodness’ sake, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.25.8" /> \begin{signline}Good and upright\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: therefore will he teach sinners in the way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.25.9" /> \begin{signline}The meek will he guide in judgment: and the meek will he teach his way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.25.10" /> \begin{signline}All the paths of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mercy and truth unto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.25.11" /> \begin{signline}For thy name’s sake, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, pardon mine iniquity; for it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.25.12" /> \begin{signline}What man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? him shall he teach in the way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he shall choose.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.25.13" /> \begin{signline}His soul shall dwell at ease; and his seed shall inherit the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.25.14" /> \begin{signline}The secret of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with them that fear him; and he will shew them his covenant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.25.15" /> \begin{signline}Mine eyes\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ever toward the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for he shall pluck my feet out of the net.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.25.16" /> \begin{signline}Turn thee unto me, and have mercy upon me; for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}desolate and afflicted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.25.17" /> \begin{signline}The troubles of my heart are enlarged:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}O\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bring thou me out of my distresses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.25.18" /> \begin{signline}Look upon mine affliction and my pain; and forgive all my sins.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.25.19" /> \begin{signline}Consider mine enemies; for they are many; and they hate me with cruel hatred.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.25.20" /> \begin{signline}O keep my soul, and deliver me: let me not be ashamed; for I put my trust in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.25.21" /> \begin{signline}Let integrity and uprightness preserve me; for I wait on thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.25.22" /> \begin{signline}Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his troubles.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="26" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.26.1" /> \begin{signline}Judge me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for I have walked in mine integrity: I have trusted also in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline};\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}therefore\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I shall not slide.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.26.2" /> \begin{signline}Examine me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and prove me; try my reins and my heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.26.3" /> \begin{signline}For thy lovingkindness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before mine eyes: and I have walked in thy truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.26.4" /> \begin{signline}I have not sat with vain persons, neither will I go in with dissemblers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.26.5" /> \begin{signline}I have hated the congregation of evil doers; and will not sit with the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.26.6" /> \begin{signline}I will wash mine hands in innocency: so will I compass thine altar, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.26.7" /> \begin{signline}That I may publish with the voice of thanksgiving, and tell of all thy wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.26.8" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I have loved the habitation of thy house, and the place where thine honour dwelleth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.26.9" /> \begin{signline}Gather not my soul with sinners, nor my life with bloody men:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.26.10" /> \begin{signline}In whose hands\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mischief, and their right hand is full of bribes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.26.11" /> \begin{signline}But as for me, I will walk in mine integrity: redeem me, and be merciful unto me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.26.12" /> \begin{signline}My foot standeth in an even place: in the congregations will I bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="27" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.27.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my light and my salvation; whom shall I fear? the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the strength of my life; of whom shall I be afraid?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.27.2" /> \begin{signline}When the wicked,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine enemies and my foes, came upon me to eat up my flesh, they stumbled and fell.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.27.3" /> \begin{signline}Though an host should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear: though war should rise against me, in this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}will\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}confident.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.27.4" /> \begin{signline}One\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thing\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have I desired of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, that will I seek after; that I may dwell in the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}all the days of my life, to behold the beauty of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and to enquire in his temple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.27.5" /> \begin{signline}For in the time of trouble he shall hide me in his pavilion: in the secret of his tabernacle shall he hide me; he shall set me up upon a rock.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.27.6" /> \begin{signline}And now shall mine head be lifted up above mine enemies round about me: therefore will I offer in his tabernacle sacrifices of joy; I will sing, yea, I will sing praises unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.27.7" /> \begin{signline}Hear, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I cry with my voice: have mercy also upon me, and answer me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.27.8" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}When thou saidst\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, Seek ye my face; my heart said unto thee, Thy face, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, will I seek.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.27.9" /> \begin{signline}Hide not thy face\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}far\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from me; put not thy servant away in anger: thou hast been my help; leave me not, neither forsake me, O God of my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.27.10" /> \begin{signline}When my father and my mother forsake me, then the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will take me up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.27.11" /> \begin{signline}Teach me thy way, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and lead me in a plain path, because of mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.27.12" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me not over unto the will of mine enemies: for false witnesses are risen up against me, and such as breathe out cruelty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.27.13" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}I had fainted\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, unless I had believed to see the goodness of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in the land of the living.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.27.14" /> \begin{signline}Wait on the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: be of good courage, and he shall strengthen thine heart: wait, I say, on the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="28" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.28.1" /> \begin{signline}Unto thee will I cry, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my rock; be not silent to me: lest,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou be silent to me, I become like them that go down into the pit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.28.2" /> \begin{signline}Hear the voice of my supplications, when I cry unto thee, when I lift up my hands toward thy holy oracle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.28.3" /> \begin{signline}Draw me not away with the wicked, and with the workers of iniquity, which speak peace to their neighbours, but mischief\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in their hearts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.28.4" /> \begin{signline}Give them according to their deeds, and according to the wickedness of their endeavours: give them after the work of their hands; render to them their desert.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.28.5" /> \begin{signline}Because they regard not the works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, nor the operation of his hands, he shall destroy them, and not build them up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.28.6" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, because he hath heard the voice of my supplications.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.28.7" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my strength and my shield; my heart trusted in him, and I am helped: therefore my heart greatly rejoiceth; and with my song will I praise him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.28.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their strength, and he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the saving strength of his anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.28.9" /> \begin{signline}Save thy people, and bless thine inheritance: feed them also, and lift them up for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="29" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.29.1" /> \begin{signline}Give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O ye mighty, give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}glory and strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.29.2" /> \begin{signline}Give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the glory due unto his name; worship the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in the beauty of holiness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.29.3" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the waters: the God of glory thundereth: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon many waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.29.4" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}powerful; the voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}full of majesty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.29.5" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}breaketh the cedars; yea, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}breaketh the cedars of Lebanon.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.29.6" /> \begin{signline}He maketh them also to skip like a calf; Lebanon and Sirion like a young unicorn.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.29.7" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}divideth the flames of fire.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.29.8" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shaketh the wilderness; the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shaketh the wilderness of Kadesh.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.29.9" /> \begin{signline}The voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}maketh the hinds to calve, and discovereth the forests: and in his temple doth every one speak of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.29.10" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}sitteth upon the flood; yea, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}sitteth King for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.29.11" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will give strength unto his people; the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will bless his people with peace.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="30" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}at\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}the dedication\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of the house\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.30.1" /> \begin{signline}I will extol thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for thou hast lifted me up, and hast not made my foes to rejoice over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.30.2" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, I cried unto thee, and thou hast healed me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.30.3" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou hast brought up my soul from the grave: thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.30.4" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O ye saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.30.5" /> \begin{signline}For his anger\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a moment; in his favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the morning.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.30.6" /> \begin{signline}And in my prosperity I said, I shall never be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.30.7" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, by thy favour thou hast made my mountain to stand strong: thou didst hide thy face,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I was troubled.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.30.8" /> \begin{signline}I cried to thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}I made supplication.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.30.9" /> \begin{signline}What profit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is there\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in my blood, when I go down to the pit? Shall the dust praise thee? shall it declare thy truth?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.30.10" /> \begin{signline}Hear, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and have mercy upon me:\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, be thou my helper.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.30.11" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast turned for me my mourning into dancing: thou hast put off my sackcloth, and girded me with gladness;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.30.12" />\begin{signline}To the end that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}glory may sing praise to thee, and not be silent. O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, I will give thanks unto thee for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="31" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.31.1" /> \begin{signline}In thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, do I put my trust; let me never be ashamed: deliver me in thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.31.2" /> \begin{signline}Bow down thine ear to me; deliver me speedily: be thou my strong rock, for an house of defence to save me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.31.3" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock and my fortress; therefore for thy name’s sake lead me, and guide me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.31.4" /> \begin{signline}Pull me out of the net that they have laid privily for me: for thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.31.5" /> \begin{signline}Into thine hand I commit my spirit: thou hast redeemed me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.31.6" /> \begin{signline}I have hated them that regard lying vanities: but I trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.31.7" /> \begin{signline}I will be glad and rejoice in thy mercy: for thou hast considered my trouble; thou hast known my soul in adversities;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.31.8" /> \begin{signline}And hast not shut me up into the hand of the enemy: thou hast set my feet in a large room.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.31.9" /> \begin{signline}Have mercy upon me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, for I am in trouble: mine eye is consumed with grief,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, my soul and my belly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.31.10" /> \begin{signline}For my life is spent with grief, and my years with sighing: my strength faileth because of mine iniquity, and my bones are consumed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.31.11" /> \begin{signline}I was a reproach among all mine enemies, but especially among my neighbours, and a fear to mine acquaintance: they that did see me without fled from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.31.12" /> \begin{signline}I am forgotten as a dead man out of mind: I am like a broken vessel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.31.13" /> \begin{signline}For I have heard the slander of many: fear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}on every side: while they took counsel together against me, they devised to take away my life.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.31.14" /> \begin{signline}But I trusted in thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I said, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.31.15" /> \begin{signline}My times\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thy hand: deliver me from the hand of mine enemies, and from them that persecute me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.31.16" /> \begin{signline}Make thy face to shine upon thy servant: save me for thy mercies’ sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.31.17" /> \begin{signline}Let me not be ashamed, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for I have called upon thee: let the wicked be ashamed,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let them be silent in the grave.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.31.18" /> \begin{signline}Let the lying lips be put to silence; which speak grievous things proudly and contemptuously against the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.31.19" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Oh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}how great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy goodness, which thou hast laid up for them that fear thee;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast wrought for them that trust in thee before the sons of men!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.31.20" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt hide them in the secret of thy presence from the pride of man: thou shalt keep them secretly in a pavilion from the strife of tongues.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.31.21" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for he hath shewed me his marvellous kindness in a strong city.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.31.22" /> \begin{signline}For I said in my haste, I am cut off from before thine eyes: nevertheless thou heardest the voice of my supplications when I cried unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.31.23" /> \begin{signline}O love the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all ye his saints:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}preserveth the faithful, and plentifully rewardeth the proud doer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.31.24" /> \begin{signline}Be of good courage, and he shall strengthen your heart, all ye that hope in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="32" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.32.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is he whose\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}transgression\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}forgiven,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whose\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sin\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}covered.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.32.2" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man unto whom the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}imputeth not iniquity, and in whose spirit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no guile.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.32.3" /> \begin{signline}When I kept silence, my bones waxed old through my roaring all the day long.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.32.4" /> \begin{signline}For day and night thy hand was heavy upon me: my moisture is turned into the drought of summer. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.32.5" /> \begin{signline}I acknowledged my sin unto thee, and mine iniquity have I not hid. I said, I will confess my transgressions unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and thou forgavest the iniquity of my sin. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.32.6" /> \begin{signline}For this shall every one that is godly pray unto thee in a time when thou mayest be found: surely in the floods of great waters they shall not come nigh unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.32.7" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my hiding place; thou shalt preserve me from trouble; thou shalt compass me about with songs of deliverance. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.32.8" /> \begin{signline}I will instruct thee and teach thee in the way which thou shalt go: I will guide thee with mine eye.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.32.9" /> \begin{signline}Be ye not as the horse,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the mule,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have no understanding: whose mouth must be held in with bit and bridle, lest they come near unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.32.10" /> \begin{signline}Many sorrows\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the wicked: but he that trusteth in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, mercy shall compass him about.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.32.11" /> \begin{signline}Be glad in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and rejoice, ye righteous: and shout for joy, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="33" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.33.1" /> \begin{signline}Rejoice in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O ye righteous:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}praise is comely for the upright.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.33.2" /> \begin{signline}Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with harp: sing unto him with the psaltery\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an instrument of ten strings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.33.3" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto him a new song; play skilfully with a loud noise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.33.4" /> \begin{signline}For the word of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right; and all his works\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are done\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.33.5" /> \begin{signline}He loveth righteousness and judgment: the earth is full of the goodness of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.33.6" /> \begin{signline}By the word of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}were the heavens made; and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.33.7" /> \begin{signline}He gathereth the waters of the sea together as an heap: he layeth up the depth in storehouses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.33.8" /> \begin{signline}Let all the earth fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.33.9" /> \begin{signline}For he spake, and it was\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}done;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he commanded, and it stood fast.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.33.10" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}bringeth the counsel of the heathen to nought: he maketh the devices of the people of none effect.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.33.11" /> \begin{signline}The counsel of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}standeth for ever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.33.12" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the nation whose God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline};\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he hath chosen for his own inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.33.13" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}looketh from heaven; he beholdeth all the sons of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.33.14" /> \begin{signline}From the place of his habitation he looketh upon all the inhabitants of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.33.15" /> \begin{signline}He fashioneth their hearts alike; he considereth all their works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.33.16" /> \begin{signline}There is no king saved by the multitude of an host: a mighty man is not delivered by much strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.33.17" /> \begin{signline}An horse\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a vain thing for safety: neither shall he deliver\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}by his great strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.33.18" /> \begin{signline}Behold, the eye of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon them that fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.33.19" /> \begin{signline}To deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.33.20" /> \begin{signline}Our soul waiteth for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our help and our shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.33.21" /> \begin{signline}For our heart shall rejoice in him, because we have trusted in his holy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.33.22" /> \begin{signline}Let thy mercy, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, be upon us, according as we hope in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="34" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he changed\end{signline}
\begin{signline}his behaviour\end{signline}
\begin{signline}before\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Abimelech;\end{signline}
\begin{signline}who drove him away,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and he departed.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.34.1" /> \begin{signline}I will bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}at all times: his praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.34.2" /> \begin{signline}My soul shall make her boast in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: the humble shall hear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereof\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and be glad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.34.3" /> \begin{signline}O magnify the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with me, and let us exalt his name together.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.34.4" /> \begin{signline}I sought the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he heard me, and delivered me from all my fears.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.34.5" /> \begin{signline}They looked unto him, and were lightened: and their faces were not ashamed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.34.6" /> \begin{signline}This poor man cried, and the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}heard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and saved him out of all his troubles.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.34.7" /> \begin{signline}The angel of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}encampeth round about them that fear him, and delivereth them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.34.8" /> \begin{signline}O taste and see that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}trusteth in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.34.9" /> \begin{signline}O fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, ye his saints: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no want to them that fear him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.34.10" /> \begin{signline}The young lions do lack, and suffer hunger: but they that seek the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall not want any good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thing\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.34.11" /> \begin{signline}Come, ye children, hearken unto me: I will teach you the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.34.12" /> \begin{signline}What man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is he that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}desireth life,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}loveth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}many\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}days, that he may see good?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.34.13" /> \begin{signline}Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.34.14" /> \begin{signline}Depart from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.34.15" /> \begin{signline}The eyes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the righteous, and his ears\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are open\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto their cry.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.34.16" /> \begin{signline}The face of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against them that do evil, to cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.34.17" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}The righteous\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cry, and the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}heareth, and delivereth them out of all their troubles.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.34.18" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nigh unto them that are of a broken heart; and saveth such as be of a contrite spirit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.34.19" /> \begin{signline}Many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the afflictions of the righteous: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}delivereth him out of them all.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.34.20" /> \begin{signline}He keepeth all his bones: not one of them is broken.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.34.21" /> \begin{signline}Evil shall slay the wicked: and they that hate the righteous shall be desolate.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.34.22" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}redeemeth the soul of his servants: and none of them that trust in him shall be desolate.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="35" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.35.1" /> \begin{signline}Plead\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my cause\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, with them that strive with me: fight against them that fight against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.35.2" /> \begin{signline}Take hold of shield and buckler, and stand up for mine help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.35.3" /> \begin{signline}Draw out also the spear, and stop\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the way\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against them that persecute me: say unto my soul, I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.35.4" /> \begin{signline}Let them be confounded and put to shame that seek after my soul: let them be turned back and brought to confusion that devise my hurt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.35.5" /> \begin{signline}Let them be as chaff before the wind: and let the angel of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}chase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.35.6" /> \begin{signline}Let their way be dark and slippery: and let the angel of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}persecute them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.35.7" /> \begin{signline}For without cause have they hid for me their net\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a pit,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}without cause they have digged for my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.35.8" /> \begin{signline}Let destruction come upon him at unawares; and let his net that he hath hid catch himself: into that very destruction let him fall.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.35.9" /> \begin{signline}And my soul shall be joyful in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: it shall rejoice in his salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.35.10" /> \begin{signline}All my bones shall say, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like unto thee, which deliverest the poor from him that is too strong for him, yea, the poor and the needy from him that spoileth him?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.35.11" /> \begin{signline}False witnesses did rise up; they laid to my charge\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that I knew not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.35.12" /> \begin{signline}They rewarded me evil for good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the spoiling of my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.35.13" /> \begin{signline}But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sackcloth: I humbled my soul with fasting; and my prayer returned into mine own bosom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.35.14" /> \begin{signline}I behaved myself as though\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he had been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my friend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}brother: I bowed down heavily, as one that mourneth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mother.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.35.15" /> \begin{signline}But in mine adversity they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, the abjects gathered themselves together against me, and I knew\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not; they did tear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and ceased not:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.35.16" /> \begin{signline}With hypocritical mockers in feasts, they gnashed upon me with their teeth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.35.17" /> \begin{signline}Lord, how long wilt thou look on? rescue my soul from their destructions, my darling from the lions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.35.18" /> \begin{signline}I will give thee thanks in the great congregation: I will praise thee among much people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.35.19" /> \begin{signline}Let not them that are mine enemies wrongfully rejoice  over me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}neither\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let them wink with the eye that hate me without a cause.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.35.20" /> \begin{signline}For they speak not peace: but they devise deceitful matters against\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}quiet in the land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.35.21" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they opened their mouth wide against me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}said, Aha, aha, our eye hath seen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.35.22" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}This\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast seen, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: keep not silence: O Lord, be not far from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.35.23" /> \begin{signline}Stir up thyself, and awake to my judgment,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto my cause, my God and my Lord.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.35.24" /> \begin{signline}Judge me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, according to thy righteousness; and let them not rejoice over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.35.25" /> \begin{signline}Let them not say in their hearts, Ah, so would we have it: let them not say, We have swallowed him up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.35.26" /> \begin{signline}Let them be ashamed and brought to confusion together that rejoice at mine hurt: let them be clothed with shame and dishonour that magnify\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}themselves\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.35.27" /> \begin{signline}Let them shout for joy, and be glad, that favour my righteous cause: yea, let them say continually, Let the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}be magnified, which hath pleasure in the prosperity of his servant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.35.28" /> \begin{signline}And my tongue shall speak of thy righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of thy praise all the day long.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="36" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the servant\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.36.1" /> \begin{signline}The transgression of the wicked saith within my heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no fear of God before his eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.36.2" /> \begin{signline}For he flattereth himself in his own eyes, until his iniquity be found to be hateful.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.36.3" /> \begin{signline}The words of his mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}iniquity and deceit: he hath left off to be wise,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to do good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.36.4" /> \begin{signline}He deviseth mischief upon his bed; he setteth himself in a way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good; he abhorreth not evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.36.5" /> \begin{signline}Thy mercy, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the heavens;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy faithfulness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}reacheth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the clouds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.36.6" /> \begin{signline}Thy righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the great mountains; thy judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a great deep: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou preservest man and beast.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.36.7" /> \begin{signline}How excellent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy lovingkindness, O God! therefore the children of men put their trust under the shadow of thy wings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.36.8" /> \begin{signline}They shall be abundantly satisfied with the fatness of thy house; and thou shalt make them drink of the river of thy pleasures.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.36.9" />\begin{signline}For with thee\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the fountain of life: in thy light shall we see light.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.36.10" /> \begin{signline}O continue thy lovingkindness unto them that know thee; and thy righteousness to the upright in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.36.11" /> \begin{signline}Let not the foot of pride come against me, and let not the hand of the wicked remove me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.36.12" /> \begin{signline}There are the workers of iniquity fallen: they are cast down, and shall not be able to rise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="37" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.37.1" /> \begin{signline}Fret not thyself because of evildoers, neither be thou envious against the workers of iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.37.2" /> \begin{signline}For they shall soon be cut down like the grass, and wither as the green herb.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.37.3" /> \begin{signline}Trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and do good;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shalt thou dwell in the land, and verily thou shalt be fed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.37.4" /> \begin{signline}Delight thyself also in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and he shall give thee the desires of thine heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.37.5" /> \begin{signline}Commit thy way unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; trust also in him; and he shall bring\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to pass.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.37.6" /> \begin{signline}And he shall bring forth thy righteousness as the light, and thy judgment as the noonday.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.37.7" /> \begin{signline}Rest in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and wait patiently for him: fret not thyself because of him who prospereth in his way, because of the man who bringeth wicked devices to pass.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.37.8" /> \begin{signline}Cease from anger, and forsake wrath: fret not thyself in any wise to do evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.37.9" /> \begin{signline}For evildoers shall be cut off: but those that wait upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, they shall inherit the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.37.10" /> \begin{signline}For yet a little while, and the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}yea, thou shalt diligently consider his place, and it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.37.11" /> \begin{signline}But the meek shall inherit the earth; and shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.37.12" /> \begin{signline}The wicked plotteth against the just, and gnasheth upon him with his teeth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.37.13" /> \begin{signline}The Lord shall laugh at him: for he seeth that his day is coming.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.37.14" /> \begin{signline}The wicked have drawn out the sword, and have bent their bow, to cast down the poor and needy,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to slay such as be of upright conversation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.37.15" /> \begin{signline}Their sword shall enter into their own heart, and their bows shall be broken.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.37.16" /> \begin{signline}A little that a righteous man hath\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than the riches of many wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.37.17" /> \begin{signline}For the arms of the wicked shall be broken: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}upholdeth the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.37.18" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}knoweth the days of the upright: and their inheritance shall be for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.37.19" /> \begin{signline}They shall not be ashamed in the evil time: and in the days of famine they shall be satisfied.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.37.20" /> \begin{signline}But the wicked shall perish, and the enemies of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the fat of lambs: they shall consume; into smoke shall they consume away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.37.21" /> \begin{signline}The wicked borroweth, and payeth not again: but the righteous sheweth mercy, and giveth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.37.22" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}such as be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blessed of him shall inherit the earth; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they that be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cursed of him shall be cut off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.37.23" /> \begin{signline}The steps of a\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}good\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man are ordered by the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: and he delighteth in his way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.37.24" /> \begin{signline}Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down: for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}upholdeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.37.25" /> \begin{signline}I have been young, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}now\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}am old; yet have I not seen the righteous forsaken, nor his seed begging bread.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.37.26" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ever merciful, and lendeth; and his seed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blessed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.37.27" /> \begin{signline}Depart from evil, and do good; and dwell for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.37.28" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}loveth judgment, and forsaketh not his saints; they are preserved for ever: but the seed of the wicked shall be cut off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.37.29" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall inherit the land, and dwell therein for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.37.30" /> \begin{signline}The mouth of the righteous speaketh wisdom, and his tongue talketh of judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.37.31" /> \begin{signline}The law of his God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his heart; none of his steps shall slide.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.37.32" /> \begin{signline}The wicked watcheth the righteous, and seeketh to slay him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.37.33" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will not leave him in his hand, nor condemn him when he is judged.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.37.34" /> \begin{signline}Wait on the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and keep his way, and he shall exalt thee to inherit the land: when the wicked are cut off, thou shalt see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.37.35" /> \begin{signline}I have seen the wicked in great power, and spreading himself like a green bay tree.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.37.36" /> \begin{signline}Yet he passed away, and, lo, he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not: yea, I sought him, but he could not be found.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.37.37" /> \begin{signline}Mark the perfect\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and behold the upright: for the end of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.37.38" /> \begin{signline}But the transgressors shall be destroyed together: the end of the wicked shall be cut off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.37.39" /> \begin{signline}But the salvation of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their strength in the time of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.37.40" /> \begin{signline}And the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall help them, and deliver them: he shall deliver them from the wicked, and save them, because they trust in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="38" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to bring to remembrance.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.38.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, rebuke me not in thy wrath: neither chasten me in thy hot displeasure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.38.2" /> \begin{signline}For thine arrows stick fast in me, and thy hand presseth me sore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.38.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no soundness in my flesh because of thine anger; neither\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is there any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}rest in my bones because of my sin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.38.4" /> \begin{signline}For mine iniquities are gone over mine head: as an heavy burden they are too heavy for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.38.5" /> \begin{signline}My wounds stink\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}are corrupt because of my foolishness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.38.6" /> \begin{signline}I am troubled; I am bowed down greatly; I go mourning all the day long.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.38.7" /> \begin{signline}For my loins are filled with a loathsome\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}disease:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no soundness in my flesh.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.38.8" /> \begin{signline}I am feeble and sore broken: I have roared by reason of the disquietness of my heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.38.9" /> \begin{signline}Lord, all my desire\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before thee; and my groaning is not hid from thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.38.10" /> \begin{signline}My heart panteth, my strength faileth me: as for the light of mine eyes, it also is gone from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.38.11" /> \begin{signline}My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my sore; and my kinsmen stand  afar off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.38.12" /> \begin{signline}They also that seek after my life lay snares\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for me:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and they that seek my hurt speak mischievous things, and imagine deceits all the day long.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.38.13" /> \begin{signline}But I, as a deaf\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, heard not; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}I was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a dumb man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}openeth not his mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.38.14" /> \begin{signline}Thus I was as a man that heareth not, and in whose mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no reproofs.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.38.15" /> \begin{signline}For in thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, do I hope: thou wilt hear, O Lord my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.38.16" /> \begin{signline}For I said,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}Hear me\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, lest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}otherwise\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they should rejoice over me: when my foot slippeth, they magnify\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}themselves\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.38.17" />\begin{signline}For I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ready to halt, and my sorrow\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually before me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.38.18" /> \begin{signline}For I will declare mine iniquity; I will be sorry for my sin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.38.19" /> \begin{signline}But mine enemies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lively,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they are strong: and they that hate me wrongfully are multiplied.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.38.20" /> \begin{signline}They also that render evil for good are mine adversaries; because I follow\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the thing that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.38.21" /> \begin{signline}Forsake me not, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: O my God, be not far from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.38.22" /> \begin{signline}Make haste to help me, O Lord my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="39" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}to Jeduthun,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.39.1" /> \begin{signline}I said, I will take heed to my ways, that I sin not with my tongue: I will keep my mouth with a bridle, while the wicked is before me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.39.2" /> \begin{signline}I was dumb with silence, I held my peace,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from good; and my sorrow was stirred.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.39.3" /> \begin{signline}My heart was hot within me, while I was musing the fire burned:\end{signline} <add> \begin{signline}then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}spake I with my tongue,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.39.4" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, make me to know mine end, and the measure of my days, what it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is; that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I may know how frail I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.39.5" /> \begin{signline}Behold, thou hast made my days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an handbreadth; and mine age\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as nothing before thee: verily every man at his best state\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}altogether vanity. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.39.6" /> \begin{signline}Surely every man walketh in a vain shew: surely they are disquieted in vain: he heapeth up\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}riches\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and knoweth not who shall gather them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.39.7" /> \begin{signline}And now, Lord, what wait I for? my hope\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.39.8" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me from all my transgressions: make me not the reproach of the foolish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.39.9" /> \begin{signline}I was dumb, I opened not my mouth; because thou didst\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.39.10" /> \begin{signline}Remove thy stroke away from me: I am consumed by the blow of thine hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.39.11" /> \begin{signline}When thou with rebukes dost correct man for iniquity, thou makest his beauty to consume away like a moth: surely every man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vanity. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.39.12" /> \begin{signline}Hear my prayer, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and give ear unto my cry; hold not thy peace at my tears: for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a stranger with thee,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a sojourner, as all my fathers\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.39.13" /> \begin{signline}O spare me, that I may recover strength, before I go hence, and be no more.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="40" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.40.1" /> \begin{signline}I waited patiently for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and he inclined unto me, and heard my cry.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.40.2" /> \begin{signline}He brought me up also out of an horrible pit, out of the miry clay, and set my feet upon a rock,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}established my goings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.40.3" /> \begin{signline}And he hath put a new song in my mouth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}praise unto our God: many shall see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and fear, and shall trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.40.4" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that man that maketh the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}his trust, and respecteth not the proud, nor such as turn aside to lies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.40.5" /> \begin{signline}Many, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy wonderful works\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast done, and thy thoughts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to us-ward: they cannot be reckoned up in order unto thee:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I would declare and speak\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, they are more than can be numbered.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.40.6" /> \begin{signline}Sacrifice and offering thou didst not desire; mine ears hast thou opened: burnt offering and sin offering hast thou not required.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.40.7" /> \begin{signline}Then said I, Lo, I come: in the volume of the book\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}written of me,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.40.8" /> \begin{signline}I delight to do thy will, O my God: yea, thy law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}within my heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.40.9" /> \begin{signline}I have preached righteousness in the great congregation: lo, I have not refrained my lips, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou knowest.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.40.10" /> \begin{signline}I have not hid thy righteousness within my heart; I have declared thy faithfulness and thy salvation: I have not concealed thy lovingkindness and thy truth from the great congregation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.40.11" /> \begin{signline}Withhold not thou thy tender mercies from me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: let thy lovingkindness and thy truth continually preserve me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.40.12" /> \begin{signline}For innumerable evils have compassed me about: mine iniquities have taken hold upon me, so that I am not able to look up; they are more than the hairs of mine head: therefore my heart faileth me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.40.13" /> \begin{signline}Be pleased, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, to deliver me: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, make haste to help me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.40.14" /> \begin{signline}Let them be ashamed and confounded together that seek after my soul to destroy it; let them be driven backward and put to shame that wish me evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.40.15" /> \begin{signline}Let them be desolate for a reward of their shame that say unto me, Aha, aha.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.40.16" /> \begin{signline}Let all those that seek thee rejoice and be glad in thee: let such as love thy salvation say continually, The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}be magnified.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.40.17" />\begin{signline}But I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor and needy;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the Lord thinketh upon me: thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my help and my deliverer; make no tarrying, O my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="41" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.41.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that considereth the poor: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will deliver him in time of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.41.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will preserve him, and keep him alive;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he shall be blessed upon the earth: and thou wilt not deliver him unto the will of his enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.41.3" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will strengthen him upon the bed of languishing: thou wilt make all his bed in his sickness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.41.4" /> \begin{signline}I said, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, be merciful unto me: heal my soul; for I have sinned against thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.41.5" /> \begin{signline}Mine enemies speak evil of me, When shall he die, and his name perish?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.41.6" /> \begin{signline}And if he come to see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, he speaketh vanity: his heart gathereth iniquity to itself;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he goeth abroad, he telleth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.41.7" /> \begin{signline}All that hate me whisper together against me: against me do they devise my hurt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.41.8" /> \begin{signline}An evil disease,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}say they\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, cleaveth fast unto him: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}now\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that he lieth he shall rise up no more.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.41.9" /> \begin{signline}Yea, mine own familiar friend, in whom I trusted, which did eat of my bread, hath lifted up\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}heel against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.41.10" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, be merciful unto me, and raise me up, that I may requite them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.41.11" /> \begin{signline}By this I know that thou favourest me, because mine enemy doth not triumph over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.41.12" /> \begin{signline}And as for me, thou upholdest me in mine integrity, and settest me before thy face for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.41.13" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of Israel from everlasting, and to everlasting. Amen, and Amen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="42" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.42.1" /> \begin{signline}As the hart panteth after the water brooks, so panteth my soul after thee, O God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.42.2" /> \begin{signline}My soul thirsteth for God, for the living God: when shall I come and appear before God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.42.3" /> \begin{signline}My tears have been my meat day and night, while they continually say unto me, Where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.42.4" /> \begin{signline}When I remember these\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, I pour out my soul in me: for I had gone with the multitude, I went with them to the house of God, with the voice of joy and praise, with a multitude that kept holyday.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.42.5" /> \begin{signline}Why art thou cast down, O my soul? and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}why\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}art thou disquieted in me? hope thou in God: for I shall yet praise him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the help of his countenance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.42.6" /> \begin{signline}O my God, my soul is cast down within me: therefore will I remember thee from the land of Jordan, and of the Hermonites, from the hill Mizar.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.42.7" /> \begin{signline}Deep calleth unto deep at the noise of thy waterspouts: all thy waves and thy billows are gone over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.42.8" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will command his lovingkindness in the daytime, and in the night his song\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my prayer unto the God of my life.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.42.9" /> \begin{signline}I will say unto God my rock, Why hast thou forgotten me? why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.42.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with a sword in my bones, mine enemies reproach me; while they say daily unto me, Where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.42.11" /> \begin{signline}Why art thou cast down, O my soul? and why art thou disquieted within me? hope thou in God: for I shall yet praise him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the health of my countenance, and my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="43" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.43.1" /> \begin{signline}Judge me, O God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation: O deliver me from the deceitful and unjust man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.43.2" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of my strength: why dost thou cast me off? why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.43.3" /> \begin{signline}O send out thy light and thy truth: let them lead me; let them bring me unto thy holy hill, and to thy tabernacles.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.43.4" /> \begin{signline}Then will I go unto the altar of God, unto God my exceeding joy: yea, upon the harp will I praise thee, O God my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.43.5" /> \begin{signline}Why art thou cast down, O my soul? and why art thou disquieted within me? hope in God: for I shall yet praise him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the health of my countenance, and my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="44" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.44.1" /> \begin{signline}We have heard with our ears, O God, our fathers have told us,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}what\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}work thou didst in their days, in the times of old.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.44.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}How\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou didst drive out the heathen with thy hand, and plantedst them;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}how\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou didst afflict the people, and cast them out.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.44.3" /> \begin{signline}For they got not the land in possession by their own sword, neither did their own arm save them: but thy right hand, and thine arm, and the light of thy countenance, because thou hadst a favour unto them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.44.4" /> \begin{signline}Thou art my King, O God: command deliverances for Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.44.5" /> \begin{signline}Through thee will we push down our enemies: through thy name will we tread them under that rise up against us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.44.6" /> \begin{signline}For I will not trust in my bow, neither shall my sword save me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.44.7" /> \begin{signline}But thou hast saved us from our enemies, and hast put them to shame that hated us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.44.8" /> \begin{signline}In God we boast all the day long, and praise thy name for ever. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.44.9" /> \begin{signline}But thou hast cast off, and put us to shame; and goest not forth with our armies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.44.10" /> \begin{signline}Thou makest us to turn back from the enemy: and they which hate us spoil for themselves.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.44.11" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast given us like sheep\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}appointed\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for meat; and hast scattered us among the heathen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.44.12" /> \begin{signline}Thou sellest thy people for nought, and dost not increase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy wealth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}by their price.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.44.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou makest us a reproach to our neighbours, a scorn and a derision to them that are round about us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.44.14" /> \begin{signline}Thou makest us a byword among the heathen, a shaking of the head among the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.44.15" /> \begin{signline}My confusion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually before me, and the shame of my face hath covered me,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.44.16" /> \begin{signline}For the voice of him that reproacheth and blasphemeth; by reason of the enemy and avenger.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.44.17" /> \begin{signline}All this is come upon us; yet have we not forgotten thee, neither have we dealt falsely in thy covenant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.44.18" /> \begin{signline}Our heart is not turned back, neither have our steps declined from thy way;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.44.19" /> \begin{signline}Though thou hast sore broken us in the place of dragons, and covered us with the shadow of death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.44.20" /> \begin{signline}If we have forgotten the name of our God, or stretched out our hands to a strange god;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.44.21" /> \begin{signline}Shall not God search this out? for he knoweth the secrets of the heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.44.22" /> \begin{signline}Yea, for thy sake are we killed all the day long; we are counted as sheep for the slaughter.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.44.23" /> \begin{signline}Awake, why sleepest thou, O Lord? arise, cast\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not off for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.44.24" /> \begin{signline}Wherefore hidest thou thy face,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}forgettest our affliction and our oppression?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.44.25" /> \begin{signline}For our soul is bowed down to the dust: our belly cleaveth unto the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.44.26" /> \begin{signline}Arise for our help, and redeem us for thy mercies’ sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="45" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Shoshannim,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of loves.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.45.1" /> \begin{signline}My heart is inditing a good matter: I speak of the things which I have made touching the king: my tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the pen of a ready writer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.45.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou art fairer than the children of men: grace is poured into thy lips: therefore God hath blessed thee for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.45.3" /> \begin{signline}Gird thy sword upon\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thigh, O\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}most\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.45.4" /> \begin{signline}And in thy majesty ride prosperously because of truth and meekness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteousness; and thy right hand shall teach thee terrible things.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.45.5" /> \begin{signline}Thine arrows\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sharp in the heart of the king’s enemies;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whereby\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the people fall under thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.45.6" /> \begin{signline}Thy throne, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever and ever: the sceptre of thy kingdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a right sceptre.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.45.7" /> \begin{signline}Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest wickedness: therefore God, thy God, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness above thy fellows.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.45.8" /> \begin{signline}All thy garments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}smell\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of myrrh, and aloes,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cassia, out of the ivory palaces, whereby they have made thee glad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.45.9" /> \begin{signline}Kings’ daughters\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among thy honourable women: upon thy right hand did stand the queen in gold of Ophir.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.45.10" /> \begin{signline}Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline thine ear; forget also thine own people, and thy father’s house;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.45.11" /> \begin{signline}So shall the king greatly desire thy beauty: for he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy Lord; and worship thou him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.45.12" /> \begin{signline}And the daughter of Tyre\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be there\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with a gift;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rich among the people shall intreat thy favour.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.45.13" /> \begin{signline}The king’s daughter\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all glorious within: her clothing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of wrought gold.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.45.14" /> \begin{signline}She shall be brought unto the king in raiment of needlework: the virgins her companions that follow her shall be brought unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.45.15" /> \begin{signline}With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought: they shall enter into the king’s palace.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.45.16" /> \begin{signline}Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children, whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.45.17" /> \begin{signline}I will make thy name to be remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise thee for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="46" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Alamoth.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.46.1" /> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.46.2" /> \begin{signline}Therefore will not we fear, though the earth be removed, and though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.46.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Though\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the waters thereof roar\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}be troubled,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}though\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.46.4" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a river, the streams whereof shall make glad the city of God, the holy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}place\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the tabernacles of the most High.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.46.5" /> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the midst of her; she shall not be moved: God shall help her,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right early.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.46.6" /> \begin{signline}The heathen raged, the kingdoms were moved: he uttered his voice, the earth melted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.46.7" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with us; the God of Jacob\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our refuge. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.46.8" /> \begin{signline}Come, behold the works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, what desolations he hath made in the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.46.9" /> \begin{signline}He maketh wars to cease unto the end of the earth; he breaketh the bow, and cutteth the spear in sunder; he burneth the chariot in the fire.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.46.10" /> \begin{signline}Be still, and know that I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.46.11" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with us; the God of Jacob\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our refuge. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="47" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.47.1" /> \begin{signline}O clap your hands, all ye people; shout unto God with the voice of triumph.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.47.2" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}most high\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a great King over all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.47.3" /> \begin{signline}He shall subdue the people under us, and the nations under our feet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.47.4" /> \begin{signline}He shall choose our inheritance for us, the excellency of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.47.5" /> \begin{signline}God is gone up with a shout, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with the sound of a trumpet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.47.6" /> \begin{signline}Sing praises to God, sing praises: sing praises unto our King, sing praises.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.47.7" /> \begin{signline}For God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the King of all the earth: sing ye praises with understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.47.8" /> \begin{signline}God reigneth over the heathen: God sitteth upon the throne of his holiness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.47.9" /> \begin{signline}The princes of the people are gathered together,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the people of the God of Abraham: for the shields of the earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belong\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto God: he is greatly exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="48" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.48.1" /> \begin{signline}Great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and greatly to be praised in the city of our God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the mountain of his holiness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.48.2" /> \begin{signline}Beautiful for situation, the joy of the whole earth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mount Zion,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}on\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sides of the north, the city of the great King.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.48.3" /> \begin{signline}God is known in her palaces for a refuge.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.48.4" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, the kings were assembled, they passed by together.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.48.5" /> \begin{signline}They saw\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it, and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}so they marvelled; they were troubled,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hasted away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.48.6" /> \begin{signline}Fear took hold upon them there,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pain, as of a woman in travail.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.48.7" /> \begin{signline}Thou breakest the ships of Tarshish with an east wind.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.48.8" /> \begin{signline}As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts, in the city of our God: God will establish it for ever. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.48.9" /> \begin{signline}We have thought of thy lovingkindness, O God, in the midst of thy temple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.48.10" /> \begin{signline}According to thy name, O God, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy praise unto the ends of the earth: thy right hand is full of righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.48.11" /> \begin{signline}Let mount Zion rejoice, let the daughters of Judah be glad, because of thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.48.12" /> \begin{signline}Walk about Zion, and go round about her: tell the towers thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.48.13" /> \begin{signline}Mark ye well her bulwarks, consider her palaces; that ye may tell\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the generation following.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.48.14" /> \begin{signline}For this God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our God for ever and ever: he will be our guide\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="49" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.49.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear this, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}people; give ear, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}inhabitants of the world:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.49.2" /> \begin{signline}Both low and high, rich and poor, together.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.49.3" /> \begin{signline}My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.49.4" /> \begin{signline}I will incline mine ear to a parable: I will open my dark saying upon the harp.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.49.5" /> \begin{signline}Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.49.6" /> \begin{signline}They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.49.7" />\begin{signline}None\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.49.8" />\begin{signline}(For the redemption of their soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}precious, and it ceaseth for ever:)\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.49.9" /> \begin{signline}That he should still live for ever,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not see corruption.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.49.10" /> \begin{signline}For he seeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise men die, likewise the fool and the brutish person perish, and leave their wealth to others.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.49.11" /> \begin{signline}Their inward thought\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is, that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their houses\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall continue\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their dwelling places to all generations; they call\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lands after their own names.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.49.12" /> \begin{signline}Nevertheless man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in honour abideth not: he is like the beasts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.49.13" /> \begin{signline}This their way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.49.14" /> \begin{signline}Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.49.15" /> \begin{signline}But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.49.16" /> \begin{signline}Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.49.17" /> \begin{signline}For when he dieth he shall carry nothing away: his glory shall not descend after him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.49.18" /> \begin{signline}Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.49.19" /> \begin{signline}He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.49.20" /> \begin{signline}Man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in honour, and understandeth not, is like the beasts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="50" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.50.1" /> \begin{signline}The mighty God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hath spoken, and called the earth from the rising of the sun unto the going down thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.50.2" /> \begin{signline}Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God hath shined.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.50.3" /> \begin{signline}Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.50.4" /> \begin{signline}He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.50.5" /> \begin{signline}Gather my saints together unto me; those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.50.6" /> \begin{signline}And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}judge himself. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.50.7" /> \begin{signline}Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.50.8" /> \begin{signline}I will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices or thy burnt offerings,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to have been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually before me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.50.9" /> \begin{signline}I will take no bullock out of thy house,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he goats out of thy folds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.50.10" /> \begin{signline}For every beast of the forest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the cattle upon a thousand hills.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.50.11" /> \begin{signline}I know all the fowls of the mountains: and the wild beasts of the field\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.50.12" /> \begin{signline}If I were hungry, I would not tell thee: for the world\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine, and the fulness thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.50.13" /> \begin{signline}Will I eat the flesh of bulls, or drink the blood of goats?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.50.14" /> \begin{signline}Offer unto God thanksgiving; and pay thy vows unto the most High:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.50.15" /> \begin{signline}And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt glorify me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.50.16" /> \begin{signline}But unto the wicked God saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, or\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.50.17" /> \begin{signline}Seeing thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.50.18" /> \begin{signline}When thou sawest a thief, then thou consentedst with him, and hast been partaker with adulterers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.50.19" /> \begin{signline}Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue frameth  deceit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.50.20" /> \begin{signline}Thou sittest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speakest against thy brother; thou slanderest thine own mother’s son.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.50.21" />\begin{signline}These\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hast thou done, and I kept silence; thou thoughtest that I was altogether\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}such an one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as thyself:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I will reprove thee, and set\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in order before thine eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.50.22" /> \begin{signline}Now consider this, ye that forget God, lest I tear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}you\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in pieces, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to deliver.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.50.23" /> \begin{signline}Whoso offereth praise glorifieth  me: and to him that ordereth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}conversation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}aright\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will I shew the salvation of God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="51" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when Nathan\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the prophet\end{signline}
\begin{signline}came\end{signline}
\begin{signline}unto him, after he had gone in\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to Bath-sheba.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.51.1" /> \begin{signline}Have mercy upon me, O God, according to thy lovingkindness: according unto the multitude of thy tender mercies blot out my transgressions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.51.2" /> \begin{signline}Wash me throughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.51.3" /> \begin{signline}For I acknowledge my transgressions: and my sin\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ever before me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.51.4" /> \begin{signline}Against thee, thee only, have I sinned, and done\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}evil in thy sight: that thou mightest be justified when thou speakest,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}be clear when thou judgest.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.51.5" /> \begin{signline}Behold, I was shapen in iniquity; and in sin did my mother conceive me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.51.6" /> \begin{signline}Behold, thou desirest truth in the inward parts: and in the hidden\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}part\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou shalt make me to know wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.51.7" /> \begin{signline}Purge me with hyssop, and I shall be clean: wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.51.8" /> \begin{signline}Make me to hear joy and gladness;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the bones\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast broken may rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.51.9" /> \begin{signline}Hide thy face from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.51.10" /> \begin{signline}Create in me a clean heart, O God; and renew a right spirit within me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.51.11" /> \begin{signline}Cast me not away from thy presence; and take not thy holy spirit from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.51.12" /> \begin{signline}Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation; and uphold me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}free spirit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.51.13" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will I teach transgressors thy ways; and sinners shall be converted unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.51.14" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, thou God of my salvation:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my tongue shall sing aloud of thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.51.15" /> \begin{signline}O Lord, open thou my lips; and my mouth shall shew forth thy praise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.51.16" /> \begin{signline}For thou desirest not sacrifice; else would I give\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou delightest not in burnt offering.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.51.17" /> \begin{signline}The sacrifices of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a broken spirit: a broken and a contrite heart, O God, thou wilt not despise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.51.18" /> \begin{signline}Do good in thy good pleasure unto Zion: build thou the walls of Jerusalem.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.51.19" /> \begin{signline}Then shalt thou be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness, with burnt offering and whole burnt offering: then shall they offer bullocks upon thine altar.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="52" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when Doeg\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the Edomite\end{signline}
\begin{signline}came\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and told\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Saul,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and said\end{signline}
\begin{signline}unto him, David\end{signline}
\begin{signline}is come\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to the house\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Ahimelech.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.52.1" /> \begin{signline}Why boastest thou thyself in mischief, O mighty man? the goodness of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.52.2" /> \begin{signline}Thy tongue deviseth mischiefs; like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.52.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou lovest evil more than good;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lying rather than to speak righteousness. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.52.4" /> \begin{signline}Thou lovest all devouring words, O\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceitful tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.52.5" /> \begin{signline}God shall likewise destroy thee for ever, he shall take thee away, and pluck thee out of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dwelling place, and root thee out of the land of the living. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.52.6" /> \begin{signline}The righteous also shall see, and fear, and shall laugh at him:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.52.7" />\begin{signline}Lo,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}made not God his strength; but trusted in the abundance of his riches,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strengthened  himself in his wickedness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.52.8" />\begin{signline}But I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like a green olive tree in the house of God: I trust in the mercy of God for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.52.9" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee for ever, because thou hast done\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and I will wait on thy name; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good before thy saints.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="53" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Mahalath,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.53.1" /> \begin{signline}The fool hath said in his heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no God. Corrupt are they, and have done abominable iniquity:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none that doeth good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.53.2" /> \begin{signline}God looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that did understand, that did seek God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.53.3" /> \begin{signline}Every one of them is gone back: they are altogether become filthy;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none that doeth good, no, not one.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.53.4" /> \begin{signline}Have the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they eat bread: they have not called upon God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.53.5" /> \begin{signline}There were they in great fear,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}where\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no fear was: for God hath scattered the bones of him that encampeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}against\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thee: thou hast put\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to shame, because God hath despised them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.53.6" /> \begin{signline}Oh that the salvation of Israel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were come\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}out of Zion! When God bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Israel shall be glad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="54" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when the Ziphims\end{signline}
\begin{signline}came\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and said\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to Saul,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Doth not David\end{signline}
\begin{signline}hide himself with us?\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.54.1" /> \begin{signline}Save me, O God, by thy name, and judge me by thy strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.54.2" /> \begin{signline}Hear my prayer, O God; give ear to the words of my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.54.3" /> \begin{signline}For strangers are risen up against me, and oppressors seek after my soul: they have not set God before them. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.54.4" /> \begin{signline}Behold, God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine helper: the Lord\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with them that uphold my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.54.5" /> \begin{signline}He shall reward evil unto mine enemies: cut them off in thy truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.54.6" /> \begin{signline}I will freely sacrifice unto thee: I will praise thy name, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.54.7" /> \begin{signline}For he hath delivered me out of all trouble: and mine eye hath seen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="55" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.55.1" /> \begin{signline}Give ear to my prayer, O God; and hide not thyself from my supplication.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.55.2" /> \begin{signline}Attend unto me, and hear me: I mourn in my complaint, and make a noise;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.55.3" /> \begin{signline}Because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked: for they cast iniquity upon me, and in wrath they hate me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.55.4" /> \begin{signline}My heart is sore pained within me: and the terrors of death are fallen upon me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.55.5" /> \begin{signline}Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and horror hath overwhelmed me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.55.6" /> \begin{signline}And I said, Oh that I had wings like a dove!\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would I fly away, and be at rest.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.55.7" />\begin{signline}Lo,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would I wander far off,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}remain in the wilderness. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.55.8" /> \begin{signline}I would hasten my escape from the windy storm\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}tempest.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.55.9" /> \begin{signline}Destroy, O Lord,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}divide their tongues: for I have seen violence and strife in the city.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.55.10" /> \begin{signline}Day and night they go about it upon the walls thereof: mischief also and sorrow\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the midst of it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.55.11" /> \begin{signline}Wickedness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the midst thereof: deceit and guile depart not from her streets.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.55.12" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not an enemy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}reproached me; then I could have borne\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}neither\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that hated me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}did magnify\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}himself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me; then I would have hid myself from him:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.55.13" />\begin{signline}But\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou, a man mine equal, my guide, and mine acquaintance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.55.14" /> \begin{signline}We took sweet counsel together,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}walked unto the house of God in company.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.55.15" /> \begin{signline}Let death seize upon them,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let them go down quick into hell: for wickedness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in their dwellings,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.55.16" /> \begin{signline}As for me, I will call upon God; and the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall save me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.55.17" /> \begin{signline}Evening, and morning, and at noon, will I pray, and cry aloud: and he shall hear my voice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.55.18" /> \begin{signline}He hath delivered my soul in peace from the battle\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me: for there were many with me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.55.19" /> \begin{signline}God shall hear, and afflict them, even he that abideth of old. Selah. Because they have no changes, therefore they fear not God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.55.20" /> \begin{signline}He hath put forth his hands against such as be at peace with him: he hath broken his covenant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.55.21" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}The words\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of his mouth were smoother than butter, but war\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his heart: his words were softer than oil, yet\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they drawn swords.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.55.22" /> \begin{signline}Cast thy burden upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he shall sustain thee: he shall never suffer the righteous to be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.55.23" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O God, shalt bring them down into the pit of destruction: bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days; but I will trust in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="56" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Jonath-elem-rechokim,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when the Philistines\end{signline}
\begin{signline}took\end{signline}
\begin{signline}him in Gath.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.56.1" /> \begin{signline}Be merciful unto me, O God: for man would swallow me up; he fighting daily oppresseth me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.56.2" /> \begin{signline}Mine enemies would daily swallow \end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}up: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}many that fight against me, O thou most High.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.56.3" /> \begin{signline}What time I am afraid, I will trust in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.56.4" /> \begin{signline}In God I will praise his word, in God I have put my trust; I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.56.5" /> \begin{signline}Every day they wrest my words: all their thoughts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}against me for evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.56.6" /> \begin{signline}They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they mark my steps, when they wait for my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.56.7" /> \begin{signline}Shall they escape by iniquity? in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thine\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}anger cast down the people, O God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.56.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou tellest my wanderings: put thou my tears into thy bottle:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are they\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not in thy book?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.56.9" /> \begin{signline}When I cry\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}unto thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, then shall mine enemies turn back: this I know; for God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.56.10" /> \begin{signline}In God will I praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}word: in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will I praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.56.11" /> \begin{signline}In God have I put my trust: I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.56.12" /> \begin{signline}Thy vows\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon me, O God: I will render praises unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.56.13" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast delivered my soul from death:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wilt\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou deliver\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="57" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Al-taschith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he fled\end{signline}
\begin{signline}from\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Saul\end{signline}
\begin{signline}in the cave.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.57.1" /> \begin{signline}Be merciful unto me, O God, be merciful unto me: for my soul trusteth in thee: yea, in the shadow of thy wings will I make my refuge, until\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}these\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}calamities be overpast.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.57.2" /> \begin{signline}I will cry unto God most high; unto God that performeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}all things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.57.3" /> \begin{signline}He shall send from heaven, and save me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the reproach of him that would swallow me up. Selah. God shall send forth his mercy and his truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.57.4" /> \begin{signline}My soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among lions:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I lie\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even among\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}them that are set on fire,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sons of men, whose teeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}spears and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.57.5" /> \begin{signline}Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}let\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.57.6" /> \begin{signline}They have prepared a net for my steps; my soul is bowed down: they have digged a pit before me, into the midst whereof they are fallen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}themselves\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.57.7" /> \begin{signline}My heart is fixed, O God, my heart is fixed: I will sing and give praise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.57.8" /> \begin{signline}Awake up, my glory; awake, psaltery and harp: I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}myself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will awake early.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.57.9" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people: I will sing unto thee among the nations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.57.10" /> \begin{signline}For thy mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great unto the heavens, and thy truth unto the clouds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.57.11" /> \begin{signline}Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}let\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="58" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Al-taschith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.58.1" /> \begin{signline}Do ye indeed speak righteousness, O congregation? do ye judge uprightly, O ye sons of men?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.58.2" /> \begin{signline}Yea, in heart ye work wickedness; ye weigh the violence of your hands in the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.58.3" /> \begin{signline}The wicked are estranged from the womb: they go astray as soon as they be born, speaking lies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.58.4" /> \begin{signline}Their poison\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the poison of a serpent:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the deaf adder\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}stoppeth her ear;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.58.5" /> \begin{signline}Which will not hearken to the voice of charmers, charming never so wisely.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.58.6" /> \begin{signline}Break their teeth, O God, in their mouth: break out the great teeth of the young lions, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.58.7" /> \begin{signline}Let them melt away as waters\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}run continually:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he bendeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his bow to shoot\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his arrows, let them be as cut in pieces.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.58.8" /> \begin{signline}As a snail\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}melteth, let\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}every one of them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pass away:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the untimely birth of a woman,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they may not see the sun.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.58.9" /> \begin{signline}Before your pots can feel the thorns, he shall take them away as with a whirlwind, both living, and in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.58.10" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall rejoice when he seeth the vengeance: he shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.58.11" /> \begin{signline}So that a man shall say, Verily\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a reward for the righteous: verily he is a God that judgeth in the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="59" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Al-taschith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David;\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when Saul\end{signline}
\begin{signline}sent,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and they watched\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the house\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to kill him.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.59.1" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me from mine enemies, O my God: defend me from them that rise up against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.59.2" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me from the workers of iniquity, and save me from bloody men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.59.3" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, they lie in wait for my soul: the mighty are gathered against me; not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my transgression, nor\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my sin, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.59.4" /> \begin{signline}They run and prepare themselves without\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fault: awake to help me, and behold.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.59.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou therefore, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of hosts, the God of Israel, awake to visit all the heathen: be not merciful to any wicked transgressors. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.59.6" /> \begin{signline}They return at evening: they make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.59.7" /> \begin{signline}Behold, they belch out with their mouth: swords\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in their lips: for who,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}say they\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, doth hear?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.59.8" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, shalt laugh at them; thou shalt have all the heathen in derision.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.59.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Because of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his strength will I wait upon thee: for God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my defence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.59.10" /> \begin{signline}The God of my mercy shall prevent me: God shall let me see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.59.11" /> \begin{signline}Slay them not, lest my people forget: scatter them by thy power; and bring them down, O Lord our shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.59.12" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}For\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sin of their mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the words of their lips let them even be taken in their pride: and for cursing and lying\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they speak.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.59.13" /> \begin{signline}Consume\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in wrath, consume\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, that they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and let them know that God ruleth in Jacob unto the ends of the earth. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.59.14" /> \begin{signline}And at evening let them return;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let them make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.59.15" /> \begin{signline}Let them wander up and down for meat, and grudge if they be not satisfied.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.59.16" /> \begin{signline}But I will sing of thy power; yea, I will sing aloud of thy mercy in the morning: for thou hast been my defence and refuge in the day of my trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.59.17" /> \begin{signline}Unto thee, O my strength, will I sing: for God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my defence,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of my mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="60" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Shushan-eduth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Michtam\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to teach;\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he strove\end{signline}
\begin{signline}with Aram-naharaim\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and with Aram-zobah,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when Joab\end{signline}
\begin{signline}returned,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and smote\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Edom\end{signline}
\begin{signline}in the valley\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of salt\end{signline}
\begin{signline}twelve\end{signline}
\begin{signline}thousand.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.60.1" /> \begin{signline}O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased; O turn thyself to us again.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.60.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast made the earth to tremble; thou hast broken it: heal the breaches thereof; for it shaketh.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.60.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast shewed thy people hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.60.4" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast given a banner to them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.60.5" /> \begin{signline}That thy beloved may be delivered; save\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy right hand, and hear me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.60.6" /> \begin{signline}God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.60.7" /> \begin{signline}Gilead\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine, and Manasseh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine; Ephraim also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the strength of mine head; Judah\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my lawgiver;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.60.8" /> \begin{signline}Moab\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe: Philistia, triumph thou because of me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.60.9" /> \begin{signline}Who will bring me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}into\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.60.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Wilt\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not thou, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hadst cast us off? and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}didst not go out with our armies?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.60.11" /> \begin{signline}Give us help from trouble: for vain\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the help of man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.60.12" /> \begin{signline}Through God we shall do valiantly: for he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall tread down our enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="61" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Neginah,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.61.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear my cry, O God; attend unto my prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.61.2" /> \begin{signline}From the end of the earth will I cry unto thee, when my heart is overwhelmed: lead me to the rock\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is higher than I.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.61.3" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast been a shelter for me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a strong tower from the enemy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.61.4" /> \begin{signline}I will abide in thy tabernacle for ever: I will trust in the covert of thy wings. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.61.5" /> \begin{signline}For thou, O God, hast heard my vows: thou hast given\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the heritage of those that fear thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.61.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou wilt prolong the king’s life:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his years as many generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.61.7" /> \begin{signline}He shall abide before God for ever: O prepare mercy and truth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}may preserve him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.61.8" /> \begin{signline}So will I sing praise unto thy name for ever, that I may daily perform my vows.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="62" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to Jeduthun,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.62.1" /> \begin{signline}Truly my soul waiteth upon God: from him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.62.2" />\begin{signline}He only\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock and my salvation;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.62.3" /> \begin{signline}How long will ye imagine mischief against a man? ye shall be slain all of you: as a bowing wall\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall ye be, and as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a tottering fence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.62.4" /> \begin{signline}They only consult to cast\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}down from his excellency: they delight in lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.62.5" /> \begin{signline}My soul, wait thou only upon God; for my expectation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.62.6" />\begin{signline}He only\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock and my salvation:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my defence; I shall not be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.62.7" /> \begin{signline}In God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my refuge,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.62.8" /> \begin{signline}Trust in him at all times;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}people, pour out your heart before him: God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a refuge for us. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.62.9" /> \begin{signline}Surely men of low degree\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vanity,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}men of high degree\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a lie: to be laid in the balance, they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}altogether\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}lighter\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}than vanity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.62.10" /> \begin{signline}Trust not in oppression, and become not vain in robbery: if riches increase, set not your heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.62.11" /> \begin{signline}God hath spoken once; twice have I heard this; that power\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belongeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.62.12" /> \begin{signline}Also unto thee, O Lord,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belongeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mercy: for thou renderest to every man according to his work.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="63" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he was in the wilderness\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Judah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.63.1" /> \begin{signline}O God, thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God; early will I seek thee: my soul thirsteth  for thee, my flesh longeth  for thee in a dry and thirsty land, where no water is;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.63.2" /> \begin{signline}To see thy power and thy glory, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I have seen thee in the sanctuary.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.63.3" /> \begin{signline}Because thy lovingkindness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than life, my lips shall praise thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.63.4" /> \begin{signline}Thus will I bless thee while I live: I will lift up my hands in thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.63.5" /> \begin{signline}My soul shall be satisfied as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}marrow and fatness; and my mouth shall praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thee\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with joyful lips:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.63.6" /> \begin{signline}When I remember thee upon my bed,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}meditate on thee in the\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}night\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}watches.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.63.7" /> \begin{signline}Because thou hast been my help, therefore in the shadow of thy wings will I rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.63.8" /> \begin{signline}My soul followeth hard after thee: thy right hand upholdeth me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.63.9" />\begin{signline}But those\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seek my soul, to destroy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, shall go into the lower parts of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.63.10" /> \begin{signline}They shall fall by the sword: they shall be a portion for foxes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.63.11" /> \begin{signline}But the king shall rejoice in God; every one that sweareth by him shall glory: but the mouth of them that speak lies shall be stopped.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="64" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.64.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear my voice, O God, in my prayer: preserve  my life from fear of the enemy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.64.2" /> \begin{signline}Hide me from the secret counsel of the wicked; from the insurrection of the workers of iniquity:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.64.3" /> \begin{signline}Who whet their tongue like a sword,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their bows to shoot\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their arrows,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bitter words:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.64.4" /> \begin{signline}That they may shoot in secret at the perfect: suddenly do they shoot at him, and fear not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.64.5" /> \begin{signline}They encourage themselves\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an evil matter: they commune of laying snares privily; they say, Who shall see them?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.64.6" /> \begin{signline}They search out iniquities; they accomplish a diligent search: both the inward\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thought\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of every one\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and the heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.64.7" /> \begin{signline}But God shall shoot at them\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an arrow; suddenly shall they be wounded.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.64.8" /> \begin{signline}So they shall make their own tongue to fall upon themselves: all that see them shall flee away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.64.9" /> \begin{signline}And all men shall fear, and shall declare the work of God; for they shall wisely consider of his doing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.64.10" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall be glad in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and shall trust in him; and all the upright in heart shall glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="65" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.65.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise waiteth for thee, O God, in Sion: and unto thee shall the vow be performed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.65.2" /> \begin{signline}O thou that hearest prayer, unto thee shall all flesh come.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.65.3" /> \begin{signline}Iniquities prevail against me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our transgressions, thou shalt purge them away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.65.4" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is the man whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou choosest, and causest to approach\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}unto thee, that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he may dwell in thy courts: we shall be satisfied with the goodness of thy house,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of thy holy temple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.65.5" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}By\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible things in righteousness wilt thou answer us, O God of our salvation;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that are afar off\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sea:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.65.6" /> \begin{signline}Which by his strength setteth fast the mountains;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}girded with power:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.65.7" /> \begin{signline}Which stilleth the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.65.8" /> \begin{signline}They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at thy tokens: thou makest the outgoings of the morning and evening to rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.65.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou visitest the earth, and waterest it: thou greatly enrichest it with the river of God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is full of water: thou preparest them corn, when thou hast so provided for it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.65.10" /> \begin{signline}Thou waterest the ridges thereof abundantly: thou settlest the furrows thereof: thou makest it soft with showers: thou blessest the springing thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.65.11" /> \begin{signline}Thou crownest the year with thy goodness; and thy paths drop fatness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.65.12" /> \begin{signline}They drop\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the pastures of the wilderness: and the little hills rejoice on every side.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.65.13" /> \begin{signline}The pastures are clothed with flocks; the valleys also are covered over with corn; they shout for joy, they also sing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="66" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Psalm.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.66.1" /> \begin{signline}Make a joyful noise unto God, all ye lands:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.66.2" /> \begin{signline}Sing forth the honour of his name: make his praise glorious.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.66.3" /> \begin{signline}Say unto God, How terrible\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art thou in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy works! through the greatness of thy power shall thine enemies submit themselves unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.66.4" /> \begin{signline}All the earth shall worship thee, and shall sing unto thee; they shall sing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy name. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.66.5" /> \begin{signline}Come and see the works of God:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}doing toward the children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.66.6" /> \begin{signline}He turned the sea into dry\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}land:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they went through the flood on foot: there did we rejoice in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.66.7" /> \begin{signline}He ruleth by his power for ever; his eyes behold the nations: let not the rebellious exalt  themselves. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.66.8" /> \begin{signline}O bless our God, ye people, and make the voice of his praise to be heard:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.66.9" /> \begin{signline}Which holdeth our soul in life, and suffereth not our feet to be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.66.10" /> \begin{signline}For thou, O God, hast proved us: thou hast tried us, as silver is tried.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.66.11" /> \begin{signline}Thou broughtest us into the net; thou laidst affliction upon our loins.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.66.12" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast caused men to ride over our heads; we went through fire and through water: but thou broughtest us out into a wealthy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}place\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.66.13" /> \begin{signline}I will go into thy house with burnt offerings: I will pay thee my vows,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.66.14" /> \begin{signline}Which my lips have uttered, and my mouth hath spoken, when I was in trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.66.15" /> \begin{signline}I will offer unto thee burnt sacrifices of fatlings, with the incense of rams; I will offer bullocks with goats. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.66.16" /> \begin{signline}Come\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hear, all ye that fear God, and I will declare what he hath done for my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.66.17" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.66.18" /> \begin{signline}If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me:\end{signline}</add>
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.66.19" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}But\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}verily God hath heard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he hath attended to the voice of my prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.66.20" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God, which hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="67" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.67.1" /> \begin{signline}God be merciful unto us, and bless us;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cause his face to shine upon us; Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.67.2" /> \begin{signline}That thy way may be known upon earth, thy saving health among all nations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.67.3" /> \begin{signline}Let the people praise thee, O God; let all the people praise thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.67.4" /> \begin{signline}O let the nations be glad and sing for joy: for thou shalt judge the people righteously, and govern the nations upon earth. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.67.5" /> \begin{signline}Let the people praise thee, O God; let all the people praise thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.67.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall the earth yield her increase;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our own God, shall bless us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.67.7" /> \begin{signline}God shall bless us; and all the ends of the earth shall fear him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="68" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.68.1" /> \begin{signline}Let God arise, let his enemies be scattered: let them also that hate him flee before him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.68.2" /> \begin{signline}As smoke is driven away,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}drive\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}away: as wax melteth before the fire,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let the wicked perish at the presence of God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.68.3" /> \begin{signline}But let the righteous be glad; let them rejoice before God: yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.68.4" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto God, sing praises to his name: extol  him that rideth upon the heavens by his name \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}Jah\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and rejoice before him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.68.5" /> \begin{signline}A father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God in his holy habitation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.68.6" /> \begin{signline}God setteth the solitary in families: he bringeth out those which are bound with chains: but the rebellious dwell in a dry\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}land\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.68.7" /> \begin{signline}O God, when thou wentest forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness; Selah:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.68.8" /> \begin{signline}The earth shook, the heavens also dropped at the presence of God:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Sinai itself\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was moved\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}at the presence of God, the God of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.68.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou, O God, didst send a plentiful rain, whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance, when it was weary.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.68.10" /> \begin{signline}Thy congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.68.11" /> \begin{signline}The Lord gave the word: great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the company of those that published\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.68.12" /> \begin{signline}Kings of armies did flee apace: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.68.13" /> \begin{signline}Though ye have lien among the pots,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet shall ye be as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the wings of a dove covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.68.14" /> \begin{signline}When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}white\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as snow in Salmon.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.68.15" /> \begin{signline}The hill of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the hill of Bashan; an high hill\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the hill of Bashan.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.68.16" /> \begin{signline}Why leap ye, ye high hills?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the hill\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God desireth to dwell in; yea, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will dwell\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.68.17" /> \begin{signline}The chariots of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}twenty thousand,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thousands of angels: the Lord\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among them,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Sinai, in the holy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}place\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.68.18" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast ascended on high, thou hast led captivity captive: thou hast received gifts for men; yea,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rebellious also, that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God might dwell\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}among them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.68.19" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the Lord,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}daily loadeth us\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with benefits, even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of our salvation. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.68.20" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of salvation; and unto\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the Lord\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belong\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the issues from death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.68.21" /> \begin{signline}But God shall wound the head of his enemies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.68.22" /> \begin{signline}The Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my people\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}again from the depths of the sea:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.68.23" /> \begin{signline}That thy foot may be dipped in the blood of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thine\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}enemies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the tongue of thy dogs in the same.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.68.24" /> \begin{signline}They have seen thy goings, O God;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.68.25" /> \begin{signline}The singers went before, the players on instruments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}followed\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}after; among\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the damsels playing with timbrels.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.68.26" /> \begin{signline}Bless ye God in the congregations,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the Lord, from the fountain of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.68.27" />\begin{signline}There\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}little Benjamin\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their ruler, the princes of Judah\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their council, the princes of Zebulun,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the princes of Naphtali.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.68.28" /> \begin{signline}Thy God hath commanded thy strength: strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.68.29" /> \begin{signline}Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.68.30" /> \begin{signline}Rebuke the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}till every one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}submit himself with pieces of silver: scatter thou the people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}delight in war.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.68.31" /> \begin{signline}Princes shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.68.32" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto God, ye kingdoms of the earth; O sing praises unto the Lord; Selah:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.68.33" /> \begin{signline}To him that rideth upon the heavens of heavens,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of old; lo, he doth send out his voice,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a mighty voice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.68.34" /> \begin{signline}Ascribe ye strength unto God: his excellency\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}over Israel, and his strength\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the clouds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.68.35" /> \begin{signline}O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible out of thy holy places: the God of Israel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that giveth strength and power unto\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}people. Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="69" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Shoshannim,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.69.1" /> \begin{signline}Save me, O God; for the waters are come in unto\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.69.2" /> \begin{signline}I sink in deep mire, where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no standing: I am come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.69.3" /> \begin{signline}I am weary of my crying: my throat is dried: mine eyes fail while I wait for my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.69.4" /> \begin{signline}They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of mine head: they that would destroy me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine enemies wrongfully, are mighty: then I restored\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}which I took not away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.69.5" /> \begin{signline}O God, thou knowest my foolishness; and my sins are not hid from thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.69.6" /> \begin{signline}Let not them that wait on thee, O Lord \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts, be ashamed for my sake: let not those that seek thee be confounded for my sake, O God of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.69.7" /> \begin{signline}Because for thy sake I have borne reproach; shame hath covered my face.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.69.8" /> \begin{signline}I am become a stranger unto my brethren, and an alien unto my mother’s children.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.69.9" /> \begin{signline}For the zeal of thine house hath eaten me up; and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.69.10" /> \begin{signline}When I wept,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and chastened\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my soul with fasting, that was to my reproach.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.69.11" /> \begin{signline}I made sackcloth also my garment; and I became a proverb to them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.69.12" /> \begin{signline}They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the song of the drunkards.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.69.13" /> \begin{signline}But as for me, my prayer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an acceptable time: O God, in the multitude of thy mercy hear me, in the truth of thy salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.69.14" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink: let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.69.15" /> \begin{signline}Let not the waterflood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up, and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.69.16" /> \begin{signline}Hear me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for thy lovingkindness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.69.17" /> \begin{signline}And hide not thy face from thy servant; for I am in trouble: hear me speedily.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.69.18" /> \begin{signline}Draw nigh unto my soul,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}redeem it: deliver me because of mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.69.19" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonour: mine adversaries\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.69.20" /> \begin{signline}Reproach hath broken my heart; and I am full of heaviness: and I looked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for some\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to take pity, but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none; and for comforters, but I found none.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.69.21" /> \begin{signline}They gave me also gall for my meat; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.69.22" /> \begin{signline}Let their table become a snare before them: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that which should have been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}welfare,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}let it become\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a trap.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.69.23" /> \begin{signline}Let their eyes be darkened, that they see not; and make their loins continually to shake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.69.24" /> \begin{signline}Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.69.25" /> \begin{signline}Let their habitation be desolate;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let none dwell in their tents.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.69.26" /> \begin{signline}For they persecute\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whom thou hast smitten; and they talk to the grief of those whom thou hast wounded.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.69.27" /> \begin{signline}Add iniquity unto their iniquity: and let them not come into thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.69.28" /> \begin{signline}Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.69.29" />\begin{signline}But I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor and sorrowful: let thy salvation, O God, set me up on high.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.69.30" /> \begin{signline}I will praise the name of God with a song, and will magnify him with thanksgiving.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.69.31" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}This\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also shall please the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}better than an ox\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bullock that hath horns and hoofs.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.69.32" /> \begin{signline}The humble shall see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this, and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}be glad: and your heart shall live that seek God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.69.33" />\begin{signline}For the \end{signline} <nd> \begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}heareth  the poor, and despiseth not his prisoners.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.69.34" /> \begin{signline}Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas, and every thing that moveth therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.69.35" /> \begin{signline}For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah: that they may dwell there, and have it in possession.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.69.36" /> \begin{signline}The seed also of his servants shall inherit it: and they that love his name shall dwell therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="70" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to bring to remembrance.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.70.1" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Make haste\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O God, to deliver me; make haste to help me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.70.2" /> \begin{signline}Let them be ashamed and confounded that seek after my soul: let them be turned backward, and put to confusion, that desire my hurt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.70.3" /> \begin{signline}Let them be turned back for a reward of their shame that say, Aha, aha.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.70.4" /> \begin{signline}Let all those that seek thee rejoice and be glad in thee: and let such as love thy salvation say continually, Let God be magnified.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.70.5" />\begin{signline}But I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor and needy: make haste unto me, O God: thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my help and my deliverer; O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, make no tarrying.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="71" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.71.1" /> \begin{signline}In thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, do I put my trust: let me never be put to confusion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.71.2" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me in thy righteousness, and cause me to escape: incline thine ear unto me, and save me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.71.3" /> \begin{signline}Be thou my strong habitation, whereunto I may continually resort: thou hast given commandment to save me; for thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock and my fortress.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.71.4" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.71.5" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my hope, O Lord \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my trust from my youth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.71.6" /> \begin{signline}By thee have I been holden up from the womb: thou art he that took me out of my mother’s bowels: my praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually of thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.71.7" /> \begin{signline}I am as a wonder unto many; but thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my strong refuge.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.71.8" /> \begin{signline}Let my mouth be filled\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy honour all the day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.71.9" /> \begin{signline}Cast me not off in the time of old age; forsake me not when my strength faileth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.71.10" /> \begin{signline}For mine enemies speak against me; and they that lay wait for my soul take counsel together,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.71.11" /> \begin{signline}Saying, God hath forsaken him: persecute and take him; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to deliver\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.71.12" /> \begin{signline}O God, be not far from me: O my God, make haste for my help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.71.13" /> \begin{signline}Let them be confounded\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}consumed that are adversaries to my soul; let them be covered\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}reproach and dishonour that seek my hurt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.71.14" /> \begin{signline}But I will hope continually, and will yet praise thee more and more.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.71.15" /> \begin{signline}My mouth shall shew forth thy righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy salvation all the day; for I know not the numbers\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereof\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.71.16" /> \begin{signline}I will go in the strength of the Lord \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I will make mention of thy righteousness,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of thine only.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.71.17" /> \begin{signline}O God, thou hast taught me from my youth: and hitherto have I declared thy wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.71.18" /> \begin{signline}Now also when I am old and grayheaded, O God, forsake me not; until I have shewed thy strength unto\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}generation,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy power to every one\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is to come.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.71.19" /> \begin{signline}Thy righteousness also, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}very high, who hast done great things: O God, who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like unto thee!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.71.20" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, which hast shewed me great and sore troubles, shalt quicken me again, and shalt bring me up again from the depths of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.71.21" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt increase my greatness, and comfort me on every side.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.71.22" /> \begin{signline}I will also praise thee with the psaltery,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy truth, O my God: unto thee will I sing with the harp, O thou Holy One of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.71.23" /> \begin{signline}My lips shall greatly rejoice when I sing unto thee; and my soul, which thou hast redeemed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.71.24" /> \begin{signline}My tongue also shall talk of thy righteousness all the day long: for they are confounded, for they are brought unto shame, that seek my hurt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="72" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}for Solomon.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.72.1" /> \begin{signline}Give the king thy judgments, O God, and thy righteousness unto the king’s son.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.72.2" /> \begin{signline}He shall judge thy people with righteousness, and thy poor with judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.72.3" /> \begin{signline}The mountains shall bring peace to the people, and the little hills, by righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.72.4" /> \begin{signline}He shall judge the poor of the people, he shall save the children of the needy, and shall break in pieces the oppressor.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.72.5" /> \begin{signline}They shall fear thee as long as the sun and moon endure, throughout all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.72.6" /> \begin{signline}He shall come down like rain upon the mown grass: as showers\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}water the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.72.7" /> \begin{signline}In his days shall the righteous flourish; and abundance of peace so long as the moon endureth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.72.8" /> \begin{signline}He shall have dominion also from sea to sea, and from the river unto the ends of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.72.9" /> \begin{signline}They that dwell in the wilderness shall bow before him; and his enemies shall lick the dust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.72.10" /> \begin{signline}The kings of Tarshish and of the isles shall bring presents: the kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.72.11" /> \begin{signline}Yea, all kings shall fall down before him: all nations shall serve him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.72.12" /> \begin{signline}For he shall deliver the needy when he crieth; the poor also, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that hath no helper.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.72.13" /> \begin{signline}He shall spare the poor and needy, and shall save the souls of the needy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.72.14" /> \begin{signline}He shall redeem their soul from deceit and violence: and precious shall their blood be in his sight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.72.15" /> \begin{signline}And he shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba: prayer also shall be made for him continually;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}daily shall he be praised.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.72.16" /> \begin{signline}There shall be an handful of corn in the earth upon the top of the mountains; the fruit thereof shall shake like Lebanon: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the city shall flourish like grass of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.72.17" /> \begin{signline}His name shall endure for ever: his name shall be continued as long as the sun: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall be blessed in him: all nations shall call him blessed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.72.18" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God, the God of Israel, who only doeth wondrous things.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.72.19" /> \begin{signline}And blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his glorious name for ever: and let the whole earth be filled\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his glory; Amen, and Amen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.72.20" /> \begin{signline}The prayers of David the son of Jesse are ended.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="73" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.73.1" /> \begin{signline}Truly God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good to Israel,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to such as are of a clean heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.73.2" /> \begin{signline}But as for me, my feet were almost gone; my steps had well nigh slipped.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.73.3" /> \begin{signline}For I was envious at the foolish,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I saw the prosperity of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.73.4" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no bands in their death: but their strength\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}firm.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.73.5" />\begin{signline}They\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not in trouble\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as other\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}men; neither are they plagued like\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}other\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.73.6" /> \begin{signline}Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain; violence covereth them\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a garment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.73.7" /> \begin{signline}Their eyes stand out with fatness: they have more than heart could wish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.73.8" /> \begin{signline}They are corrupt, and speak wickedly\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}concerning\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}oppression: they speak loftily.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.73.9" /> \begin{signline}They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walketh through the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.73.10" /> \begin{signline}Therefore his people return hither: and waters of a full\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cup\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}are wrung out to them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.73.11" /> \begin{signline}And they say, How doth God know? and is there knowledge in the most High?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.73.12" />\begin{signline}Behold, these\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ungodly, who prosper in the world; they increase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}riches.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.73.13" /> \begin{signline}Verily I have cleansed my heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vain, and washed my hands in innocency.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.73.14" /> \begin{signline}For all the day long have I been plagued, and chastened every morning.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.73.15" /> \begin{signline}If I say, I will speak thus; behold, I should offend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}against\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the generation of thy children.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.73.16" /> \begin{signline}When I thought to know this, it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}too painful for me;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.73.17" /> \begin{signline}Until I went into the sanctuary of God;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}understood I their end.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.73.18" /> \begin{signline}Surely thou didst set them in slippery places: thou castedst them down into destruction.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.73.19" />\begin{signline}How are they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}brought\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}into desolation, as in a moment! they are utterly consumed with terrors.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.73.20" /> \begin{signline}As a dream when\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}awaketh;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.73.21" /> \begin{signline}Thus my heart was grieved, and I was pricked in my reins.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.73.22" /> \begin{signline}So foolish\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I, and ignorant: I was\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a beast before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.73.23" />\begin{signline}Nevertheless I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually with thee: thou hast holden\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}by my right hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.73.24" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel, and afterward receive me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.73.25" /> \begin{signline}Whom have I in heaven\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}? and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none upon earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I desire beside thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.73.26" /> \begin{signline}My flesh and my heart faileth:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.73.27" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.73.28" /> \begin{signline}But\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good for me to draw near to God: I have put my trust in the Lord \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, that I may declare all thy works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="74" />
<d>\begin{signline}Maschil\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.74.1" /> \begin{signline}O God, why hast thou cast\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}off for ever?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}why\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}doth thine anger smoke against the sheep of thy pasture?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.74.2" /> \begin{signline}Remember thy congregation,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast purchased of old; the rod of thine inheritance,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast redeemed; this mount Zion, wherein thou hast dwelt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.74.3" /> \begin{signline}Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.74.4" /> \begin{signline}Thine enemies roar in the midst of thy congregations; they set up their ensigns\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}signs.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.74.5" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}A man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.74.6" /> \begin{signline}But now they break down the carved work thereof at once with axes and hammers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.74.7" /> \begin{signline}They have cast fire into thy sanctuary, they have defiled\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}by casting down\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the dwelling place of thy name to the ground.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.74.8" /> \begin{signline}They said in their hearts, Let us destroy them together: they have burned up all the synagogues of God in the land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.74.9" /> \begin{signline}We see not our signs:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no more any prophet: neither\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is there\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among us any that knoweth how long.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.74.10" /> \begin{signline}O God, how long shall the adversary reproach? shall the enemy blaspheme thy name for ever?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.74.11" /> \begin{signline}Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand? pluck\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}out of thy bosom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.74.12" /> \begin{signline}For God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.74.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou didst divide the sea by thy strength: thou brakest the heads of the dragons in the waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.74.14" /> \begin{signline}Thou brakest the heads of leviathan in pieces,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gavest him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}meat to the people inhabiting the wilderness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.74.15" /> \begin{signline}Thou didst cleave the fountain and the flood: thou driedst up mighty rivers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.74.16" /> \begin{signline}The day\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine, the night also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine: thou hast prepared the light and the sun.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.74.17" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast set all the borders of the earth: thou hast made summer and winter.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.74.18" /> \begin{signline}Remember this,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the enemy hath reproached, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the foolish people have blasphemed thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.74.19" /> \begin{signline}O deliver not the soul of thy turtledove unto the multitude\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of the wicked:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}forget not the congregation of thy poor for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.74.20" /> \begin{signline}Have respect unto the covenant: for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations of cruelty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.74.21" /> \begin{signline}O let not the oppressed return ashamed: let the poor and needy praise thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.74.22" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O God, plead thine own cause: remember how the foolish man reproacheth thee daily.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.74.23" /> \begin{signline}Forget not the voice of thine enemies: the tumult of those that rise up against thee increaseth continually.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="75" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Al-taschith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.75.1" /> \begin{signline}Unto thee, O God, do we give thanks,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}unto thee\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do we give thanks: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy name is near thy wondrous works declare.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.75.2" /> \begin{signline}When I shall receive the congregation I will judge uprightly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.75.3" /> \begin{signline}The earth and all the inhabitants thereof are dissolved: I bear up the pillars of it. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.75.4" /> \begin{signline}I said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.75.5" /> \begin{signline}Lift not up your horn on high: speak\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}not with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a stiff neck.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.75.6" /> \begin{signline}For promotion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.75.7" /> \begin{signline}But God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the judge: he putteth down one, and setteth up another.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.75.8" /> \begin{signline}For in the hand of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a cup, and the wine is red; it is full of mixture; and he poureth out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall wring\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}out,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}drink\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.75.9" /> \begin{signline}But I will declare for ever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.75.10" /> \begin{signline}All the horns of the wicked also will I cut off;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="76" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}on Neginoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.76.1" /> \begin{signline}In Judah\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God known: his name\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great in Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.76.2" /> \begin{signline}In Salem also is his tabernacle, and his dwelling place in Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.76.3" /> \begin{signline}There brake he the arrows of the bow, the shield, and the sword, and the battle. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.76.4" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more glorious\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}excellent than the mountains of prey.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.76.5" /> \begin{signline}The stouthearted are spoiled, they have slept their sleep: and none of the men of might have found their hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.76.6" /> \begin{signline}At thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, both the chariot and horse are cast into a dead sleep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.76.7" />\begin{signline}Thou,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to be feared: and who may stand in thy sight when once thou art angry?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.76.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou didst cause judgment to be heard from heaven; the earth feared, and was still,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.76.9" /> \begin{signline}When God arose to judgment, to save all the meek of the earth. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.76.10" /> \begin{signline}Surely the wrath of man shall praise thee: the remainder of wrath shalt thou restrain.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.76.11" /> \begin{signline}Vow, and pay unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}your God: let all that be round about him bring presents unto him that ought to be feared.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.76.12" /> \begin{signline}He shall cut off the spirit of princes:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible to the kings of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="77" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to Jeduthun,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.77.1" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto God with my voice,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto God with my voice; and he gave ear unto me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.77.2" /> \begin{signline}In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord: my sore ran in the night, and ceased not: my soul refused  to be comforted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.77.3" /> \begin{signline}I remembered God, and was troubled: I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.77.4" /> \begin{signline}Thou holdest mine eyes waking: I am so troubled that I cannot speak.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.77.5" /> \begin{signline}I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.77.6" /> \begin{signline}I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with mine own heart: and my spirit made diligent search.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.77.7" /> \begin{signline}Will the Lord cast off for ever? and will he be favourable no more?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.77.8" /> \begin{signline}Is his mercy clean gone for ever? doth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}promise fail for evermore?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.77.9" /> \begin{signline}Hath God forgotten to be gracious? hath he in anger shut up his tender mercies? Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.77.10" /> \begin{signline}And I said, This\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my infirmity:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but I will remember\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the years of the right hand of the most High.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.77.11" /> \begin{signline}I will remember the works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: surely I will remember thy wonders of old.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.77.12" /> \begin{signline}I will meditate also of all thy work, and talk of thy doings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.77.13" /> \begin{signline}Thy way, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the sanctuary: who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great a God as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}our\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.77.14" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God that doest wonders: thou hast declared thy strength among the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.77.15" />\begin{signline}Thou hast with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thine\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}arm redeemed thy people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.77.16" /> \begin{signline}The waters saw thee, O God, the waters saw thee; they were afraid: the depths also were troubled.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.77.17" /> \begin{signline}The clouds poured out water: the skies sent out a sound: thine arrows also went abroad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.77.18" /> \begin{signline}The voice of thy thunder\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the heaven: the lightnings lightened the world: the earth trembled and shook.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.77.19" /> \begin{signline}Thy way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the sea, and thy path in the great waters, and thy footsteps are not known.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.77.20" /> \begin{signline}Thou leddest thy people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="78" />
<d>\begin{signline}Maschil\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.78.1" /> \begin{signline}Give ear, O my people,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my law: incline your ears to the words of my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.78.2" /> \begin{signline}I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.78.3" /> \begin{signline}Which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.78.4" /> \begin{signline}We will not hide\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from their children, shewing to the generation to come the praises of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he hath done.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.78.5" /> \begin{signline}For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.78.6" /> \begin{signline}That the generation to come might know\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them, even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the children\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}should be born;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}should arise and declare\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to their children:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.78.7" /> \begin{signline}That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.78.8" /> \begin{signline}And might not be as their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not stedfast with God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.78.9" /> \begin{signline}The children of Ephraim,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}armed,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.78.10" /> \begin{signline}They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.78.11" /> \begin{signline}And forgat his works, and his wonders that he had shewed them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.78.12" /> \begin{signline}Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the field of Zoan.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.78.13" /> \begin{signline}He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters to stand as an heap.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.78.14" /> \begin{signline}In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.78.15" /> \begin{signline}He clave the rocks in the wilderness, and gave\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}drink as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}out of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the great depths.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.78.16" /> \begin{signline}He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.78.17" /> \begin{signline}And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.78.18" /> \begin{signline}And they tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.78.19" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they spake against God; they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.78.20" /> \begin{signline}Behold, he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide flesh for his people?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.78.21" /> \begin{signline}Therefore the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}heard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and was wroth: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.78.22" /> \begin{signline}Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.78.23" /> \begin{signline}Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.78.24" /> \begin{signline}And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the corn of heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.78.25" /> \begin{signline}Man did eat angels’ food: he sent them meat to the full.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.78.26" /> \begin{signline}He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.78.27" /> \begin{signline}He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.78.28" />\begin{signline}And he let\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.78.29" /> \begin{signline}So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.78.30" /> \begin{signline}They were not estranged from their lust. But while their meat\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}yet in their mouths,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.78.31" /> \begin{signline}The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.78.32" /> \begin{signline}For all this they sinned still, and believed not for his wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.78.33" /> \begin{signline}Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.78.34" /> \begin{signline}When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and enquired early after God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.78.35" /> \begin{signline}And they remembered that God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their rock, and the high God their redeemer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.78.36" /> \begin{signline}Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.78.37" /> \begin{signline}For their heart was not right with him, neither were they stedfast in his covenant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.78.38" />\begin{signline}But he,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}full of compassion, forgave\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}iniquity, and destroyed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.78.39" /> \begin{signline}For he remembered that they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flesh; a wind that passeth away, and cometh not again.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.78.40" /> \begin{signline}How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}grieve him in the desert!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.78.41" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they turned back and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.78.42" /> \begin{signline}They remembered not his hand,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the day when he delivered them from the enemy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.78.43" /> \begin{signline}How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zoan:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.78.44" /> \begin{signline}And had turned their rivers into blood; and their floods, that they could not drink.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.78.45" /> \begin{signline}He sent divers sorts of flies among them, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="46" bcv="PSA.78.46" /> \begin{signline}He gave also their increase unto the caterpiller, and their labour unto the locust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="47" bcv="PSA.78.47" /> \begin{signline}He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycomore trees with frost.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="48" bcv="PSA.78.48" /> \begin{signline}He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="49" bcv="PSA.78.49" /> \begin{signline}He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending evil angels\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}among them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="50" bcv="PSA.78.50" /> \begin{signline}He made a way to his anger; he spared not their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="51" bcv="PSA.78.51" /> \begin{signline}And smote all the firstborn in Egypt; the chief of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strength in the tabernacles of Ham:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="52" bcv="PSA.78.52" /> \begin{signline}But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="53" bcv="PSA.78.53" /> \begin{signline}And he led them on safely, so that they feared not: but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="54" bcv="PSA.78.54" /> \begin{signline}And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}this mountain,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his right hand had purchased.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="55" bcv="PSA.78.55" /> \begin{signline}He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="56" bcv="PSA.78.56" /> \begin{signline}Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="57" bcv="PSA.78.57" /> \begin{signline}But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="58" bcv="PSA.78.58" /> \begin{signline}For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="59" bcv="PSA.78.59" /> \begin{signline}When God heard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred  Israel:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="60" bcv="PSA.78.60" /> \begin{signline}So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he placed among men;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="61" bcv="PSA.78.61" /> \begin{signline}And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy’s hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="62" bcv="PSA.78.62" /> \begin{signline}He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="63" bcv="PSA.78.63" /> \begin{signline}The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="64" bcv="PSA.78.64" /> \begin{signline}Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="65" bcv="PSA.78.65" /> \begin{signline}Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="66" bcv="PSA.78.66" /> \begin{signline}And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he put them to a perpetual reproach.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="67" bcv="PSA.78.67" /> \begin{signline}Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="68" bcv="PSA.78.68" /> \begin{signline}But chose the tribe of Judah, the mount Zion which he loved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="69" bcv="PSA.78.69" /> \begin{signline}And he built his sanctuary like high\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}palaces\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, like the earth which he hath established for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="70" bcv="PSA.78.70" /> \begin{signline}He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="71" bcv="PSA.78.71" /> \begin{signline}From following the ewes great with young he brought him to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="72" bcv="PSA.78.72" /> \begin{signline}So he fed them according to the integrity of his heart; and guided them by the skilfulness of his hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="79" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.79.1" /> \begin{signline}O God, the heathen are come into thine inheritance; thy holy temple have they defiled; they have laid Jerusalem on heaps.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.79.2" /> \begin{signline}The dead bodies of thy servants have they given\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}meat unto the fowls of the heaven, the flesh of thy saints unto the beasts of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.79.3" /> \begin{signline}Their blood have they shed like water round about Jerusalem; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to bury\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.79.4" /> \begin{signline}We are become a reproach to our neighbours, a scorn and derision to them that are round about us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.79.5" /> \begin{signline}How long,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? wilt thou be angry for ever? shall thy jealousy burn like fire?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.79.6" /> \begin{signline}Pour out thy wrath upon the heathen that have not known thee, and upon the kingdoms that have not called upon thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.79.7" /> \begin{signline}For they have devoured Jacob, and laid waste his dwelling place.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.79.8" /> \begin{signline}O remember not against us former iniquities: let thy tender mercies speedily prevent us: for we are brought very low.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.79.9" /> \begin{signline}Help us, O God of our salvation, for the glory of thy name: and deliver us, and purge away our sins, for thy name’s sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.79.10" /> \begin{signline}Wherefore should the heathen say, Where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their God? let him be known among the heathen in our sight\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}by\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the revenging of the blood of thy servants\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.79.11" /> \begin{signline}Let the sighing of the prisoner come before thee; according to the greatness of thy power preserve thou those that are appointed to die;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.79.12" /> \begin{signline}And render unto our neighbours sevenfold into their bosom their reproach, wherewith they have reproached thee, O Lord.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.79.13" /> \begin{signline}So we thy people and sheep of thy pasture will give thee thanks for ever: we will shew forth thy praise to all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="80" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Shoshannim-eduth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.80.1" /> \begin{signline}Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}between\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the cherubims, shine forth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.80.2" /> \begin{signline}Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}save us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.80.3" /> \begin{signline}Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.80.4" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.80.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.80.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.80.7" /> \begin{signline}Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.80.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.80.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou preparedst\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}room\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.80.10" /> \begin{signline}The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the goodly cedars.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.80.11" /> \begin{signline}She sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.80.12" />\begin{signline}Why hast thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.80.13" /> \begin{signline}The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.80.14" /> \begin{signline}Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.80.15" /> \begin{signline}And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou madest strong for thyself.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.80.16" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}burned with fire,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.80.17" /> \begin{signline}Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou madest strong for thyself.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.80.18" /> \begin{signline}So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.80.19" /> \begin{signline}Turn us again, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="81" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Gittith,\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.81.1" /> \begin{signline}Sing aloud unto God our strength: make a joyful noise unto the God of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.81.2" /> \begin{signline}Take a psalm, and bring hither the timbrel, the pleasant harp with the psaltery.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.81.3" /> \begin{signline}Blow up the trumpet in the new moon, in the time appointed, on our solemn feast day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.81.4" />\begin{signline}For this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a statute for Israel,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a law of the God of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.81.5" /> \begin{signline}This he ordained in Joseph\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a testimony, when he went out through the land of Egypt:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}where\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I heard a language\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I understood not.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.81.6" /> \begin{signline}I removed his shoulder from the burden: his hands were delivered from the pots.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.81.7" /> \begin{signline}Thou calledst in trouble, and I delivered thee; I answered thee in the secret place of thunder: I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.81.8" /> \begin{signline}Hear, O my people, and I will testify unto thee: O Israel, if thou wilt hearken unto me;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.81.9" /> \begin{signline}There shall no strange god be in thee; neither shalt thou worship any strange god.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.81.10" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.81.11" /> \begin{signline}But my people would not hearken to my voice; and Israel would none of me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.81.12" /> \begin{signline}So I gave them up unto their own hearts’ lust:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they walked in their own counsels.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.81.13" /> \begin{signline}Oh that my people had hearkened unto me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Israel had walked in my ways!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.81.14" /> \begin{signline}I should soon have subdued their enemies, and turned my hand against their adversaries.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.81.15" /> \begin{signline}The haters of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}should have submitted themselves unto him: but their time should have endured for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.81.16" /> \begin{signline}He should have fed them also with the finest of the wheat: and with honey out of the rock should I have satisfied thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="82" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.82.1" /> \begin{signline}God standeth in the congregation of the mighty; he judgeth among the gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.82.2" /> \begin{signline}How long will ye judge unjustly, and accept the persons of the wicked? Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.82.3" /> \begin{signline}Defend the poor and fatherless: do justice to the afflicted and needy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.82.4" /> \begin{signline}Deliver the poor and needy: rid\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}out of the hand of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.82.5" /> \begin{signline}They know not, neither will they understand; they walk on in darkness: all the foundations of the earth are out of course.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.82.6" /> \begin{signline}I have said, Ye\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gods; and all of you\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}children of the most High.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.82.7" /> \begin{signline}But ye shall die like men, and fall like one of the princes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.82.8" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O God, judge the earth: for thou shalt inherit all nations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="83" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Asaph.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.83.1" /> \begin{signline}Keep not thou silence, O God: hold not thy peace, and be not still, O God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.83.2" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, thine enemies make a tumult: and they that hate thee have lifted up the head.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.83.3" /> \begin{signline}They have taken crafty counsel against thy people, and consulted against thy hidden ones.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.83.4" /> \begin{signline}They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a nation; that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.83.5" /> \begin{signline}For they have consulted together with one consent: they are confederate against thee:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.83.6" /> \begin{signline}The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagarenes;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.83.7" /> \begin{signline}Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.83.8" /> \begin{signline}Assur also is joined with them: they have holpen the children of Lot. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.83.9" /> \begin{signline}Do unto them as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the Midianites; as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Sisera, as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Jabin, at the brook of Kison:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.83.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perished at Endor: they became\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dung for the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.83.11" /> \begin{signline}Make their nobles like Oreb, and like Zeeb: yea, all their princes as Zebah, and as Zalmunna:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.83.12" /> \begin{signline}Who said, Let us take to ourselves the houses of God in possession.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.83.13" /> \begin{signline}O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.83.14" /> \begin{signline}As the fire burneth a wood, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.83.15" /> \begin{signline}So persecute them with thy tempest, and make them afraid with thy storm.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.83.16" /> \begin{signline}Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek thy name, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.83.17" /> \begin{signline}Let them be confounded and troubled for ever; yea, let them be put to shame, and perish:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.83.18" />\begin{signline}That\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}may know that thou, whose name alone\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add>  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}JEHOVAH\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the most high over all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="84" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Gittith,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.84.1" /> \begin{signline}How amiable\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy tabernacles, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.84.2" /> \begin{signline}My soul longeth, yea, even fainteth for the courts of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: my heart and my flesh crieth out for the living God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.84.3" /> \begin{signline}Yea, the sparrow hath found an house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine altars, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts, my King, and my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.84.4" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that dwell in thy house: they will be still praising thee. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.84.5" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man whose strength\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thee; in whose heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ways\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.84.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}passing through the valley of Baca make it a well; the rain also filleth the pools.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.84.7" /> \begin{signline}They go from strength to strength,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}every one of them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in Zion appeareth before God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.84.8" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.84.9" /> \begin{signline}Behold, O God our shield, and look upon the face of thine anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.84.10" /> \begin{signline}For a day in thy courts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.84.11" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a sun and shield: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will give grace and glory: no good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thing\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will he withhold from them that walk uprightly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.84.12" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}of hosts, blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man that trusteth in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="85" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.85.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou hast been favourable unto thy land: thou hast brought back the captivity of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.85.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast forgiven the iniquity of thy people, thou hast covered all their sin. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.85.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast taken away all thy wrath: thou hast turned\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thyself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the fierceness of thine anger.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.85.4" /> \begin{signline}Turn us, O God of our salvation, and cause thine anger toward us to cease.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.85.5" /> \begin{signline}Wilt thou be angry with us for ever? wilt thou draw out thine anger to all generations?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.85.6" /> \begin{signline}Wilt thou not revive us again: that thy people may rejoice in thee?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.85.7" /> \begin{signline}Shew us thy mercy, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and grant us thy salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.85.8" /> \begin{signline}I will hear what God the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will speak: for he will speak peace unto his people, and to his saints: but let them not turn again to folly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.85.9" /> \begin{signline}Surely his salvation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nigh them that fear him; that glory may dwell in our land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.85.10" /> \begin{signline}Mercy and truth are met together; righteousness and peace have kissed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}each other\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.85.11" /> \begin{signline}Truth shall spring out of the earth; and righteousness shall look down from heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.85.12" /> \begin{signline}Yea, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall give\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good; and our land shall yield her increase.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.85.13" /> \begin{signline}Righteousness shall go before him; and shall set\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the way of his steps.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="86" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Prayer\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.86.1" /> \begin{signline}Bow down thine ear, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hear me: for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor and needy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.86.2" /> \begin{signline}Preserve my soul; for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy: O thou my God, save thy servant that trusteth in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.86.3" /> \begin{signline}Be merciful unto me, O Lord: for I cry unto thee daily.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.86.4" /> \begin{signline}Rejoice the soul of thy servant: for unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.86.5" /> \begin{signline}For thou, Lord,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good, and ready to forgive; and plenteous in mercy unto all them that call upon thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.86.6" /> \begin{signline}Give ear, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, unto my prayer; and attend to the voice of my supplications.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.86.7" /> \begin{signline}In the day of my trouble I will call upon thee: for thou wilt answer me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.86.8" /> \begin{signline}Among the gods\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none like unto thee, O Lord; neither\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are there any works\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like unto thy works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.86.9" /> \begin{signline}All nations whom thou hast made shall come and worship before thee, O Lord; and shall glorify thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.86.10" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great, and doest wondrous things: thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God alone.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.86.11" /> \begin{signline}Teach me thy way, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; I will walk in thy truth: unite my heart to fear thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.86.12" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify thy name for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.86.13" /> \begin{signline}For great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy mercy toward me: and thou hast delivered my soul from the lowest hell.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.86.14" /> \begin{signline}O God, the proud are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have sought after my soul; and have not set thee before them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.86.15" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O Lord,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.86.16" /> \begin{signline}O turn unto me, and have mercy upon me; give thy strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thine handmaid.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.86.17" /> \begin{signline}Shew me a token for good; that they which hate me may see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and be ashamed: because thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hast holpen me, and comforted me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="87" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.87.1" /> \begin{signline}His foundation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the holy mountains.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.87.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}loveth the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.87.3" /> \begin{signline}Glorious things are spoken of thee, O city of God. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.87.4" /> \begin{signline}I will make mention of Rahab and Babylon to them that know me: behold Philistia, and Tyre, with Ethiopia; this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}was born there.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.87.5" /> \begin{signline}And of Zion it shall be said, This and that man was born in her: and the highest himself shall establish her.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.87.6" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall count, when he writeth up the people,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}was born there. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.87.7" /> \begin{signline}As well the singers as the players on instruments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be there:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all my springs\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="88" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sons\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Korah,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}to the chief Musician\end{signline}
\begin{signline}upon Mahalath\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Leannoth,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}Maschil\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Heman\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the Ezrahite.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.88.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of my salvation, I have cried day\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}night before thee:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.88.2" /> \begin{signline}Let my prayer come before thee: incline thine ear unto my cry;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.88.3" /> \begin{signline}For my soul is full of troubles: and my life draweth nigh unto the grave.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.88.4" /> \begin{signline}I am counted with them that go down into the pit: I am as a man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no strength:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.88.5" /> \begin{signline}Free among the dead, like the slain that lie in the grave, whom thou rememberest no more: and they are cut off from thy hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.88.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast laid me in the lowest pit, in darkness, in the deeps.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.88.7" /> \begin{signline}Thy wrath lieth hard upon me, and thou hast afflicted\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with all thy waves. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.88.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast put away mine acquaintance far from me; thou hast made me an abomination unto them:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}I am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shut up, and I cannot come forth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.88.9" /> \begin{signline}Mine eye mourneth by reason of affliction: \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I have called daily upon thee, I have stretched out my hands unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.88.10" /> \begin{signline}Wilt thou shew wonders to the dead? shall the dead arise \end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}praise thee? Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.88.11" /> \begin{signline}Shall thy lovingkindness be declared in the grave?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy faithfulness in destruction?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.88.12" /> \begin{signline}Shall thy wonders be known in the dark? and thy righteousness in the land of forgetfulness?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.88.13" /> \begin{signline}But unto thee have I cried, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and in the morning shall my prayer prevent thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.88.14" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, why castest thou off my soul?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}why\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hidest thou thy face from me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.88.15" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}afflicted and ready to die from\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}youth up:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}while\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I suffer thy terrors I am distracted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.88.16" /> \begin{signline}Thy fierce wrath goeth over me; thy terrors have cut me off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.88.17" /> \begin{signline}They came round about me daily like water; they compassed me about together.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.88.18" /> \begin{signline}Lover and friend hast thou put far from me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine acquaintance into darkness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="89" />
<d>\begin{signline}Maschil\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Ethan\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the Ezrahite.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.89.1" /> \begin{signline}I will sing of the mercies of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}for ever: with my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.89.2" /> \begin{signline}For I have said, Mercy shall be built up for ever: thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.89.3" /> \begin{signline}I have made a covenant with my chosen, I have sworn unto David my servant,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.89.4" /> \begin{signline}Thy seed will I establish for ever, and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.89.5" /> \begin{signline}And the heavens shall praise thy wonders, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.89.6" /> \begin{signline}For who in the heaven can be compared unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.89.7" /> \begin{signline}God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}about him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.89.8" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of hosts, who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a strong \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness round about thee?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.89.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou rulest the raging of the sea: when the waves thereof arise, thou stillest them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.89.10" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; thou hast scattered thine enemies with thy strong arm.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.89.11" /> \begin{signline}The heavens\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine, the earth also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the world and the fulness thereof, thou hast founded them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.89.12" /> \begin{signline}The north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.89.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast a mighty arm: strong is thy hand,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high is thy right hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.89.14" /> \begin{signline}Justice and judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the habitation of thy throne: mercy and truth shall go before thy face.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.89.15" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the people that know the joyful sound: they shall walk, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in the light of thy countenance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.89.16" /> \begin{signline}In thy name shall they rejoice all the day: and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.89.17" />\begin{signline}For thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the glory of their strength: and in thy favour our horn shall be exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.89.18" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our defence; and the Holy One of Israel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our king.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.89.19" /> \begin{signline}Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I have laid help upon\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mighty; I have exalted\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}chosen out of the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.89.20" /> \begin{signline}I have found David my servant; with my holy oil have I anointed him:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.89.21" /> \begin{signline}With whom my hand shall be established: mine arm also shall strengthen him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.89.22" /> \begin{signline}The enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.89.23" /> \begin{signline}And I will beat down his foes before his face, and plague them that hate him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.89.24" /> \begin{signline}But my faithfulness and my mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.89.25" /> \begin{signline}I will set his hand also in the sea, and his right hand in the rivers.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.89.26" /> \begin{signline}He shall cry unto me, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my father, my God, and the rock of my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.89.27" /> \begin{signline}Also I will make him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}firstborn, higher than the kings of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.89.28" /> \begin{signline}My mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.89.29" /> \begin{signline}His seed also will I make\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to endure\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever, and his throne as the days of heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.89.30" /> \begin{signline}If his children forsake my law, and walk not in my judgments;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.89.31" /> \begin{signline}If they break my statutes, and keep not my commandments;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.89.32" /> \begin{signline}Then will I visit their transgression with the rod, and their iniquity with stripes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.89.33" /> \begin{signline}Nevertheless my lovingkindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.89.34" /> \begin{signline}My covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.89.35" /> \begin{signline}Once have I sworn by my holiness that I will not lie unto David.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.89.36" /> \begin{signline}His seed shall endure for ever, and his throne as the sun before me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.89.37" /> \begin{signline}It shall be established for ever as the moon, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a faithful witness in heaven. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.89.38" /> \begin{signline}But thou hast cast off and abhorred, thou hast been wroth with thine anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.89.39" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant: thou hast profaned his crown\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}by casting it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the ground.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.89.40" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast broken down all his hedges; thou hast brought his strong holds to ruin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.89.41" /> \begin{signline}All that pass by the way spoil him: he is a reproach to his neighbours.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.89.42" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast set up the right hand of his adversaries; thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.89.43" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast also turned the edge of his sword, and hast not made him to stand in the battle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.89.44" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast made his glory to cease, and cast his throne down to the ground.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.89.45" /> \begin{signline}The days of his youth hast thou shortened: thou hast covered him with shame. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="46" bcv="PSA.89.46" /> \begin{signline}How long,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? wilt thou hide thyself for ever? shall thy wrath burn like fire?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="47" bcv="PSA.89.47" /> \begin{signline}Remember how short my time is: wherefore hast thou made all men in vain?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="48" bcv="PSA.89.48" /> \begin{signline}What man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is he that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}liveth, and shall not see death? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave? Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="49" bcv="PSA.89.49" /> \begin{signline}Lord, where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy former lovingkindnesses,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou swarest unto David in thy truth?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="50" bcv="PSA.89.50" /> \begin{signline}Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}how\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I do bear in my bosom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the reproach of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all the mighty people;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="51" bcv="PSA.89.51" /> \begin{signline}Wherewith thine enemies have reproached, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; wherewith they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="52" bcv="PSA.89.52" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}for evermore. Amen, and Amen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="90" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Prayer\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of Moses\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the man\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of God.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.90.1" /> \begin{signline}Lord, thou hast been our dwelling place in all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.90.2" /> \begin{signline}Before the mountains were brought forth, or ever thou hadst formed the earth and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting, thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.90.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou turnest man to destruction; and sayest, Return, ye children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.90.4" /> \begin{signline}For a thousand years in thy sight\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as yesterday when it is past, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a watch in the night.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.90.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou carriest them away as with a flood; they are\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a sleep: in the morning\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like grass\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}groweth up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.90.6" /> \begin{signline}In the morning it flourisheth, and groweth up; in the evening it is cut down, and withereth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.90.7" /> \begin{signline}For we are consumed by thine anger, and by thy wrath are we troubled.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.90.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast set our iniquities before thee, our secret\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}sins\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the light of thy countenance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.90.9" /> \begin{signline}For all our days are passed away in thy wrath: we spend our years as a tale\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is told\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.90.10" /> \begin{signline}The days of our years\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}threescore years and ten; and if by reason of strength\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fourscore years, yet\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their strength labour and sorrow; for it is soon cut off, and we fly away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.90.11" /> \begin{signline}Who knoweth the power of thine anger? even according to thy fear,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.90.12" /> \begin{signline}So teach\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to number our days, that we may apply\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}our\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hearts unto wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.90.13" /> \begin{signline}Return, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how long? and let it repent thee concerning thy servants.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.90.14" /> \begin{signline}O satisfy us early with thy mercy; that we may rejoice and be glad all our days.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.90.15" /> \begin{signline}Make us glad according to the days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wherein\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast afflicted us,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the years\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wherein\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}we have seen evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.90.16" /> \begin{signline}Let thy work appear unto thy servants, and thy glory unto their children.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.90.17" /> \begin{signline}And let the beauty of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God be upon us: and establish thou the work of our hands upon us; yea, the work of our hands establish  thou it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="91" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.91.1" /> \begin{signline}He that dwelleth in the secret place of the most High shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.91.2" /> \begin{signline}I will say of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}He is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my refuge and my fortress: my God; in him will I trust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.91.3" /> \begin{signline}Surely he shall deliver thee from the snare of the fowler,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the noisome pestilence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.91.4" /> \begin{signline}He shall cover thee with his feathers, and under his wings shalt thou trust: his truth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shield and buckler.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.91.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt not be afraid for the terror by night;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for the arrow\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flieth by day;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.91.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for the pestilence\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}walketh in darkness;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for the destruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wasteth at noonday.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.91.7" /> \begin{signline}A thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it shall not come nigh thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.91.8" /> \begin{signline}Only with thine eyes shalt thou behold and see the reward of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.91.9" /> \begin{signline}Because thou hast made the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my refuge,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the most High, thy habitation;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.91.10" /> \begin{signline}There shall no evil befall thee, neither shall any plague come nigh thy dwelling.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.91.11" /> \begin{signline}For he shall give his angels charge over thee, to keep thee in all thy ways.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.91.12" /> \begin{signline}They shall bear thee up in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hands, lest thou dash thy foot against a stone.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.91.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt tread upon the lion and adder: the young lion and the dragon shalt thou trample under feet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.91.14" /> \begin{signline}Because he hath set his love upon me, therefore will I deliver him: I will set him on high, because he hath known my name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.91.15" /> \begin{signline}He shall call upon me, and I will answer him: I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}will be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with him in trouble; I will deliver him, and honour him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.91.16" /> \begin{signline}With long life will I satisfy him, and shew him my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="92" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for the sabbath\end{signline}
\begin{signline}day.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.92.1" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is a\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thing\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and to sing praises unto thy name, O most High:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.92.2" /> \begin{signline}To shew forth thy lovingkindness in the morning, and thy faithfulness every night,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.92.3" /> \begin{signline}Upon an instrument of ten strings, and upon the psaltery; upon the harp with a solemn sound.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.92.4" /> \begin{signline}For thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hast made me glad through thy work: I will triumph in the works of thy hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.92.5" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how great are thy works!\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy thoughts are very deep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.92.6" /> \begin{signline}A brutish man knoweth not; neither doth a fool understand  this.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.92.7" /> \begin{signline}When the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that they shall be destroyed for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.92.8" /> \begin{signline}But thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art most\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.92.9" /> \begin{signline}For, lo, thine enemies, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, for, lo, thine enemies shall perish; all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.92.10" /> \begin{signline}But my horn shalt thou exalt like\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the horn of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an unicorn: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.92.11" /> \begin{signline}Mine eye also shall see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}on mine enemies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine ears shall hear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the wicked that rise up against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.92.12" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.92.13" /> \begin{signline}Those that be planted in the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall flourish in the courts of our God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.92.14" /> \begin{signline}They shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be fat and flourishing;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.92.15" /> \begin{signline}To shew that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rock, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no unrighteousness in him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="93" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.93.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}reigneth, he is clothed with majesty; the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}is clothed with strength,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wherewith\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he hath girded himself: the world also is stablished, that it cannot be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.93.2" /> \begin{signline}Thy throne\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}established  of old: thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from everlasting.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.93.3" /> \begin{signline}The floods have lifted up, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.93.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}on high\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mightier than the noise of many waters,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea, than\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the mighty waves of the sea.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.93.5" /> \begin{signline}Thy testimonies are very sure: holiness becometh thine house, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="94" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.94.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God, to whom vengeance belongeth; O God, to whom vengeance belongeth, shew thyself.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.94.2" /> \begin{signline}Lift up thyself, thou judge of the earth: render a reward to the proud.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.94.3" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.94.4" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}How long\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall they utter\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speak hard things?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.94.5" /> \begin{signline}They break in pieces thy people, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and afflict thine heritage.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.94.6" /> \begin{signline}They slay the widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.94.7" /> \begin{signline}Yet they say, The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.94.8" /> \begin{signline}Understand, ye brutish among the people: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fools, when will ye be wise?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.94.9" /> \begin{signline}He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? he that formed the eye, shall he not see?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.94.10" /> \begin{signline}He that chastiseth the heathen, shall not he correct? he that teacheth man knowledge,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall not he know\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.94.11" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}knoweth the thoughts of man, that they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vanity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.94.12" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man whom thou chastenest, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and teachest him out of thy law;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.94.13" /> \begin{signline}That thou mayest give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit be digged for the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.94.14" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.94.15" /> \begin{signline}But judgment shall return unto righteousness: and all the upright in heart shall follow it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.94.16" /> \begin{signline}Who will rise up for me against the evildoers?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.94.17" /> \begin{signline}Unless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}had been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.94.18" /> \begin{signline}When I said, My foot slippeth; thy mercy, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, held me up.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.94.19" /> \begin{signline}In the multitude of my thoughts within me thy comforts delight my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.94.20" /> \begin{signline}Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship with thee, which frameth mischief by a law?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.94.21" /> \begin{signline}They gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.94.22" /> \begin{signline}But the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}is my defence; and my God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rock of my refuge.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.94.23" /> \begin{signline}And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God shall cut them off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="95" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.95.1" /> \begin{signline}O come, let us sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.95.2" /> \begin{signline}Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.95.3" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a great God, and a great King above all gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.95.4" /> \begin{signline}In his hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his also.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.95.5" /> \begin{signline}The sea\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}land\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.95.6" /> \begin{signline}O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our maker.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.95.7" />\begin{signline}For he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our God; and we\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.95.8" /> \begin{signline}Harden not your heart, as in the provocation,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the day of temptation in the wilderness:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.95.9" /> \begin{signline}When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.95.10" /> \begin{signline}Forty years long was I grieved with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}this\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}generation, and said, It\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.95.11" /> \begin{signline}Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="96" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.96.1" /> \begin{signline}O sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}a new song: sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.96.2" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, bless his name; shew forth his salvation from day to day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.96.3" /> \begin{signline}Declare his glory among the heathen, his wonders among all people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.96.4" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great, and greatly to be praised: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to be feared above all gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.96.5" /> \begin{signline}For all the gods of the nations\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}idols: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}made the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.96.6" /> \begin{signline}Honour and majesty\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before him: strength and beauty\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his sanctuary.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.96.7" /> \begin{signline}Give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O ye kindreds of the people, give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}glory and strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.96.8" /> \begin{signline}Give unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}due unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his name: bring an offering, and come into his courts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.96.9" /> \begin{signline}O worship the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in the beauty of holiness: fear before him, all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.96.10" /> \begin{signline}Say among the heathen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}reigneth: the world also shall be established that it shall not be moved: he shall judge the people righteously.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.96.11" /> \begin{signline}Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.96.12" /> \begin{signline}Let the field be joyful, and all that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}therein: then shall all the trees of the wood rejoice\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.96.13" /> \begin{signline}Before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for he cometh, for he cometh to judge the earth: he shall judge the world with righteousness, and the people with his truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="97" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.97.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}reigneth; let the earth rejoice; let the multitude of isles be glad\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereof\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.97.2" /> \begin{signline}Clouds and darkness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}round about him: righteousness and judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the habitation of his throne.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.97.3" /> \begin{signline}A fire goeth before him, and burneth up his enemies round about.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.97.4" /> \begin{signline}His lightnings enlightened the world: the earth saw, and trembled.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.97.5" /> \begin{signline}The hills melted like wax at the presence of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, at the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.97.6" /> \begin{signline}The heavens declare his righteousness, and all the people see his glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.97.7" /> \begin{signline}Confounded be all they that serve graven images, that boast themselves of idols: worship him, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.97.8" /> \begin{signline}Zion heard, and was glad; and the daughters of Judah rejoiced because of thy judgments, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.97.9" /> \begin{signline}For thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high above all the earth: thou art exalted far above all gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.97.10" /> \begin{signline}Ye that love the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hate evil: he preserveth the souls of his saints; he delivereth them out of the hand of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.97.11" /> \begin{signline}Light is sown for the righteous, and gladness for the upright in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.97.12" /> \begin{signline}Rejoice in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, ye righteous; and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="98" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.98.1" /> \begin{signline}O sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}a new song; for he hath done marvellous things: his right hand, and his holy arm, hath gotten him the victory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.98.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath made known his salvation: his righteousness hath he openly shewed in the sight of the heathen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.98.3" /> \begin{signline}He hath remembered his mercy and his truth toward the house of Israel: all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.98.4" /> \begin{signline}Make a joyful noise unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all the earth: make a loud noise, and rejoice, and sing praise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.98.5" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with the harp; with the harp, and the voice of a psalm.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.98.6" /> \begin{signline}With trumpets and sound of cornet make a joyful noise before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, the King.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.98.7" /> \begin{signline}Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.98.8" /> \begin{signline}Let the floods clap\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hands: let the hills be joyful together\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.98.9" /> \begin{signline}Before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for he cometh to judge the earth: with righteousness shall he judge the world, and the people with equity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="99" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.99.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}reigneth; let the people tremble: he sitteth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}between\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the cherubims; let the earth be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.99.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great in Zion; and he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high above all the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.99.3" /> \begin{signline}Let them praise thy great and terrible name;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.99.4" /> \begin{signline}The king’s strength also loveth judgment; thou dost establish equity, thou executest judgment and righteousness in Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.99.5" /> \begin{signline}Exalt ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God, and worship at his footstool;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.99.6" /> \begin{signline}Moses and Aaron among his priests, and Samuel among them that call upon his name; they called upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he answered them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.99.7" /> \begin{signline}He spake unto them in the cloudy pillar: they kept his testimonies, and the ordinance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he gave them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.99.8" /> \begin{signline}Thou answeredst them, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God: thou wast a God that forgavest them, though thou tookest vengeance of their inventions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.99.9" /> \begin{signline}Exalt the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God, and worship at his holy hill; for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="100" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of praise.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.100.1" /> \begin{signline}Make a joyful noise unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all ye lands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.100.2" /> \begin{signline}Serve the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with gladness: come before his presence with singing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.100.3" /> \begin{signline}Know ye that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}God:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hath made us, and not we ourselves;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}we are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his people, and the sheep of his pasture.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.100.4" /> \begin{signline}Enter into his gates with thanksgiving,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}into his courts with praise: be thankful unto him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bless his name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.100.5" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good; his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}everlasting; and his truth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="101" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.101.1" /> \begin{signline}I will sing of mercy and judgment: unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, will I sing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.101.2" /> \begin{signline}I will behave myself wisely in a perfect way. O when wilt thou come unto me? I will walk within my house with a perfect heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.101.3" /> \begin{signline}I will set no wicked thing before mine eyes: I hate the work of them that turn aside;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall not cleave to me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.101.4" /> \begin{signline}A froward heart shall depart from me: I will not know a wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}person\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.101.5" /> \begin{signline}Whoso privily slandereth his neighbour, him will I cut off: him that hath an high look and a proud heart will not I suffer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.101.6" /> \begin{signline}Mine eyes\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the faithful of the land, that they may dwell with me: he that walketh in a perfect way, he shall serve me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.101.7" /> \begin{signline}He that worketh deceit shall not dwell within my house: he that telleth lies shall not tarry in my sight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.101.8" /> \begin{signline}I will early destroy all the wicked of the land; that I may cut off all wicked doers from the city of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="102" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Prayer\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of the afflicted,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he is overwhelmed,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}and poureth out\end{signline}
\begin{signline}his complaint\end{signline}
\begin{signline}before\end{signline}
\begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.102.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear my prayer, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and let my cry come unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.102.2" /> \begin{signline}Hide not thy face from me in the day\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I am in trouble; incline thine ear unto me: in the day\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I call answer me speedily.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.102.3" /> \begin{signline}For my days are consumed like smoke, and my bones are burned as an hearth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.102.4" /> \begin{signline}My heart is smitten, and withered like grass; so that I forget to eat my bread.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.102.5" /> \begin{signline}By reason of the voice of my groaning my bones cleave to my skin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.102.6" /> \begin{signline}I am like a pelican of the wilderness: I am like an owl of the desert.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.102.7" /> \begin{signline}I watch, and am as a sparrow alone upon the house top.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.102.8" /> \begin{signline}Mine enemies reproach me all the day;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that are mad against me are sworn against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.102.9" /> \begin{signline}For I have eaten ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.102.10" /> \begin{signline}Because of thine indignation and thy wrath: for thou hast lifted me up, and cast me down.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.102.11" /> \begin{signline}My days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like a shadow that declineth; and I am withered like grass.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.102.12" /> \begin{signline}But thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, shalt endure for ever; and thy remembrance unto all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.102.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt arise,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have mercy upon Zion: for the time to favour her, yea, the set time, is come.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.102.14" /> \begin{signline}For thy servants take pleasure in her stones, and favour the dust thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.102.15" /> \begin{signline}So the heathen shall fear the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and all the kings of the earth thy glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.102.16" /> \begin{signline}When the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall build up Zion, he shall appear in his glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.102.17" /> \begin{signline}He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and not despise their prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.102.18" /> \begin{signline}This shall be written for the generation to come: and the people which shall be created shall praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.102.19" /> \begin{signline}For he hath looked down from the height of his sanctuary; from heaven did the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}behold the earth;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.102.20" /> \begin{signline}To hear the groaning of the prisoner; to loose those that are appointed to death;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.102.21" /> \begin{signline}To declare the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in Zion, and his praise in Jerusalem;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.102.22" /> \begin{signline}When the people are gathered together, and the kingdoms, to serve the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.102.23" /> \begin{signline}He weakened my strength in the way; he shortened my days.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.102.24" /> \begin{signline}I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days: thy years\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}throughout all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.102.25" /> \begin{signline}Of old hast thou laid the foundation of the earth: and the heavens\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the work of thy hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.102.26" /> \begin{signline}They shall perish, but thou shalt endure: yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment; as a vesture shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.102.27" />\begin{signline}But thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the same, and thy years shall have no end.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.102.28" /> \begin{signline}The children of thy servants shall continue, and their seed shall be established before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="103" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.103.1" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul: and all that is within me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}bless\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his holy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.103.2" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.103.3" /> \begin{signline}Who forgiveth all thine iniquities; who healeth all thy diseases;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.103.4" /> \begin{signline}Who redeemeth thy life from destruction; who crowneth thee with lovingkindness and tender mercies;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.103.5" /> \begin{signline}Who satisfieth thy mouth with good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things; so that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy youth is renewed like the eagle’s.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.103.6" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}executeth righteousness and judgment for all that are oppressed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.103.7" /> \begin{signline}He made known his ways unto Moses, his acts unto the children of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.103.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}merciful and gracious, slow to anger, and plenteous in mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.103.9" /> \begin{signline}He will not always chide: neither will he keep\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his anger\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.103.10" /> \begin{signline}He hath not dealt with us after our sins; nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.103.11" /> \begin{signline}For as the heaven is high above the earth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great is his mercy toward them that fear him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.103.12" /> \begin{signline}As far as the east is from the west,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far hath he removed our transgressions from us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.103.13" /> \begin{signline}Like as a father pitieth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}children,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}pitieth them that fear him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.103.14" /> \begin{signline}For he knoweth our frame; he remembereth that we\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.103.15" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man, his days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as grass: as a flower of the field, so he flourisheth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.103.16" /> \begin{signline}For the wind passeth over it, and it is gone; and the place thereof shall know it no more.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.103.17" /> \begin{signline}But the mercy of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from everlasting to everlasting upon them that fear him, and his righteousness unto children’s children;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.103.18" /> \begin{signline}To such as keep his covenant, and to those that remember his commandments to do them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.103.19" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath prepared his throne in the heavens; and his kingdom ruleth over all.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.103.20" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, ye his angels, that excel in strength, that do his commandments, hearkening  unto the voice of his word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.103.21" /> \begin{signline}Bless ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his hosts;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ministers of his, that do his pleasure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.103.22" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all his works in all places of his dominion: bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="104" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.104.1" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul. O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God, thou art very great; thou art clothed with honour and majesty.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.104.2" /> \begin{signline}Who coverest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thyself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with light as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a garment: who stretchest out the heavens like a curtain:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.104.3" /> \begin{signline}Who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters: who maketh the clouds his chariot: who walketh upon the wings of the wind:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.104.4" /> \begin{signline}Who maketh his angels spirits; his ministers a flaming fire:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.104.5" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}laid the foundations of the earth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it should not be removed for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.104.6" /> \begin{signline}Thou coveredst it with the deep as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a garment: the waters stood above the mountains.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.104.7" /> \begin{signline}At thy rebuke they fled; at the voice of thy thunder they hasted away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.104.8" /> \begin{signline}They go up by the mountains; they go down by the valleys unto the place which thou hast founded for them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.104.9" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast set a bound that they may not pass over; that they turn not again to cover the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.104.10" /> \begin{signline}He sendeth the springs into the valleys,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}run among the hills.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.104.11" /> \begin{signline}They give drink to every beast of the field: the wild asses quench their thirst.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.104.12" /> \begin{signline}By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sing among the branches.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.104.13" /> \begin{signline}He watereth the hills from his chambers: the earth is satisfied with the fruit of thy works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.104.14" /> \begin{signline}He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle, and herb for the service of man: that he may bring forth food out of the earth;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.104.15" /> \begin{signline}And wine\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}maketh glad the heart of man,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}oil to make\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}face to shine, and bread\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strengtheneth man’s heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.104.16" /> \begin{signline}The trees of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}are full\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of sap;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.104.17" /> \begin{signline}Where the birds make their nests:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the stork, the fir trees\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}her house.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.104.18" /> \begin{signline}The high hills\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a refuge for the wild goats;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rocks for the conies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.104.19" /> \begin{signline}He appointed the moon for seasons: the sun knoweth his going down.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.104.20" /> \begin{signline}Thou makest darkness, and it is night: wherein all the beasts of the forest do creep\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}forth\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.104.21" /> \begin{signline}The young lions roar after their prey, and seek their meat from God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.104.22" /> \begin{signline}The sun ariseth, they gather themselves together, and lay them down in their dens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.104.23" /> \begin{signline}Man goeth forth unto his work and to his labour until the evening.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.104.24" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, how manifold are thy works! in wisdom hast thou made them all: the earth is full of thy riches.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.104.25" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}So is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}this great and wide sea, wherein\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}things creeping innumerable, both small and great beasts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.104.26" /> \begin{signline}There go the ships:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that leviathan,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast made to play therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.104.27" /> \begin{signline}These wait all upon thee; that thou mayest give\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their meat in due season.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.104.28" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}That\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou givest them they gather: thou openest thine hand, they are filled with good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.104.29" /> \begin{signline}Thou hidest thy face, they are troubled: thou takest away their breath, they die, and return to their dust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.104.30" /> \begin{signline}Thou sendest forth thy spirit, they are created: and thou renewest the face of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.104.31" /> \begin{signline}The glory of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall endure for ever: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall rejoice in his works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.104.32" /> \begin{signline}He looketh on the earth, and it trembleth: he toucheth the hills, and they smoke.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.104.33" /> \begin{signline}I will sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}as long as I live: I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.104.34" /> \begin{signline}My meditation of him shall be sweet: I will be glad in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.104.35" /> \begin{signline}Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth, and let the wicked be no more. Bless thou the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="105" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.105.1" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; call upon his name: make known his deeds among the people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.105.2" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk ye of all his wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.105.3" /> \begin{signline}Glory ye in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.105.4" /> \begin{signline}Seek the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and his strength: seek his face evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.105.5" /> \begin{signline}Remember his marvellous works that he hath done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.105.6" /> \begin{signline}O ye seed of Abraham his servant, ye children of Jacob his chosen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.105.7" />\begin{signline}He\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God: his judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in all the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.105.8" /> \begin{signline}He hath remembered his covenant for ever, the word\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he commanded to a thousand generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.105.9" />\begin{signline}Which\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}covenant\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he made with Abraham, and his oath unto Isaac;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.105.10" /> \begin{signline}And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to Israel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an everlasting covenant:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.105.11" /> \begin{signline}Saying, Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.105.12" />\begin{signline}When they were\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a few men in number; yea, very few, and strangers in it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.105.13" /> \begin{signline}When they went from one nation to another, from\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}kingdom to another people;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.105.14" /> \begin{signline}He suffered no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.105.15" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Saying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, Touch not mine anointed, and do my prophets no harm.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.105.16" /> \begin{signline}Moreover he called for a famine upon the land: he brake the whole staff of bread.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.105.17" /> \begin{signline}He sent a man before them,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Joseph,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}was sold for a servant:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.105.18" /> \begin{signline}Whose feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in iron:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.105.19" /> \begin{signline}Until the time that his word came: the word of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}tried him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.105.20" /> \begin{signline}The king sent and loosed him;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ruler of the people, and let him go free.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.105.21" /> \begin{signline}He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his substance:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.105.22" /> \begin{signline}To bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his senators wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.105.23" /> \begin{signline}Israel also came into Egypt; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.105.24" /> \begin{signline}And he increased his people greatly; and made them stronger than their enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.105.25" /> \begin{signline}He turned their heart to hate his people, to deal subtilly with his servants.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.105.26" /> \begin{signline}He sent Moses his servant;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Aaron whom he had chosen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.105.27" /> \begin{signline}They shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.105.28" /> \begin{signline}He sent darkness, and made it dark; and they rebelled not against his word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.105.29" /> \begin{signline}He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.105.30" /> \begin{signline}Their land brought forth frogs in abundance, in the chambers of their kings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.105.31" /> \begin{signline}He spake, and there came divers sorts of flies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lice in all their coasts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.105.32" /> \begin{signline}He gave them hail for rain,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flaming fire in their land.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.105.33" /> \begin{signline}He smote their vines also and their fig trees; and brake the trees of their coasts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.105.34" /> \begin{signline}He spake, and the locusts came, and caterpillers, and that without number,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.105.35" /> \begin{signline}And did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.105.36" /> \begin{signline}He smote also all the firstborn in their land, the chief of all their strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.105.37" /> \begin{signline}He brought them forth also with silver and gold: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not one feeble\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}person\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}among their tribes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.105.38" /> \begin{signline}Egypt was glad when they departed: for the fear of them fell upon them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.105.39" /> \begin{signline}He spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.105.40" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}The people\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.105.41" /> \begin{signline}He opened the rock, and the waters gushed out; they ran in the dry places\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a river.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.105.42" /> \begin{signline}For he remembered his holy promise,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Abraham his servant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.105.43" /> \begin{signline}And he brought forth his people with joy,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his chosen with gladness:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.105.44" /> \begin{signline}And gave them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited the labour of the people;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.105.45" /> \begin{signline}That they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="106" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.106.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.106.2" /> \begin{signline}Who can utter the mighty acts of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}can shew forth all his praise?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.106.3" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that keep judgment,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that doeth righteousness at all times.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.106.4" /> \begin{signline}Remember me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, with the favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that thou bearest unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.106.5" /> \begin{signline}That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that I may glory with thine inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.106.6" /> \begin{signline}We have sinned with our fathers, we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.106.7" /> \begin{signline}Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt; they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies; but provoked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}at the sea,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}at the Red sea.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.106.8" /> \begin{signline}Nevertheless he saved them for his name’s sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.106.9" /> \begin{signline}He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried up: so he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.106.10" /> \begin{signline}And he saved them from the hand of him that hated\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.106.11" /> \begin{signline}And the waters covered their enemies: there was not one of them left.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.106.12" /> \begin{signline}Then believed they his words; they sang his praise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.106.13" /> \begin{signline}They soon forgat his works; they waited not for his counsel:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.106.14" /> \begin{signline}But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tempted God in the desert.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.106.15" /> \begin{signline}And he gave them their request; but sent leanness into their soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.106.16" /> \begin{signline}They envied Moses also in the camp,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Aaron the saint of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.106.17" /> \begin{signline}The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.106.18" /> \begin{signline}And a fire was kindled in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.106.19" /> \begin{signline}They made a calf in Horeb, and worshipped the molten image.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.106.20" /> \begin{signline}Thus they changed their glory into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.106.21" /> \begin{signline}They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things in Egypt;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.106.22" /> \begin{signline}Wondrous works in the land of Ham,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}terrible things by the Red sea.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.106.23" /> \begin{signline}Therefore he said that he would destroy them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.106.24" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.106.25" /> \begin{signline}But murmured in their tents,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hearkened not unto the voice of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.106.26" /> \begin{signline}Therefore he lifted up his hand against them, to overthrow them in the wilderness:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.106.27" /> \begin{signline}To overthrow their seed also among the nations, and to scatter them in the lands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.106.28" /> \begin{signline}They joined themselves also unto Baal-peor, and ate the sacrifices of the dead.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.106.29" />\begin{signline}Thus they provoked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to anger with their inventions: and the plague brake in upon them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.106.30" /> \begin{signline}Then stood up Phinehas, and executed judgment: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the plague was stayed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.106.31" /> \begin{signline}And that was counted unto him for righteousness unto all generations for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.106.32" /> \begin{signline}They angered\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also at the waters of strife, so that it went ill with Moses for their sakes:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.106.33" /> \begin{signline}Because they provoked his spirit, so that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.106.34" /> \begin{signline}They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}commanded them:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.106.35" /> \begin{signline}But were mingled among the heathen, and learned their works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.106.36" /> \begin{signline}And they served their idols: which were a snare unto them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.106.37" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.106.38" /> \begin{signline}And shed innocent blood,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan: and the land was polluted with blood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.106.39" /> \begin{signline}Thus were they defiled with their own works, and went a whoring with their own inventions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.106.40" /> \begin{signline}Therefore was the wrath of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}kindled against his people, insomuch that he abhorred his own inheritance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.106.41" /> \begin{signline}And he gave them into the hand of the heathen; and they that hated them ruled over them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.106.42" /> \begin{signline}Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.106.43" /> \begin{signline}Many times did he deliver them; but they provoked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with their counsel, and were brought low for their iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.106.44" /> \begin{signline}Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.106.45" /> \begin{signline}And he remembered for them his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="46" bcv="PSA.106.46" /> \begin{signline}He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="47" bcv="PSA.106.47" /> \begin{signline}Save us, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God, and gather us from among the heathen, to give thanks unto thy holy name,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to triumph in thy praise.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="48" bcv="PSA.106.48" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="107" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.107.1" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.107.2" /> \begin{signline}Let the redeemed of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}say\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.107.3" /> \begin{signline}And gathered them out of the lands, from the east, and from the west, from the north, and from the south.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.107.4" /> \begin{signline}They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way; they found no city to dwell in.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.107.5" /> \begin{signline}Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted  in them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.107.6" /> \begin{signline}Then they cried unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in their trouble,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he delivered them out of their distresses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.107.7" /> \begin{signline}And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.107.8" />\begin{signline}Oh that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his goodness, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his wonderful works to the children of men!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.107.9" /> \begin{signline}For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.107.10" /> \begin{signline}Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}being\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bound in affliction and iron;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.107.11" /> \begin{signline}Because they rebelled against the words of God, and contemned the counsel of the most High:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.107.12" /> \begin{signline}Therefore he brought down their heart with labour; they fell down, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none to help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.107.13" /> \begin{signline}Then they cried unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in their trouble,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he saved them out of their distresses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.107.14" /> \begin{signline}He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.107.15" />\begin{signline}Oh that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his goodness, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his wonderful works to the children of men!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.107.16" /> \begin{signline}For he hath broken the gates of brass, and cut the bars of iron in sunder.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.107.17" /> \begin{signline}Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.107.18" /> \begin{signline}Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat; and they draw near unto the gates of death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.107.19" /> \begin{signline}Then they cry unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in their trouble,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he saveth them out of their distresses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.107.20" /> \begin{signline}He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from their destructions.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.107.21" />\begin{signline}Oh that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his goodness, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his wonderful works to the children of men!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.107.22" /> \begin{signline}And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.107.23" /> \begin{signline}They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.107.24" /> \begin{signline}These see the works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and his wonders in the deep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.107.25" /> \begin{signline}For he commandeth, and raiseth the stormy wind, which lifteth up the waves thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.107.26" /> \begin{signline}They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.107.27" /> \begin{signline}They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wits’ end. \end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.107.28" /> \begin{signline}Then they cry unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in their trouble, and he bringeth them out of their distresses.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.107.29" /> \begin{signline}He maketh the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.107.30" /> \begin{signline}Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.107.31" />\begin{signline}Oh that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}would praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his goodness, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his wonderful works to the children of men!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.107.32" /> \begin{signline}Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.107.33" /> \begin{signline}He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.107.34" /> \begin{signline}A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.107.35" /> \begin{signline}He turneth the wilderness into a standing water, and dry ground into watersprings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.107.36" /> \begin{signline}And there he maketh the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.107.37" /> \begin{signline}And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.107.38" /> \begin{signline}He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.107.39" /> \begin{signline}Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.107.40" /> \begin{signline}He poureth contempt upon princes, and causeth them to wander in the wilderness,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}where there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.107.41" /> \begin{signline}Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction, and maketh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}families like a flock.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.107.42" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop her mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.107.43" />\begin{signline}Whoso\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise, and will observe these\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="108" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.108.1" /> \begin{signline}O God, my heart is fixed; I will sing and give praise, even with my glory.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.108.2" /> \begin{signline}Awake, psaltery and harp: I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}myself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will awake early.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.108.3" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, among the people: and I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.108.4" /> \begin{signline}For thy mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great above the heavens: and thy truth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}reacheth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the clouds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.108.5" /> \begin{signline}Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens: and thy glory above all the earth;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.108.6" /> \begin{signline}That thy beloved may be delivered: save\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy right hand, and answer me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.108.7" /> \begin{signline}God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.108.8" /> \begin{signline}Gilead\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine; Manasseh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine; Ephraim also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the strength of mine head; Judah\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my lawgiver;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.108.9" /> \begin{signline}Moab\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe; over Philistia will I triumph.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.108.10" /> \begin{signline}Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.108.11" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Wilt\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O God,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.108.12" /> \begin{signline}Give us help from trouble: for vain\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the help of man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.108.13" /> \begin{signline}Through God we shall do valiantly: for he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall tread down our enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="109" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.109.1" /> \begin{signline}Hold not thy peace, O God of my praise;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.109.2" /> \begin{signline}For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful are opened against me: they have spoken against me with a lying tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.109.3" /> \begin{signline}They compassed me about also with words of hatred; and fought against me without a cause.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.109.4" /> \begin{signline}For my love they are my adversaries: but I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}give myself unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}prayer.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.109.5" /> \begin{signline}And they have rewarded me evil for good, and hatred for my love.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.109.6" /> \begin{signline}Set thou a wicked man over him: and let Satan stand at his right hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.109.7" /> \begin{signline}When he shall be judged, let him be condemned: and let his prayer become sin.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.109.8" /> \begin{signline}Let his days be few;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}let another take his office.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.109.9" /> \begin{signline}Let his children be fatherless, and his wife a widow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.109.10" /> \begin{signline}Let his children be continually vagabonds, and beg: let them seek\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their bread\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also out of their desolate places.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.109.11" /> \begin{signline}Let the extortioner catch all that he hath; and let the strangers spoil his labour.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.109.12" /> \begin{signline}Let there be none to extend mercy unto him: neither let there be any to favour his fatherless children.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.109.13" /> \begin{signline}Let his posterity be cut off;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the generation following let their name be blotted out.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.109.14" /> \begin{signline}Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered with the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and let not the sin of his mother be blotted out.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.109.15" /> \begin{signline}Let them be before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}continually, that he may cut off the memory of them from the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.109.16" /> \begin{signline}Because that he remembered not to shew mercy, but persecuted the poor and needy man, that he might even slay the broken in heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.109.17" /> \begin{signline}As he loved cursing, so let it come unto him: as he delighted not in blessing, so let it be far from him.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.109.18" /> \begin{signline}As he clothed himself with cursing like as with his garment, so let it come into his bowels like water, and like oil into his bones.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.109.19" /> \begin{signline}Let it be unto him as the garment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}covereth him, and for a girdle wherewith he is girded continually.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.109.20" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Let\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the reward of mine adversaries from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and of them that speak evil against my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.109.21" /> \begin{signline}But do thou for me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the Lord, for thy name’s sake: because thy mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good, deliver thou me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.109.22" />\begin{signline}For I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor and needy, and my heart is wounded within me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.109.23" /> \begin{signline}I am gone like the shadow when it declineth: I am tossed up and down as the locust.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.109.24" /> \begin{signline}My knees are weak through fasting; and my flesh faileth of fatness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.109.25" /> \begin{signline}I became also a reproach unto them:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they looked upon me they shaked their heads.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.109.26" /> \begin{signline}Help me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my God: O save me according to thy mercy:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.109.27" /> \begin{signline}That they may know that this\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy hand;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, hast done it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.109.28" /> \begin{signline}Let them curse, but bless thou: when they arise, let them be ashamed; but let thy servant rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.109.29" /> \begin{signline}Let mine adversaries be clothed with shame, and let them cover themselves with their own confusion, as with a mantle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.109.30" /> \begin{signline}I will greatly praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with my mouth; yea, I will praise him among the multitude.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.109.31" /> \begin{signline}For he shall stand at the right hand of the poor, to save\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from those that condemn his soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="110" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.110.1" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, until I make thine enemies thy footstool.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.110.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion: rule thou in the midst of thine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.110.3" /> \begin{signline}Thy people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}willing in the day of thy power, in the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning: thou hast the dew of thy youth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.110.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath sworn, and will not repent, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.110.5" /> \begin{signline}The Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.110.6" /> \begin{signline}He shall judge among the heathen, he shall fill\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the places\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the dead bodies; he shall wound the heads over many countries.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.110.7" /> \begin{signline}He shall drink of the brook in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="111" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.111.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. I will praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whole heart, in the assembly of the upright, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the congregation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.111.2" /> \begin{signline}The works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great, sought out of all them that have pleasure therein.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.111.3" /> \begin{signline}His work\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}honourable and glorious: and his righteousness endureth for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.111.4" /> \begin{signline}He hath made his wonderful works to be remembered: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gracious and full of compassion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.111.5" /> \begin{signline}He hath given meat unto them that fear him: he will ever be mindful of his covenant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.111.6" /> \begin{signline}He hath shewed his people the power of his works, that he may give them the heritage of the heathen.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.111.7" /> \begin{signline}The works of his hands\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}verity and judgment; all his commandments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.111.8" /> \begin{signline}They stand fast for ever and ever,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}done in truth and uprightness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.111.9" /> \begin{signline}He sent redemption unto his people: he hath commanded his covenant for ever: holy and reverend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.111.10" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the beginning of wisdom: a good understanding have all they that do\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his commandments:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his praise endureth for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="112" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.112.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}delighteth greatly in his commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.112.2" /> \begin{signline}His seed shall be mighty upon earth: the generation of the upright shall be blessed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.112.3" /> \begin{signline}Wealth and riches\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his house: and his righteousness endureth for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.112.4" /> \begin{signline}Unto the upright there ariseth light in the darkness:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gracious, and full of compassion, and righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.112.5" /> \begin{signline}A good man sheweth favour, and lendeth: he will guide his affairs with discretion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.112.6" /> \begin{signline}Surely he shall not be moved for ever: the righteous shall be in everlasting remembrance.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.112.7" /> \begin{signline}He shall not be afraid of evil tidings: his heart is fixed, trusting in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.112.8" /> \begin{signline}His heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}established, he shall not be afraid, until he see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon his enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.112.9" /> \begin{signline}He hath dispersed, he hath given to the poor; his righteousness endureth for ever; his horn shall be exalted with honour.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.112.10" /> \begin{signline}The wicked shall see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and be grieved; he shall gnash with his teeth, and melt away: the desire of the wicked shall perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="113" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.113.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise, O ye servants of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, praise the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.113.2" /> \begin{signline}Blessed be the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}from this time forth and for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.113.3" /> \begin{signline}From the rising of the sun unto the going down of the same the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}name\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to be praised.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.113.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high above all nations,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his glory above the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.113.5" />\begin{signline}Who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God, who dwelleth on high,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.113.6" /> \begin{signline}Who humbleth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}himself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to behold\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the things that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in heaven, and in the earth!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.113.7" /> \begin{signline}He raiseth up the poor out of the dust,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lifteth the needy out of the dunghill;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.113.8" /> \begin{signline}That he may set\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with princes,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the princes of his people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.113.9" /> \begin{signline}He maketh the barren woman to keep house,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and to be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a joyful mother of children. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="114" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.114.1" /> \begin{signline}When Israel went out of Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of strange language;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.114.2" /> \begin{signline}Judah was his sanctuary,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Israel his dominion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.114.3" /> \begin{signline}The sea saw\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and fled: Jordan was driven back.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.114.4" /> \begin{signline}The mountains skipped like rams,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the little hills like lambs.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.114.5" />\begin{signline}What\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ailed\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thee, O thou sea, that thou fleddest? thou Jordan,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou wast driven back?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.114.6" /> \begin{signline}Ye mountains,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ye skipped like rams;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ye little hills, like lambs?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.114.7" /> \begin{signline}Tremble, thou earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.114.8" /> \begin{signline}Which turned the rock\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}into\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a standing water, the flint into a fountain of waters.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="115" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.115.1" /> \begin{signline}Not unto us, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, not unto us, but unto thy name give glory, for thy mercy,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for thy truth’s sake.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.115.2" /> \begin{signline}Wherefore should the heathen say, Where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}now their God?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.115.3" /> \begin{signline}But our God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the heavens: he hath done whatsoever he hath pleased.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.115.4" /> \begin{signline}Their idols\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.115.5" /> \begin{signline}They have mouths, but they speak not: eyes have they, but they see not:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.115.6" /> \begin{signline}They have ears, but they hear not: noses have they, but they smell not:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.115.7" /> \begin{signline}They have hands, but they handle not: feet have they, but they walk not: neither speak they through their throat.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.115.8" /> \begin{signline}They that make them are like unto them;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}every one that trusteth in them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.115.9" /> \begin{signline}O Israel, trust thou in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their help and their shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.115.10" /> \begin{signline}O house of Aaron, trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their help and their shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.115.11" /> \begin{signline}Ye that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their help and their shield.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.115.12" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath been mindful of us: he will bless\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he will bless the house of Israel; he will bless the house of Aaron.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.115.13" /> \begin{signline}He will bless them that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}both\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}small and great.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.115.14" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall increase you more and more, you and your children.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.115.15" />\begin{signline}Ye\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blessed of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}which made heaven and earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.115.16" /> \begin{signline}The heaven,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the heavens,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but the earth hath he given to the children of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.115.17" /> \begin{signline}The dead praise not the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, neither any that go down into silence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.115.18" /> \begin{signline}But we will bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}from this time forth and for evermore. Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="116" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.116.1" /> \begin{signline}I love the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, because he hath heard my voice\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my supplications.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.116.2" /> \begin{signline}Because he hath inclined his ear unto me, therefore will I call upon\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as long as I live.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.116.3" /> \begin{signline}The sorrows of death compassed me, and the pains of hell gat hold upon me: I found trouble and sorrow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.116.4" /> \begin{signline}Then called I upon the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I beseech thee, deliver my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.116.5" /> \begin{signline}Gracious\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and righteous; yea, our God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}merciful.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.116.6" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}preserveth the simple: I was brought low, and he helped me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.116.7" /> \begin{signline}Return unto thy rest, O my soul; for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath dealt bountifully with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.116.8" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast delivered my soul from death, mine eyes from tears,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my feet from falling.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.116.9" /> \begin{signline}I will walk before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in the land of the living.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.116.10" /> \begin{signline}I believed, therefore have I spoken: I was greatly afflicted:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.116.11" /> \begin{signline}I said in my haste, All men\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}liars.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.116.12" /> \begin{signline}What shall I render unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all his benefits toward me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.116.13" /> \begin{signline}I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.116.14" /> \begin{signline}I will pay my vows unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}now in the presence of all his people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.116.15" /> \begin{signline}Precious in the sight of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the death of his saints.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.116.16" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, truly I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servant; I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servant,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the son of thine handmaid: thou hast loosed my bonds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.116.17" /> \begin{signline}I will offer to thee the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and will call upon the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.116.18" /> \begin{signline}I will pay my vows unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}now in the presence of all his people,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.116.19" /> \begin{signline}In the courts of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}house, in the midst of thee, O Jerusalem. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="117" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.117.1" /> \begin{signline}O praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all ye nations: praise him, all ye people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.117.2" /> \begin{signline}For his merciful kindness is great toward us: and the truth of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="118" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.118.1" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: because his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.118.2" /> \begin{signline}Let Israel now say, that his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.118.3" /> \begin{signline}Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.118.4" /> \begin{signline}Let them now that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}say, that his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.118.5" /> \begin{signline}I called upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}in distress: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}answered me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and set me\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in a large place.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.118.6" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}on my side; I will not fear: what can man do unto me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.118.7" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}taketh my part with them that help me: therefore shall I see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my desire\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon them that hate me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.118.8" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better to trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}than to put confidence in man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.118.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better to trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}than to put confidence in princes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.118.10" /> \begin{signline}All nations compassed me about: but in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will I destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.118.11" /> \begin{signline}They compassed me about; yea, they compassed me about: but in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}I will destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.118.12" /> \begin{signline}They compassed me about like bees; they are quenched as the fire of thorns: for in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}I will destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.118.13" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast thrust sore at me that I might fall: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}helped me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.118.14" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my strength and song, and is become my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.118.15" /> \begin{signline}The voice of rejoicing and salvation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the tabernacles of the righteous: the right hand of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}doeth valiantly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.118.16" /> \begin{signline}The right hand of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}is exalted: the right hand of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}doeth valiantly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.118.17" /> \begin{signline}I shall not die, but live, and declare the works of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.118.18" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath chastened me sore: but he hath not given me over unto death.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.118.19" /> \begin{signline}Open to me the gates of righteousness: I will go into them,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I will praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.118.20" /> \begin{signline}This gate of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, into which the righteous shall enter.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.118.21" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee: for thou hast heard me, and art become my salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.118.22" /> \begin{signline}The stone\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the builders refused is become the head\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}stone\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the corner.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.118.23" />\begin{signline}This is the \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}doing; it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}marvellous in our eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.118.24" />\begin{signline}This\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the day\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.118.25" /> \begin{signline}Save now, I beseech thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I beseech thee, send now prosperity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.118.26" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that cometh in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: we have blessed you out of the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.118.27" /> \begin{signline}God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, which hath shewed us light: bind the sacrifice with cords,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the horns of the altar.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.118.28" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God, and I will praise thee:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God, I will exalt thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.118.29" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="119" />
<s><tl> \begin{signline}א ALEPH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.119.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.119.2" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that keep his testimonies,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seek him with the whole heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.119.3" /> \begin{signline}They also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.119.4" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast commanded\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to keep thy precepts diligently.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.119.5" /> \begin{signline}O that my ways were directed to keep thy statutes!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.119.6" /> \begin{signline}Then shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.119.7" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned thy righteous judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.119.8" /> \begin{signline}I will keep thy statutes: O forsake me not utterly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ב BETH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.119.9" /> \begin{signline}Wherewithal shall a young man cleanse his way? by taking heed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.119.10" /> \begin{signline}With my whole heart have I sought thee: O let me not wander from thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.119.11" /> \begin{signline}Thy word have I hid in mine heart, that I might not sin against thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.119.12" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.119.13" /> \begin{signline}With my lips have I declared all the judgments of thy mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.119.14" /> \begin{signline}I have rejoiced in the way of thy testimonies, as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}much as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in all riches.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.119.15" /> \begin{signline}I will meditate in thy precepts, and have respect unto thy ways.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.119.16" /> \begin{signline}I will delight myself in thy statutes: I will not forget thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ג GIMEL.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.119.17" /> \begin{signline}Deal bountifully with thy servant,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I may live, and keep thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.119.18" /> \begin{signline}Open thou mine eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.119.19" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a stranger in the earth: hide not thy commandments from me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.119.20" /> \begin{signline}My soul breaketh for the longing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that it hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto thy judgments at all times.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.119.21" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast rebuked the proud\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cursed, which do err from thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.119.22" /> \begin{signline}Remove from me reproach and contempt; for I have kept thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.119.23" /> \begin{signline}Princes also did sit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speak against me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servant did meditate in thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.119.24" /> \begin{signline}Thy testimonies also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my delight\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my counsellors.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ד DALETH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.119.25" /> \begin{signline}My soul cleaveth  unto the dust: quicken thou me according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.119.26" /> \begin{signline}I have declared my ways, and thou heardest me: teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="27" bcv="PSA.119.27" /> \begin{signline}Make me to understand the way of thy precepts: so shall I talk of thy wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="28" bcv="PSA.119.28" /> \begin{signline}My soul melteth for heaviness: strengthen thou me according unto thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="29" bcv="PSA.119.29" /> \begin{signline}Remove from me the way of lying: and grant me thy law graciously.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="30" bcv="PSA.119.30" /> \begin{signline}I have chosen the way of truth: thy judgments have I laid\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}before me\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="31" bcv="PSA.119.31" /> \begin{signline}I have stuck unto thy testimonies: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, put me not to shame.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="32" bcv="PSA.119.32" /> \begin{signline}I will run the way of thy commandments, when thou shalt enlarge my heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ה HE.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="33" bcv="PSA.119.33" /> \begin{signline}Teach me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, the way of thy statutes; and I shall keep it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the end.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="34" bcv="PSA.119.34" /> \begin{signline}Give me understanding, and I shall keep thy law; yea, I shall observe it with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whole heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="35" bcv="PSA.119.35" /> \begin{signline}Make me to go in the path of thy commandments; for therein do I delight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="36" bcv="PSA.119.36" /> \begin{signline}Incline my heart unto thy testimonies, and not to covetousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="37" bcv="PSA.119.37" /> \begin{signline}Turn away mine eyes from beholding vanity;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}quicken thou me in thy way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="38" bcv="PSA.119.38" /> \begin{signline}Stablish thy word unto thy servant, who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is devoted\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to thy fear.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="39" bcv="PSA.119.39" /> \begin{signline}Turn away my reproach which I fear: for thy judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="40" bcv="PSA.119.40" /> \begin{signline}Behold, I have longed after thy precepts: quicken me in thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ו VAU.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="41" bcv="PSA.119.41" /> \begin{signline}Let thy mercies come also unto me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy salvation, according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="42" bcv="PSA.119.42" /> \begin{signline}So shall I have wherewith to answer him that reproacheth me: for I trust in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="43" bcv="PSA.119.43" /> \begin{signline}And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth; for I have hoped in thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="44" bcv="PSA.119.44" /> \begin{signline}So shall I keep thy law continually for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="45" bcv="PSA.119.45" /> \begin{signline}And I will walk at liberty: for I seek thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="46" bcv="PSA.119.46" /> \begin{signline}I will speak of thy testimonies also before kings, and will not be ashamed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="47" bcv="PSA.119.47" /> \begin{signline}And I will delight myself in thy commandments, which I have loved.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="48" bcv="PSA.119.48" /> \begin{signline}My hands also will I lift up unto thy commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ז ZAIN.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="49" bcv="PSA.119.49" /> \begin{signline}Remember the word unto thy servant, upon which thou hast caused me to hope.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="50" bcv="PSA.119.50" />\begin{signline}This\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my comfort in my affliction: for thy word hath quickened me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="51" bcv="PSA.119.51" /> \begin{signline}The proud have had me greatly in derision:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have I not declined from thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="52" bcv="PSA.119.52" /> \begin{signline}I remembered thy judgments of old, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and have comforted myself.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="53" bcv="PSA.119.53" /> \begin{signline}Horror hath taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="54" bcv="PSA.119.54" /> \begin{signline}Thy statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="55" bcv="PSA.119.55" /> \begin{signline}I have remembered thy name, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in the night, and have kept thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="56" bcv="PSA.119.56" /> \begin{signline}This I had, because I kept thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ח CHETH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="57" bcv="PSA.119.57" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Thou art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my portion, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I have said that I would keep thy words.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="58" bcv="PSA.119.58" /> \begin{signline}I intreated thy favour with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whole heart: be merciful unto me according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="59" bcv="PSA.119.59" /> \begin{signline}I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="60" bcv="PSA.119.60" /> \begin{signline}I made haste, and delayed not to keep thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="61" bcv="PSA.119.61" /> \begin{signline}The bands of the wicked have robbed me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I have not forgotten thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="62" bcv="PSA.119.62" /> \begin{signline}At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto thee because of thy righteous judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="63" bcv="PSA.119.63" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a companion of all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that fear thee, and of them that keep thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="64" bcv="PSA.119.64" /> \begin{signline}The earth, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ט TETH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="65" bcv="PSA.119.65" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, according unto thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="66" bcv="PSA.119.66" /> \begin{signline}Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="67" bcv="PSA.119.67" /> \begin{signline}Before I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="68" bcv="PSA.119.68" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good, and doest good; teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="69" bcv="PSA.119.69" /> \begin{signline}The proud have forged a lie against me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I will keep thy precepts with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whole heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="70" bcv="PSA.119.70" /> \begin{signline}Their heart is as fat as grease;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I delight in thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="71" bcv="PSA.119.71" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="72" bcv="PSA.119.72" /> \begin{signline}The law of thy mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better unto me than thousands of gold and silver.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}י JOD.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="73" bcv="PSA.119.73" /> \begin{signline}Thy hands have made me and fashioned me: give me understanding, that I may learn thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="74" bcv="PSA.119.74" /> \begin{signline}They that fear thee will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="75" bcv="PSA.119.75" /> \begin{signline}I know, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, that thy judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou in faithfulness hast afflicted me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="76" bcv="PSA.119.76" /> \begin{signline}Let, I pray thee, thy merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="77" bcv="PSA.119.77" /> \begin{signline}Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my delight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="78" bcv="PSA.119.78" /> \begin{signline}Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I will meditate in thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="79" bcv="PSA.119.79" /> \begin{signline}Let those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="80" bcv="PSA.119.80" /> \begin{signline}Let my heart be sound in thy statutes; that I be not ashamed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}כ CAPH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="81" bcv="PSA.119.81" /> \begin{signline}My soul fainteth  for thy salvation:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I hope in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="82" bcv="PSA.119.82" /> \begin{signline}Mine eyes fail for thy word, saying, When wilt thou comfort me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="83" bcv="PSA.119.83" /> \begin{signline}For I am become like a bottle in the smoke;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do I not forget thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="84" bcv="PSA.119.84" />\begin{signline}How many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the days of thy servant? when wilt thou execute judgment on them that persecute me?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="85" bcv="PSA.119.85" /> \begin{signline}The proud have digged pits for me, which\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not after thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="86" bcv="PSA.119.86" /> \begin{signline}All thy commandments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help thou me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="87" bcv="PSA.119.87" /> \begin{signline}They had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="88" bcv="PSA.119.88" /> \begin{signline}Quicken me after thy lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of thy mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ל LAMED.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="89" bcv="PSA.119.89" /> \begin{signline}For ever, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thy word is settled in heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="90" bcv="PSA.119.90" /> \begin{signline}Thy faithfulness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto all generations: thou hast established the earth, and it abideth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="91" bcv="PSA.119.91" /> \begin{signline}They continue this day according to thine ordinances: for all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servants.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="92" bcv="PSA.119.92" /> \begin{signline}Unless thy law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}had been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my delights, I should then have perished in mine affliction.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="93" bcv="PSA.119.93" /> \begin{signline}I will never forget thy precepts: for with them thou hast quickened me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="94" bcv="PSA.119.94" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine, save me; for I have sought thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="95" bcv="PSA.119.95" /> \begin{signline}The wicked have waited for me to destroy me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I will consider thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="96" bcv="PSA.119.96" /> \begin{signline}I have seen an end of all perfection:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy commandment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}exceeding broad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}מ MEM.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="97" bcv="PSA.119.97" /> \begin{signline}O how love I thy law! it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my meditation all the day.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="98" bcv="PSA.119.98" /> \begin{signline}Thou through thy commandments hast made me wiser than mine enemies: for they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ever with me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="99" bcv="PSA.119.99" /> \begin{signline}I have more understanding than all my teachers: for thy testimonies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my meditation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="100" bcv="PSA.119.100" /> \begin{signline}I understand more than the ancients, because I keep thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="101" bcv="PSA.119.101" /> \begin{signline}I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="102" bcv="PSA.119.102" /> \begin{signline}I have not departed from thy judgments: for thou hast taught me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="103" bcv="PSA.119.103" /> \begin{signline}How sweet are thy words unto my taste!\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea, sweeter\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}than honey to my mouth!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="104" bcv="PSA.119.104" /> \begin{signline}Through thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}נ NUN.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="105" bcv="PSA.119.105" /> \begin{signline}Thy word\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a lamp unto my feet, and a light unto my path.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="106" bcv="PSA.119.106" /> \begin{signline}I have sworn, and I will perform\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, that I will keep thy righteous judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="107" bcv="PSA.119.107" /> \begin{signline}I am afflicted very much: quicken  me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, according unto thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="108" bcv="PSA.119.108" /> \begin{signline}Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and teach me thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="109" bcv="PSA.119.109" /> \begin{signline}My soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}continually in my hand: yet do I not forget thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="110" bcv="PSA.119.110" /> \begin{signline}The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="111" bcv="PSA.119.111" /> \begin{signline}Thy testimonies have I taken as an heritage for ever: for they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rejoicing of my heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="112" bcv="PSA.119.112" /> \begin{signline}I have inclined mine heart to perform thy statutes alway,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even unto\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the end.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ס SAMECH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="113" bcv="PSA.119.113" /> \begin{signline}I hate\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}vain\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thoughts: but thy law do I love.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="114" bcv="PSA.119.114" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my hiding place and my shield: I hope in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="115" bcv="PSA.119.115" /> \begin{signline}Depart from me, ye evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="116" bcv="PSA.119.116" /> \begin{signline}Uphold me according unto thy word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="117" bcv="PSA.119.117" /> \begin{signline}Hold thou me up, and I shall be safe: and I will have respect unto thy statutes continually.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="118" bcv="PSA.119.118" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast trodden down all them that err from thy statutes: for their deceit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}falsehood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="119" bcv="PSA.119.119" /> \begin{signline}Thou puttest away all the wicked of the earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dross: therefore I love thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="120" bcv="PSA.119.120" /> \begin{signline}My flesh trembleth for fear of thee; and I am afraid of thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ע AIN.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="121" bcv="PSA.119.121" /> \begin{signline}I have done judgment and justice: leave me not to mine oppressors.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="122" bcv="PSA.119.122" /> \begin{signline}Be surety for thy servant for good: let not the proud oppress me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="123" bcv="PSA.119.123" /> \begin{signline}Mine eyes fail for thy salvation, and for the word of thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="124" bcv="PSA.119.124" /> \begin{signline}Deal with thy servant according unto thy mercy, and teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="125" bcv="PSA.119.125" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servant; give me understanding, that I may know thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="126" bcv="PSA.119.126" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}time for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, \end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, to work:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they have made void thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="127" bcv="PSA.119.127" /> \begin{signline}Therefore I love thy commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="128" bcv="PSA.119.128" />\begin{signline}Therefore I esteem all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}precepts\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}concerning\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things to be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I hate every false way.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}פ PE.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="129" bcv="PSA.119.129" /> \begin{signline}Thy testimonies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wonderful: therefore doth my soul keep them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="130" bcv="PSA.119.130" /> \begin{signline}The entrance of thy words giveth light; it giveth understanding unto the simple.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="131" bcv="PSA.119.131" /> \begin{signline}I opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="132" bcv="PSA.119.132" /> \begin{signline}Look thou upon me, and be merciful unto me, as thou usest to do unto those that love thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="133" bcv="PSA.119.133" /> \begin{signline}Order my steps in thy word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="134" bcv="PSA.119.134" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="135" bcv="PSA.119.135" /> \begin{signline}Make thy face to shine upon thy servant; and teach me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="136" bcv="PSA.119.136" /> \begin{signline}Rivers of waters run down mine eyes, because they keep not thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}צ TZADDI.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="137" bcv="PSA.119.137" /> \begin{signline}Righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and upright\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="138" bcv="PSA.119.138" /> \begin{signline}Thy testimonies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast commanded\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteous and very faithful.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="139" bcv="PSA.119.139" /> \begin{signline}My zeal hath consumed me, because mine enemies have forgotten thy words.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="140" bcv="PSA.119.140" /> \begin{signline}Thy word\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}very pure: therefore thy servant loveth it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="141" bcv="PSA.119.141" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}small and despised:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do not I forget thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="142" bcv="PSA.119.142" /> \begin{signline}Thy righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an everlasting righteousness, and thy law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="143" bcv="PSA.119.143" /> \begin{signline}Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy commandments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my delights.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="144" bcv="PSA.119.144" /> \begin{signline}The righteousness of thy testimonies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ק KOPH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="145" bcv="PSA.119.145" /> \begin{signline}I cried with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whole heart; hear me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I will keep thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="146" bcv="PSA.119.146" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="147" bcv="PSA.119.147" /> \begin{signline}I prevented the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="148" bcv="PSA.119.148" /> \begin{signline}Mine eyes prevent the\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}night\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}watches, that I might meditate in thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="149" bcv="PSA.119.149" /> \begin{signline}Hear my voice according unto thy lovingkindness: O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, quicken me according to thy judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="150" bcv="PSA.119.150" /> \begin{signline}They draw nigh that follow after mischief: they are far from thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="151" bcv="PSA.119.151" />\begin{signline}Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}near, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and all thy commandments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="152" bcv="PSA.119.152" /> \begin{signline}Concerning thy testimonies, I have known of old that thou hast founded them for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ר RESH.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="153" bcv="PSA.119.153" /> \begin{signline}Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="154" bcv="PSA.119.154" /> \begin{signline}Plead my cause, and deliver me: quicken me according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="155" bcv="PSA.119.155" /> \begin{signline}Salvation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="156" bcv="PSA.119.156" /> \begin{signline}Great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy tender mercies, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: quicken me according to thy judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="157" bcv="PSA.119.157" /> \begin{signline}Many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my persecutors and mine enemies;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do I not decline from thy testimonies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="158" bcv="PSA.119.158" /> \begin{signline}I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="159" bcv="PSA.119.159" /> \begin{signline}Consider how I love thy precepts: quicken me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, according to thy lovingkindness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="160" bcv="PSA.119.160" /> \begin{signline}Thy word\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}true\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><s><tl> \begin{signline}ש SCHIN.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="161" bcv="PSA.119.161" /> \begin{signline}Princes have persecuted me without a cause: but my heart standeth in awe of thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="162" bcv="PSA.119.162" /> \begin{signline}I rejoice at thy word, as one that findeth great spoil.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="163" bcv="PSA.119.163" /> \begin{signline}I hate and abhor lying:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy law do I love.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="164" bcv="PSA.119.164" /> \begin{signline}Seven times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="165" bcv="PSA.119.165" /> \begin{signline}Great peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="166" bcv="PSA.119.166" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I have hoped for thy salvation, and done thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="167" bcv="PSA.119.167" /> \begin{signline}My soul hath kept thy testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="168" bcv="PSA.119.168" /> \begin{signline}I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><s><tl> \begin{signline}ת TAU.\end{signline}</tl>
</s><q><v id="169" bcv="PSA.119.169" /> \begin{signline}Let my cry come near before thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: give me understanding according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="170" bcv="PSA.119.170" /> \begin{signline}Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="171" bcv="PSA.119.171" /> \begin{signline}My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="172" bcv="PSA.119.172" /> \begin{signline}My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="173" bcv="PSA.119.173" /> \begin{signline}Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="174" bcv="PSA.119.174" /> \begin{signline}I have longed for thy salvation, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and thy law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my delight.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="175" bcv="PSA.119.175" /> \begin{signline}Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="176" bcv="PSA.119.176" /> \begin{signline}I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="120" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.120.1" /> \begin{signline}In my distress I cried unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he heard me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.120.2" /> \begin{signline}Deliver my soul, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, from lying lips,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from a deceitful tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.120.3" /> \begin{signline}What shall be given unto thee? or what shall be done unto thee, thou false tongue?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.120.4" /> \begin{signline}Sharp arrows of the mighty, with coals of juniper.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.120.5" /> \begin{signline}Woe is me, that I sojourn in Mesech,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I dwell in the tents of Kedar!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.120.6" /> \begin{signline}My soul hath long dwelt with him that hateth peace.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.120.7" />\begin{signline}I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace: but when I speak, they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for war.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="121" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.121.1" /> \begin{signline}I will lift up mine eyes unto the hills, from whence cometh my help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.121.2" /> \begin{signline}My help\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, which made heaven and earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.121.3" /> \begin{signline}He will not suffer thy foot to be moved: he that keepeth thee will not slumber.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.121.4" /> \begin{signline}Behold, he that keepeth Israel shall neither slumber nor sleep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.121.5" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy keeper: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy shade upon thy right hand.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.121.6" /> \begin{signline}The sun shall not smite thee by day, nor the moon by night.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.121.7" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall preserve thee from all evil: he shall preserve thy soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.121.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall preserve thy going out and thy coming in from this time forth, and even for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="122" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.122.1" /> \begin{signline}I was glad when they said unto me, Let us go into the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.122.2" /> \begin{signline}Our feet shall stand within thy gates, O Jerusalem.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.122.3" /> \begin{signline}Jerusalem is builded as a city that is compact together:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.122.4" /> \begin{signline}Whither the tribes go up, the tribes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, unto the testimony of Israel, to give thanks unto the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.122.5" /> \begin{signline}For there are set thrones of judgment, the thrones of the house of David.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.122.6" /> \begin{signline}Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: they shall prosper that love thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.122.7" /> \begin{signline}Peace be within thy walls,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}prosperity within thy palaces.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.122.8" /> \begin{signline}For my brethren and companions’ sakes, I will now say, Peace\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}within thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.122.9" /> \begin{signline}Because of the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God I will seek thy good.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="123" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.123.1" /> \begin{signline}Unto thee lift I up mine eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.123.2" /> \begin{signline}Behold, as the eyes of servants\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}look\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto the hand of their masters,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the eyes of a maiden unto the hand of her mistress; so our eyes\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wait\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}our God, until that he have mercy upon us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.123.3" /> \begin{signline}Have mercy upon us, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, have mercy upon us: for we are exceedingly filled with contempt.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.123.4" /> \begin{signline}Our soul is exceedingly filled with the scorning of those that are at ease,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the contempt of the proud.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="124" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.124.1" /> \begin{signline}If\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it had not been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}who was on our side, now may Israel say;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.124.2" /> \begin{signline}If\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it had not been\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}who was on our side, when men rose up against us:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.124.3" /> \begin{signline}Then they had swallowed us up quick, when their wrath was kindled against us:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.124.4" /> \begin{signline}Then the waters had overwhelmed us, the stream had gone over our soul:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.124.5" /> \begin{signline}Then the proud waters had gone over our soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.124.6" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, who hath not given us\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a prey to their teeth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.124.7" /> \begin{signline}Our soul is escaped as a bird out of the snare of the fowlers: the snare is broken, and we are escaped.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.124.8" /> \begin{signline}Our help\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, who made heaven and earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="125" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.125.1" /> \begin{signline}They that trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as mount Zion,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cannot be removed,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abideth for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.125.2" /> \begin{signline}As the mountains\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}round about Jerusalem, so the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}round about his people from henceforth even for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.125.3" /> \begin{signline}For the rod of the wicked shall not rest upon the lot of the righteous; lest the righteous put forth their hands unto iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.125.4" /> \begin{signline}Do good, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, unto\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}those that be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to them that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright in their hearts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.125.5" /> \begin{signline}As for such as turn aside unto their crooked ways, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall lead them forth with the workers of iniquity:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="126" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.126.1" /> \begin{signline}When the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}turned again the captivity of Zion, we were like them that dream.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.126.2" /> \begin{signline}Then was our mouth filled with laughter, and our tongue with singing: then said they among the heathen, The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath done great things for them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.126.3" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath done great things for us;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whereof\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}we are glad.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.126.4" /> \begin{signline}Turn again our captivity, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, as the streams in the south.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.126.5" /> \begin{signline}They that sow in tears shall reap in joy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.126.6" /> \begin{signline}He that goeth forth and weepeth, bearing precious seed, shall doubtless come again with rejoicing, bringing his sheaves\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="127" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees\end{signline}
\begin{signline}for Solomon.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.127.1" /> \begin{signline}Except the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}build  the house, they labour in vain that build it: except the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}keep the city, the watchman waketh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in vain.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.127.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vain for you to rise up early, to sit up late, to eat the bread of sorrows:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}so he giveth his beloved sleep.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.127.3" /> \begin{signline}Lo, children\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an heritage of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the fruit of the womb\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}reward.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.127.4" /> \begin{signline}As arrows\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the hand of a mighty man; so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}children of the youth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.127.5" /> \begin{signline}Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man that hath his quiver full of them: they shall not be ashamed, but they shall speak with the enemies in the gate.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="128" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.128.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}every one that feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; that walketh in his ways.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.128.2" /> \begin{signline}For thou shalt eat the labour of thine hands: happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shalt\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}well with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.128.3" /> \begin{signline}Thy wife\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a fruitful vine by the sides of thine house: thy children like olive plants round about thy table.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.128.4" /> \begin{signline}Behold, that thus shall the man be blessed that feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.128.5" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall bless thee out of Zion: and thou shalt see the good of Jerusalem all the days of thy life.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.128.6" /> \begin{signline}Yea, thou shalt see thy children’s children,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace upon Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="129" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.129.1" /> \begin{signline}Many a time have they afflicted me from my youth, may Israel now say:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.129.2" /> \begin{signline}Many a time have they afflicted me from my youth: yet they have not prevailed against me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.129.3" /> \begin{signline}The plowers plowed upon my back: they made long their furrows.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.129.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteous: he hath cut asunder the cords of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.129.5" /> \begin{signline}Let them all be confounded and turned back that hate Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.129.6" /> \begin{signline}Let them be as the grass\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the housetops, which withereth afore it groweth up:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.129.7" /> \begin{signline}Wherewith the mower filleth not his hand; nor he that bindeth sheaves his bosom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.129.8" /> \begin{signline}Neither do they which go by say, The blessing of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon you: we bless you in the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="130" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.130.1" /> \begin{signline}Out of the depths have I cried unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.130.2" /> \begin{signline}Lord, hear my voice: let thine ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.130.3" /> \begin{signline}If thou,\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, shouldest mark iniquities, O Lord, who shall stand?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.130.4" />\begin{signline}But\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}forgiveness with thee, that thou mayest be feared.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.130.5" /> \begin{signline}I wait for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, my soul doth wait, and in his word do I hope.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.130.6" /> \begin{signline}My soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}waiteth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for the Lord more than they that watch for the morning:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}I say, more than\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they that watch for the morning.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.130.7" /> \begin{signline}Let Israel hope in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for with the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mercy, and with him\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}plenteous redemption.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.130.8" /> \begin{signline}And he shall redeem Israel from all his iniquities.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="131" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.131.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, my heart is not haughty, nor mine eyes lofty: neither do I exercise myself in great matters, or in things too high for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.131.2" /> \begin{signline}Surely I have behaved and quieted myself, as a child that is weaned of his mother: my soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}even as a weaned child.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.131.3" /> \begin{signline}Let Israel hope in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}from henceforth and for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="132" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.132.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, remember David,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all his afflictions:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.132.2" /> \begin{signline}How he sware unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vowed unto the mighty\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}God\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of Jacob;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.132.3" /> \begin{signline}Surely I will not come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go up into my bed;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.132.4" /> \begin{signline}I will not give sleep to mine eyes,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}slumber to mine eyelids,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.132.5" /> \begin{signline}Until I find out a place for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, an habitation for the mighty\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}God\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of Jacob.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.132.6" /> \begin{signline}Lo, we heard of it at Ephratah: we found it in the fields of the wood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.132.7" /> \begin{signline}We will go into his tabernacles: we will worship at his footstool.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.132.8" /> \begin{signline}Arise, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, into thy rest; thou, and the ark of thy strength.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.132.9" /> \begin{signline}Let thy priests be clothed with righteousness; and let thy saints shout for joy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.132.10" /> \begin{signline}For thy servant David’s sake turn not away the face of thine anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.132.11" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath sworn\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}truth unto David; he will not turn from it; Of the fruit of thy body will I set upon thy throne.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.132.12" /> \begin{signline}If thy children will keep my covenant and my testimony that I shall teach them, their children shall also sit upon thy throne for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.132.13" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath chosen Zion; he hath desired\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for his habitation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.132.14" />\begin{signline}This\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my rest for ever: here will I dwell; for I have desired it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.132.15" /> \begin{signline}I will abundantly bless her provision: I will satisfy her poor with bread.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.132.16" /> \begin{signline}I will also clothe her priests with salvation: and her saints shall shout aloud for joy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.132.17" /> \begin{signline}There will I make the horn of David to bud: I have ordained a lamp for mine anointed.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.132.18" /> \begin{signline}His enemies will I clothe with shame: but upon himself shall his crown flourish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="133" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.133.1" /> \begin{signline}Behold, how good and how pleasant\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for brethren to dwell together in unity!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.133.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the precious ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Aaron’s beard: that went down to the skirts of his garments;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.133.3" /> \begin{signline}As the dew of Hermon,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and as the dew\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that descended upon the mountains of Zion: for there the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}commanded the blessing,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life for evermore.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="134" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Song\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of degrees.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.134.1" /> \begin{signline}Behold, bless ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}ye\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}servants of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, which by night stand in the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.134.2" /> \begin{signline}Lift up your hands\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sanctuary, and bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.134.3" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}that made heaven and earth bless thee out of Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="135" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.135.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise ye the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; praise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, O ye servants of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.135.2" /> \begin{signline}Ye that stand in the house of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, in the courts of the house of our God,\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.135.3" /> \begin{signline}Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: sing praises unto his name; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pleasant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.135.4" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath chosen Jacob unto himself,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}Israel for his peculiar treasure.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.135.5" /> \begin{signline}For I know that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our Lord\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above all gods.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.135.6" /> \begin{signline}Whatsoever the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}pleased,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}did he in heaven, and in earth, in the seas, and all deep places.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.135.7" /> \begin{signline}He causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings for the rain; he bringeth the wind out of his treasuries.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.135.8" /> \begin{signline}Who smote the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and beast.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.135.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sent tokens and wonders into the midst of thee, O Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his servants.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.135.10" /> \begin{signline}Who smote great nations, and slew mighty kings;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.135.11" /> \begin{signline}Sihon king of the Amorites, and Og king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.135.12" /> \begin{signline}And gave their land\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an heritage, an heritage unto Israel his people.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.135.13" /> \begin{signline}Thy name, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy memorial, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, throughout all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.135.14" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will judge his people, and he will repent himself concerning his servants.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.135.15" /> \begin{signline}The idols of the heathen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.135.16" /> \begin{signline}They have mouths, but they speak not; eyes have they, but they see not;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.135.17" /> \begin{signline}They have ears, but they hear not; neither is there\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}breath in their mouths.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.135.18" /> \begin{signline}They that make them are like unto them:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}every one that trusteth in them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.135.19" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O house of Israel: bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O house of Aaron:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.135.20" /> \begin{signline}Bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O house of Levi: ye that fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, bless the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.135.21" /> \begin{signline}Blessed be the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}out of Zion, which dwelleth at Jerusalem. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="136" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.136.1" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.136.2" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the God of gods: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.136.3" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks to the Lord of lords: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.136.4" /> \begin{signline}To him who alone doeth great wonders: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.136.5" /> \begin{signline}To him that by wisdom made the heavens: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.136.6" /> \begin{signline}To him that stretched out the earth above the waters: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.136.7" /> \begin{signline}To him that made great lights: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.136.8" /> \begin{signline}The sun to rule by day: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.136.9" /> \begin{signline}The moon and stars to rule by night: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.136.10" /> \begin{signline}To him that smote Egypt in their firstborn: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.136.11" /> \begin{signline}And brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.136.12" /> \begin{signline}With a strong hand, and with a stretched out arm: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.136.13" /> \begin{signline}To him which divided the Red sea into parts: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.136.14" /> \begin{signline}And made Israel to pass through the midst of it: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.136.15" /> \begin{signline}But overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red sea: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.136.16" /> \begin{signline}To him which led his people through the wilderness: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.136.17" /> \begin{signline}To him which smote great kings: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.136.18" /> \begin{signline}And slew famous kings: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.136.19" /> \begin{signline}Sihon king of the Amorites: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.136.20" /> \begin{signline}And Og the king of Bashan: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.136.21" /> \begin{signline}And gave their land for an heritage: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.136.22" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an heritage unto Israel his servant: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.136.23" /> \begin{signline}Who remembered us in our low estate: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.136.24" /> \begin{signline}And hath redeemed us from our enemies: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="25" bcv="PSA.136.25" /> \begin{signline}Who giveth food to all flesh: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="26" bcv="PSA.136.26" /> \begin{signline}O give thanks unto the God of heaven: for his mercy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="137" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.137.1" /> \begin{signline}By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, yea, we wept, when we remembered Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.137.2" /> \begin{signline}We hanged our harps upon the willows in the midst thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.137.3" /> \begin{signline}For there they that carried us away captive required of us a song; and they that wasted us\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}required of us\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mirth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}saying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, Sing us\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the songs of Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.137.4" /> \begin{signline}How shall we sing the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}song in a strange land?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.137.5" /> \begin{signline}If I forget thee, O Jerusalem, let my right hand forget\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}her cunning\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.137.6" /> \begin{signline}If I do not remember thee, let my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth; if I prefer not Jerusalem above my chief joy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.137.7" /> \begin{signline}Remember, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, the children of Edom in the day of Jerusalem; who said, Rase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, rase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it, even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the foundation thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.137.8" /> \begin{signline}O daughter of Babylon, who art to be destroyed; happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall he be\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, that rewardeth thee as thou hast served us.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.137.9" /> \begin{signline}Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall he be\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, that taketh and dasheth thy little ones against the stones.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="138" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.138.1" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee with my whole heart: before the gods will I sing praise unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.138.2" /> \begin{signline}I will worship toward thy holy temple, and praise thy name for thy lovingkindness and for thy truth: for thou hast magnified thy word above all thy name.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.138.3" /> \begin{signline}In the day when I cried thou answeredst me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strengthenedst me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strength in my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.138.4" /> \begin{signline}All the kings of the earth shall praise thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, when they hear the words of thy mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.138.5" /> \begin{signline}Yea, they shall sing in the ways of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the glory of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.138.6" /> \begin{signline}Though the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}high, yet hath he respect unto the lowly: but the proud he knoweth afar off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.138.7" /> \begin{signline}Though I walk in the midst of trouble, thou wilt revive me: thou shalt stretch forth thine hand against the wrath of mine enemies, and thy right hand shall save me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.138.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will perfect\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}concerneth me: thy mercy, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for ever: forsake  not the works of thine own hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="139" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.139.1" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou hast searched me, and known\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}me\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.139.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou knowest my downsitting and mine uprising, thou understandest my thought afar off.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.139.3" /> \begin{signline}Thou compassest my path and my lying down, and art acquainted\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all my ways.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.139.4" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not a word in my tongue,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, lo, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, thou knowest it altogether.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.139.5" /> \begin{signline}Thou hast beset me behind and before, and laid thine hand upon me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.139.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Such\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}knowledge\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}too wonderful for me; it is high, I cannot\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}attain\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto it.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.139.7" /> \begin{signline}Whither shall I go from thy spirit? or whither shall I flee from thy presence?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.139.8" /> \begin{signline}If I ascend up into heaven, thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}there: if I make my bed in hell, behold, thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art there\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.139.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}If\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I take the wings of the morning,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.139.10" /> \begin{signline}Even there shall thy hand lead me, and thy right hand shall hold me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.139.11" /> \begin{signline}If I say, Surely the darkness shall cover me; even the night shall be light about me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.139.12" /> \begin{signline}Yea, the darkness hideth not from thee; but the night shineth as the day: the darkness and the light\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}both alike\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.139.13" /> \begin{signline}For thou hast possessed my reins: thou hast covered me in my mother’s womb.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.139.14" /> \begin{signline}I will praise thee; for I am fearfully\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wonderfully made: marvellous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy works; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my soul knoweth right well.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.139.15" /> \begin{signline}My substance was not hid from thee, when I was made in secret,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}curiously wrought in the lowest parts of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.139.16" /> \begin{signline}Thine eyes did see my substance, yet being unperfect; and in thy book all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my members\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}were written,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in continuance were fashioned, when\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as yet there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}none of them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.139.17" /> \begin{signline}How precious also are thy thoughts unto me, O God! how great is the sum of them!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.139.18" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}If\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I should count them, they are more in number than the sand: when I awake, I am still with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.139.19" /> \begin{signline}Surely thou wilt slay the wicked, O God: depart from me therefore, ye bloody men.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.139.20" /> \begin{signline}For they speak against thee wickedly,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine enemies take\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy name\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in vain.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.139.21" /> \begin{signline}Do not I hate them, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, that hate thee? and am not I grieved with those that rise up against thee?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="22" bcv="PSA.139.22" /> \begin{signline}I hate them with perfect hatred: I count them mine enemies.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="23" bcv="PSA.139.23" /> \begin{signline}Search me, O God, and know my heart: try me, and know my thoughts:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="24" bcv="PSA.139.24" /> \begin{signline}And see if\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there be any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="140" />
<d>\begin{signline}To the chief Musician,\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.140.1" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, from the evil man: preserve me from the violent man;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.140.2" /> \begin{signline}Which imagine mischiefs in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}heart; continually are they gathered together\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}war.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.140.3" /> \begin{signline}They have sharpened their tongues like a serpent; adders’ poison\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}under their lips. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.140.4" /> \begin{signline}Keep me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, from the hands of the wicked; preserve  me from the violent man; who have purposed to overthrow my goings.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.140.5" /> \begin{signline}The proud have hid a snare for me, and cords; they have spread a net by the wayside; they have set gins for me. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.140.6" /> \begin{signline}I said unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God: hear the voice of my supplications, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.140.7" /> \begin{signline}O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the Lord, the strength of my salvation, thou hast covered my head in the day of battle.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.140.8" /> \begin{signline}Grant not, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, the desires of the wicked: further not his wicked device;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}lest\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they exalt themselves. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.140.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the head of those that compass me about, let the mischief of their own lips cover them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.140.10" /> \begin{signline}Let burning coals fall upon them: let them be cast into the fire; into deep pits, that they rise not up again.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.140.11" /> \begin{signline}Let not an evil speaker be established in the earth: evil shall hunt the violent man to overthrow\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.140.12" /> \begin{signline}I know that the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will maintain the cause of the afflicted,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the right of the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.140.13" /> \begin{signline}Surely the righteous shall give thanks unto thy name: the upright shall dwell in thy presence.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="141" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.141.1" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.141.2" /> \begin{signline}Let my prayer be set forth before thee\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}incense;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the lifting up of my hands\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the evening sacrifice.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.141.3" /> \begin{signline}Set a watch, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.141.4" /> \begin{signline}Incline not my heart to\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}evil thing, to practise wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.141.5" /> \begin{signline}Let the righteous smite me;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a kindness: and let him reprove me;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an excellent oil,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in their calamities.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.141.6" /> \begin{signline}When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.141.7" /> \begin{signline}Our bones are scattered at the grave’s mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}wood\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.141.8" /> \begin{signline}But mine eyes\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}GOD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}the Lord: in thee is my trust; leave not my soul destitute.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.141.9" /> \begin{signline}Keep me from the snares\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they have laid for me, and the gins of the workers of iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.141.10" /> \begin{signline}Let the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="142" />
<d>\begin{signline}Maschil\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David;\end{signline}
\begin{signline}A Prayer\end{signline}
\begin{signline}when he was in the cave.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.142.1" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with my voice; with my voice unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}did I make my supplication.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.142.2" /> \begin{signline}I poured out my complaint before him; I shewed before him my trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.142.3" /> \begin{signline}When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, then thou knewest my path. In the way wherein I walked have they privily laid a snare for me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.142.4" /> \begin{signline}I looked on\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}my\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right hand, and beheld, but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no man that would know me: refuge failed me; no man cared for my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.142.5" /> \begin{signline}I cried unto thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I said, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my refuge\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my portion in the land of the living.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.142.6" /> \begin{signline}Attend unto my cry; for I am brought very low: deliver me from my persecutors; for they are stronger than I.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.142.7" /> \begin{signline}Bring my soul out of prison, that I may praise thy name: the righteous shall compass me about; for thou shalt deal bountifully with me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="143" />
<d>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.143.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear my prayer, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, give ear to my supplications: in thy faithfulness answer me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.143.2" /> \begin{signline}And enter not into judgment with thy servant: for in thy sight shall no man living be justified.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.143.3" /> \begin{signline}For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath smitten my life down to the ground; he hath made me to dwell in darkness, as those that have been long dead.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.143.4" /> \begin{signline}Therefore is my spirit overwhelmed  within me; my heart within me is desolate.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.143.5" /> \begin{signline}I remember the days of old; I meditate on all thy works; I muse on the work of thy hands.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.143.6" /> \begin{signline}I stretch forth my hands unto thee: my soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thirsteth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}after thee, as a thirsty land. Selah.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.143.7" /> \begin{signline}Hear me speedily, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: my spirit faileth: hide not thy face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.143.8" /> \begin{signline}Cause me to hear thy lovingkindness in the morning; for in thee do I trust: cause me to know the way wherein I should walk; for I lift up my soul unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.143.9" /> \begin{signline}Deliver me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, from mine enemies: I flee unto thee to hide me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.143.10" /> \begin{signline}Teach me to do thy will; for thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my God: thy spirit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good; lead me into the land of uprightness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.143.11" /> \begin{signline}Quicken me, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, for thy name’s sake: for thy righteousness’ sake bring my soul out of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.143.12" /> \begin{signline}And of thy mercy cut off mine enemies, and destroy all them that afflict my soul: for I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy servant.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="144" />
<d><add>\begin{signline}A Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of David.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.144.1" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}my strength, which teacheth my hands to war,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my fingers to fight:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.144.2" /> \begin{signline}My goodness, and my fortress; my high tower, and my deliverer; my shield, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in whom I trust; who subdueth my people under me.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.144.3" />  \begin{signline}\end{signline}<nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, what\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man, that thou takest knowledge of him!\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the son of man, that thou makest account of him!\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.144.4" /> \begin{signline}Man is like to vanity: his days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a shadow that passeth away.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.144.5" /> \begin{signline}Bow thy heavens, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and come down: touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.144.6" /> \begin{signline}Cast forth lightning, and scatter them: shoot out thine arrows, and destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.144.7" /> \begin{signline}Send thine hand from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of strange children;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.144.8" /> \begin{signline}Whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a right hand of falsehood.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.144.9" /> \begin{signline}I will sing a new song unto thee, O God: upon a psaltery\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises unto thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.144.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is he\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that giveth salvation unto kings: who delivereth David his servant from the hurtful sword.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.144.11" /> \begin{signline}Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a right hand of falsehood:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.144.12" /> \begin{signline}That our sons\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as plants grown up in their youth;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our daughters\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as corner stones, polished\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}after\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the similitude of a palace:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.144.13" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}That\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our garners\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}full, affording all manner of store:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our sheep may bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our streets:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.144.14" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}That\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our oxen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strong to labour;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that there be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no breaking in, nor going out; that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no complaining in our streets.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.144.15" /> \begin{signline}Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}people, that is in such a case:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}people, whose God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="145" />
<d>\begin{signline}David’s\end{signline}
<add>\begin{signline}Psalm\end{signline}</add>
\begin{signline}of praise.\end{signline}
</d><q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.145.1" /> \begin{signline}I will extol thee, my God, O king; and I will bless thy name for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.145.2" /> \begin{signline}Every day will I bless thee; and I will praise thy name for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.145.3" /> \begin{signline}Great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and greatly to be praised; and his greatness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unsearchable.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.145.4" /> \begin{signline}One generation shall praise thy works to another, and shall declare thy mighty acts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.145.5" /> \begin{signline}I will speak of the glorious honour of thy majesty, and of thy wondrous works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.145.6" />\begin{signline}And\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall speak of the might of thy terrible acts: and I will declare thy greatness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.145.7" /> \begin{signline}They shall abundantly utter the memory of thy great goodness, and shall sing of thy righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.145.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gracious, and full of compassion; slow to anger, and of great mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.145.9" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good to all: and his tender mercies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}over all his works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.145.10" /> \begin{signline}All thy works shall praise thee, O\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and thy saints shall bless thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.145.11" /> \begin{signline}They shall speak of the glory of thy kingdom, and talk of thy power;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.145.12" /> \begin{signline}To make known to the sons of men his mighty acts, and the glorious majesty of his kingdom.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.145.13" /> \begin{signline}Thy kingdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an everlasting kingdom, and thy dominion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endureth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}throughout all generations.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.145.14" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}upholdeth all that fall, and raiseth up all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}those that be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bowed down.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.145.15" /> \begin{signline}The eyes of all wait upon thee; and thou givest them their meat in due season.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.145.16" /> \begin{signline}Thou openest thine hand, and satisfiest the desire of every living thing.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.145.17" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteous in all his ways, and holy in all his works.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.145.18" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nigh unto all them that call upon him, to all that call upon him in truth.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.145.19" /> \begin{signline}He will fulfil the desire of them that fear him: he also will hear their cry, and will save them.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.145.20" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}preserveth all them that love him: but all the wicked will he destroy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="21" bcv="PSA.145.21" /> \begin{signline}My mouth shall speak the praise of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: and let all flesh bless his holy name for ever and ever.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="146" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.146.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O my soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.146.2" /> \begin{signline}While I live will I praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.146.3" /> \begin{signline}Put not your trust in princes,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the son of man, in whom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no help.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.146.4" /> \begin{signline}His breath goeth forth, he returneth to his earth; in that very day his thoughts perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.146.5" /> \begin{signline}Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is he\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}his God:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.146.6" /> \begin{signline}Which made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that therein\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}which keepeth truth for ever:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.146.7" /> \begin{signline}Which executeth judgment for the oppressed: which giveth food to the hungry. The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}looseth the prisoners:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.146.8" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}openeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the eyes of\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the blind: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}raiseth them that are bowed down: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}loveth the righteous:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.146.9" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}preserveth the strangers; he relieveth the fatherless and widow: but the way of the wicked he turneth upside down.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.146.10" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall reign for ever,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="147" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.147.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good to sing praises unto our God; for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pleasant;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}praise is comely.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.147.2" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}doth build up Jerusalem: he gathereth together the outcasts of Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.147.3" /> \begin{signline}He healeth the broken in heart, and bindeth up their wounds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.147.4" /> \begin{signline}He telleth the number of the stars; he calleth them all by\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}names.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.147.5" /> \begin{signline}Great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}our Lord, and of great power: his understanding\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}infinite.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.147.6" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}lifteth up the meek: he casteth the wicked down to the ground.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.147.7" /> \begin{signline}Sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with thanksgiving; sing praise upon the harp unto our God:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.147.8" /> \begin{signline}Who covereth the heaven with clouds, who prepareth rain for the earth, who maketh grass to grow upon the mountains.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.147.9" /> \begin{signline}He giveth to the beast his food,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the young ravens which cry.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.147.10" /> \begin{signline}He delighteth not in the strength of the horse: he taketh not pleasure in the legs of a man.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.147.11" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}taketh pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.147.12" /> \begin{signline}Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, O Jerusalem; praise thy God, O Zion.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.147.13" /> \begin{signline}For he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; he hath blessed thy children within thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.147.14" /> \begin{signline}He maketh peace\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy borders,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}filleth  thee with the finest of the wheat.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="15" bcv="PSA.147.15" /> \begin{signline}He sendeth forth his commandment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}upon\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}earth: his word runneth very swiftly.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="16" bcv="PSA.147.16" /> \begin{signline}He giveth snow like wool: he scattereth the hoarfrost like ashes.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="17" bcv="PSA.147.17" /> \begin{signline}He casteth forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="18" bcv="PSA.147.18" /> \begin{signline}He sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the waters flow.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="19" bcv="PSA.147.19" /> \begin{signline}He sheweth his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his judgments unto Israel.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="20" bcv="PSA.147.20" /> \begin{signline}He hath not dealt so with any nation: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}judgments, they have not known them. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="148" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.148.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}from the heavens: praise him in the heights.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.148.2" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye him, all his angels: praise ye him, all his hosts.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.148.3" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye him, sun and moon: praise him, all ye stars of light.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.148.4" /> \begin{signline}Praise him, ye heavens of heavens, and ye waters that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.148.5" /> \begin{signline}Let them praise the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for he commanded, and they were created.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.148.6" /> \begin{signline}He hath also stablished them for ever and ever: he hath made a decree which shall not pass.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.148.7" /> \begin{signline}Praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}from the earth, ye dragons, and all deeps:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.148.8" /> \begin{signline}Fire, and hail; snow, and vapour; stormy wind fulfilling his word:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.148.9" /> \begin{signline}Mountains, and all hills; fruitful trees, and all cedars:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="10" bcv="PSA.148.10" /> \begin{signline}Beasts, and all cattle; creeping things, and flying fowl:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="11" bcv="PSA.148.11" /> \begin{signline}Kings of the earth, and all people; princes, and all judges of the earth:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="12" bcv="PSA.148.12" /> \begin{signline}Both young men, and maidens; old men, and children:\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="13" bcv="PSA.148.13" /> \begin{signline}Let them praise the name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: for his name alone is excellent; his glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above the earth and heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="14" bcv="PSA.148.14" /> \begin{signline}He also exalteth the horn of his people, the praise of all his saints;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="149" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.149.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Sing unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}a new song,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his praise in the congregation of saints.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.149.2" /> \begin{signline}Let Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.149.3" /> \begin{signline}Let them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.149.4" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}taketh pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.149.5" /> \begin{signline}Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><b /><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.149.6" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Let\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the high\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}praises\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="7" bcv="PSA.149.7" /> \begin{signline}To execute vengeance upon the heathen,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}punishments upon the people;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="8" bcv="PSA.149.8" /> \begin{signline}To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="9" bcv="PSA.149.9" /> \begin{signline}To execute upon them the judgment written: this honour have all his saints. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><c id="150" />
<q><v id="1" bcv="PSA.150.1" /> \begin{signline}Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise God in his sanctuary: praise him in the firmament of his power.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="2" bcv="PSA.150.2" /> \begin{signline}Praise him for his mighty acts: praise him according to his excellent greatness.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="3" bcv="PSA.150.3" /> \begin{signline}Praise him with the sound of the trumpet: praise him with the psaltery and harp.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="4" bcv="PSA.150.4" /> \begin{signline}Praise him with the timbrel and dance: praise him with stringed instruments and organs.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="5" bcv="PSA.150.5" /> \begin{signline}Praise him upon the loud cymbals: praise him upon the high sounding cymbals.\end{signline}
<ve /></q><q><v id="6" bcv="PSA.150.6" /> \begin{signline}Let every thing that hath breath praise the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}. Praise ye the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></q></book>
